{"department_text": "Automotive", "nr_products": 2695, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Speakers/SubCategory/ID-558", "text": "Speakers", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Store/Promotion.aspx?storeid=19&name=Auto", "description_title": "Car Speakers", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Car-Electronics/Category/ID-283?name=Car-Electronics", "keyword_count": {"speakers": 11, "car speakers": 2}, "description_wc": 355, "description_text": "Nothing is more important to sound quality than speakers. Without a good or at least serviceable sound system, audio content can be distorted and quality can be affected by feedback. Poor playback is especially noticeable while driving, as auto manufacturers don't typically install high-end car speakers. However, drivers can always seek out and install their own devices. The two most important features to look for when buying car speakers are sensitivity and power limits. Sensitivity refers to the sound your speakers produce based on the electricity they receive. Speakers with high sensitivity work best with radios with lower power levels and vice versa. Speakers can produce fuller sounds if they have more features. For instance, a 3-way model has one more driver than a 2-way device, meaning that mid-range sounds are louder. When listening to music, you'll clearly hear background instruments. There are even 4-way speakers that can produce much richer tones than their counterparts. Devices are available in every size and with various settings. You can find the best make and model for your vehicle, so you don't have to return your speakers due to incompatibility. Installing speakers is impossible if you don't have the correct components. Fortunately, there are bundles available that include all the necessary cables so you can easily connect your new speakers with your audio system. These packages are beneficial to budget-conscious drivers who don't want to hire professionals for the relatively simple task. Few people sit in silence on the road. Music is a necessity for most drivers, especially those who like to sing along to their favorite songs while they're in traffic or barreling down empty streets. Speakers play an important part in audio production, so if you want to hear every note clearly you should consider installing new ones in your vehicle. WARNING: Products with exposed solder may contain lead, a chemical known to the State of California to cause cancer, birth defects and other reproductive harm. Please wash hands after handling internal components and motherboards and avoid inhalation of fumes if heating the solder.", "parent_text": "Car Electronics", "keyword_density": {"speakers": "3.1", "car speakers": "1.1"}, "department_id": 10},
