{"department_text": "Automotive", "nr_products": 914, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/In-Dash/SubCategory/ID-557", "text": "In-Dash", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Store/Promotion.aspx?storeid=19&name=Auto", "description_title": "Car Stereo", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Car-Electronics/Category/ID-283?name=Car-Electronics", "keyword_count": {"car": 3, "stereo": 5, "car stereo": 2}, "description_wc": 351, "description_text": "Few drivers enjoy silence while traveling the open road. The car stereo is the device that most people turn to for entertainment during long rides. Whether they listen to news broadcasts or turn up their favorite songs, consumers enjoy hearing something other than their roaring engines and spinning tires. Auto manufacturers don't often put high-end stereos into their vehicles, but any system can be replaced with another that features more components and accessories than standard devices. Most models receive AM and FM signals, but certain radios have different features that not every driver will require. For instance, some models have LCD displays that use touchscreen navigation. These stereos may be more useful to consumers who think it's unsafe to use buttons and knobs while driving. Some devices have DVD players as well, allowing passengers to watch movies or TV shows during those long journeys. Less tech-savvy drivers may prefer radios that resemble their current models but boast increased functionality. Smartphones and MP3 players are commonly used to stream music and podcasts, so consumers may want a gadget that can sync with their mobile devices. Fortunately, radios with connection ports that are compatible with most wires are available. There are also some models with USB slots, while others use headphone jacks. Finally, some car stereos feature docks that ensure your mobile device is secure while you drive. If you don't want to tether your phone to your radio, you should consider a device with Bluetooth compatibility. The wireless technology can be convenient, but keep in mind that it can quickly drain your device's battery. The open road can be a quiet and lonely place, so you need a high quality stereo to listen to your favorite songs and broadcasts. You spend a long time in your car and should enjoy yourself while driving. WARNING: Products with exposed solder may contain lead, a chemical known to the State of California to cause cancer, birth defects and other reproductive harm. Please wash hands after handling internal components and motherboards and avoid inhalation of fumes if heating the solder.", "parent_text": "Car Electronics", "keyword_density": {"car": "0.9", "stereo": "1.4", "car stereo": "1.1"}, "department_id": 10},
{"department_text": "Automotive", "nr_products": 1055, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/GPS-Navigation/SubCategory/ID-357", "text": "GPS Navigation", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Store/Promotion.aspx?storeid=19&name=Auto", "description_title": "GPS Receivers", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Car-Electronics/Category/ID-283?name=Car-Electronics", "keyword_count": {"gps": 9, "gps receivers": 4, "receivers": 9}, "description_wc": 272, "description_text": "Use this link for more information about GPS Navigation Systems in our Learning Center GPS (global positioning system) receivers are quickly making atlas maps obsolete. No matter where you are located or how lost you are, a GPS receiver will not only pinpoint your location but also tell you exactly where to go. When you make wrong turns, a GPS receiver will recalculate the route for you. Need a gas station? The more advanced receivers can lead you to the nearest one. Here at Newegg, we offer GPS receivers manufactured by the top companies in the industry. Our extensive collection includes receivers at a wide range of prices. Receivers also vary in terms of accuracy, display, and function. Our online catalog provides detailed specifications for all GPS receivers, which makes it easy for you to find something that meets your needs. How to Choose a GPS Receiver Almost all receivers are accurate within 15 meters, but some are even more exact. Another factor to consider is whether you need voice directions. If you frequently drive alone to new places, voice directions are desirable. While many GPS receivers have well-lit LCD displays, it can still be difficult to read while driving. You can always turn the voice off when you do not need it. If you like to measure distances or track your average speed, many GPS receivers can do this for you. And if you take long road trips that include several destinations, you may want a receiver that can store up to 50 locations. As you can see, there are many things you can do with a global positioning system.", "parent_text": "Car Electronics", "keyword_density": {"gps receivers": "2.9", "receivers": "3.3", "gps": "3.3"}, "department_id": 10},
