{"nr_products": 666, "level": 0, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Product/ProductList.aspx?Submit=ENE&N=600158674&QksAutoSuggestion=&ShowDeactivatedMark=False&Configurator=&IsNodeId=1&name=Tablet-Accessories", "text": "Tablet Accessories", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "parent_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "department_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "department_id": 2},
{"department_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "level": 0, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26?name=Ultrabook-Accessories", "text": "Ultrabook Accessories", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "description_title": "Laptop Accessories", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "keyword_count": {"laptop accessories": 3, "laptop": 14}, "description_wc": 378, "description_text": "It seems like everyone has a laptop these days. While tablets may be lighter, depending on the specific make and model, almost no device can match the functionality and convenience of a portable computer. Buying the right laptop accessories could create an even better user experience by making devices safer and supplementing the hardware. One of a laptop's biggest conveniences is its portability, but it can be awkward to carry in hand and doing so increases the odds of an accident - like being dropped on the sidewalk. A padded backpack can carry a laptop of any size while protecting the device from the elements. Laptop bags and cases are designed to absorb most bumps and bruises, so any valuables stored inside are less likely to be damaged during transit. You might also want to protect your laptop from potential thieves. Putting a lock on a computer would make it difficult for anyone to just walk away with it. Many laptops come with a security slot, so you might want to take advantage of it for additional security measures. Heavier users may find it difficult to find a device that can meet all their demands. A laptop battery can lose power quickly when the machine is asked to handle too many tasks at once. Sometimes there might not be an available outlet, so a power adapter is necessary to provide the extra juice needed to finish an important project before the charge dies. Additionally, most batteries last longer if a laptop does not overheat. Unfortunately, it's easy for a system's internal fan to be obstructed because they are mostly located on the bottom. A cooling pad could supplement a laptop's fans and prevent damage caused by excessive heat. Most of these devices connect via a USB port but have additional outlets so users can still connect flash drives with their computer while the cooling pad is working. Newegg is proud to offer a variety of laptop accessories, including laptop batteries, AC adapters, extended warranties, add-on cards, laptop bags and cases, hard drives, memory, networking devices, luggage & bags, replicators, docking stations and solid state disks. Find the laptop accessories you\u2019re looking for while enjoying the smoothest, most pleasurable online shopping experience available at Newegg.com.", "parent_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "keyword_density": {"laptop accessories": "1.6", "laptop": "3.7"}, "department_id": 2},
{"level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Product/ProductList.aspx?Submit=ENE&IsNodeId=1&bop=And&PMSub=380%2014&PMSubCP=0&SrchInDesc=hybrid&Page=1&name=Hybrid-Hard-Drives", "text": "Hybrid Hard Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/SSDs/Category/ID-119", "parent_text": "SSDs", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 672, "level": 0, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Headsets-Accessories/SubCategory/ID-707", "text": "Headsets & Accessories", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Headsets", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "keyword_count": {"headsets": 4}, "description_wc": 287, "description_text": "Gamers see their hobby as serious business, so having the right tools to maximize playtime is essential. Nobody wants to mess around with desk microphones with unnecessary feedback or large computer speakers that garble in-game music and distort what other players are saying. Serious gaming requires serious headsets, and finding one that works best for you is what raises your in-game performance. Like standard pairs of headphones , headsets have a variety of styles and sizes. Some have bands that go over the top of the head, others wrap behind and still others do away with bands altogether and clip to ears to avoid stressing the temples. A wireless set may be more up a gamer's alley, as these relieve the exasperation a tethered headset can provide. The real added benefit of a headset comes from the onboard microphone, a feature that not all headsets provide but one that's worth looking for. This function gives you the ability to talk and listen without getting excessive feedback from keyboard or electronic activity, as well as reducing the amount of interference on your end so that other people in your conversation can hear you more easily. As any gamer knows, a successful raid relies partly on good communication, so it's essential that everyone in the party knows who you're dotting before someone kites the group. Headsets come in a variety of colors and styles, and picking the right one with the best additional features will depend on your preferences. Noise reducing, wireless or wired, with a slew of different wearing options and the ability to talk more easily while hammering on your keyboard, a headset is an integral part of successful online communication.", "parent_text": "PCs & Laptops", "keyword_density": {"headsets": "1.4"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "level": 0, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks/Category/ID-259", "text": "Ultrabooks", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "description_title": "What is an Ultrabook?", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "keyword_count": {"ultrabook": 12}, "description_wc": 360, "description_text": "The Ultrabook concept, spearheaded by Intel, is essentially the next step in the evolution of netbooks. A netbooks is a small, lightweight laptop that has been created with portability in mind. An Ultrabook improves upon the netbook by giving users a more complete computing experience. These slim pieces of machinery also come packed with high-powered features, so you don\u2019t have to sacrifice performance for portability and style. Next-generation ultrabooks To actually qualify as an Ultrabook, a PC must meet certain Intel quality standards for speed and processing power. In addition to being lightweight like its netbook predecessor, an Ultrabook must be thin. Most weigh less than three pounds and are under an inch thick when closed. Also, the high-definition resolution of an Ultrabook is superior to most monitors available today. The everlasting battery A short charge is the bane of every laptop user's existence. To combat poor performance and running time, Intel requires ultrabooks to feature at least five hours of battery life. An all-day battery would be a dream come true for most consumers. Currently, the best ultrabooks offer about eight hours of battery life, which would be particularly convenient for users who can't constantly recharge their devices. For instance, college students and traveling businesspeople won't have to worry about their laptops if Intel keeps its promise. Touchscreen may be the future Ultrabooks and tablets are strong competitors among the tech industry mainly because the devices share a great deal of similarities. Both machines are convenient for mobile use and allow users to complete basic tasks. The biggest difference between tablets and ultrabooks is their software. Tablets run on mobile operating systems like Android and iOS, while ultrabooks feature Windows 7. With Windows 8 , however, the gap between the gadgets might close completely. The next-generation of ultrabooks will look completely different from today's computers. Technological innovations and increased performance standards will force manufacturers to build high-quality laptops. If computers with all-day battery life, touchscreen capabilities and 1080p resolution become the standard, then it's difficult to imagine that there are further improvements that manufacturers could make.", "parent_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "keyword_density": {"ultrabook": "3.3"}, "department_id": 2},
{"department_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "nr_products": 101, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Mac-Hard-Drives/SubCategory/ID-552", "text": "Mac Hard Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "description_title": "External Hard Drives for Macs", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/External-Hard-Drives/Category/ID-344", "keyword_count": {"external hard": 2, "hard": 6, "drives": 2, "external": 3}, "description_wc": 313, "description_text": "Mac users need to sync an external hard drive with their computer to use Time Machine, Apple's built-in file backup system. Shoppers can find and choose the right Mac hard drive by thinking about storage and portability needs. To figure out what size hard drive you should buy, think about how much computing you do each day and how many files you save. If you're a heavy user, consider buying a drive with terabytes (TB) of available storage. You'll be able to save an entire system to a device with that much room, so if you need a new computer, you will be able to reinstall everything as it was previously. These units are beneficial to people who work in creative industries and have libraries that are too expansive for a single Mac external hard drive. For example, a photographer who has hundreds of thousands of pictures saved on his or her desktop won't be able to back everything up with a smaller unit. Casual consumers should consider drives with a few hundred gigabytes (GB) of space. Buying a device with TBs of data storage would result in a great deal of wasted space for users who only have a couple thousand files that need to be saved. If you plan on bringing your external Mac hard drive everywhere you go, you'll want to purchase a unit that is light and damage-resistant. Some drives are smaller than most tablets, while other devices are large enough to be confused with video game consoles. If you're prone to damaging your gadgets, consider a drive with pads and shock protectors to defend against significant bumps and bruises. Time Machine is a convenient program to help ensure that every file is saved, and buying the right Mac hard drive can help Mac users make the most of the program.", "parent_text": "External Hard Drives", "keyword_density": {"external hard": "1.3", "hard": "1.9", "drives": "0.6", "external": "1.0"}, "department_id": 2},
