{"department_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Projectors/Category/ID-343", "text": "Projectors", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "description_title": "Business Projectors", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks/Category/ID-259", "keyword_count": {"business": 2, "projectors": 5, "business projectors": 1}, "description_wc": 136, "description_text": "Use this link for more on Business Projectors in our Learning Center Newegg.com offers a rich selection of projectors using LCD or DLP and from mainstream to professional.We carry projectors from Epson, InFocus, Mitsubishi, Sony, NEC and others. These days, projectors come in a wide range of resolutions and luminosities, for small offices or large lecture halls! Home and business users alike will be able to find projectors that fit and function perfectly both for the office and the home and enjoy maximum visual quality and impact as well as enhanced work efficiency. WARNING: Products with exposed solder may contain lead, a chemical known to the State of California to cause cancer, birth defects and other reproductive harm. Please wash hands after handling internal components and motherboards and avoid inhalation of fumes if heating the solder.", "parent_text": "Ultrabooks", "keyword_density": {"business projectors": "1.5", "projectors": "3.7", "business": "1.5"}, "department_id": 2},
{"department_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "nr_products": 558, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/All-External-Hard-Drives/SubCategory/ID-414", "text": "All External Hard Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "description_title": "External Hard Drives", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks/Category/ID-259", "keyword_count": {"external hard": 8, "external hard drives": 5, "hard": 13, "drives": 6, "external": 11}, "description_wc": 398, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on External Hard Drives in our Learning Center External hard drives are ideal for backing up your hard drive or storing additional media separately from your main hard drive. Photos, videos, and digital music have all become so popular in recent years that people need a place to put it all. CDs and DVDs do not have the capacity to hold PC backups and are not all that convenient. However, the prices of external hard drives have come down so much that they are perfect for backing up your important data. The two most common interfaces for hooking up external drives to your computer are USB and FireWire with eSata now becoming popular also. USB has been around for years and are standard on just about all computers today while FireWire ports are newer and if you use a digital video camera with your computer you probably already have one. In terms of access speeds the latest eSata standard offers the fastest connection however that comes with a price. USB 2.0 and Firewire can cover most of your general needs without having to upgrade your system with a new eSata card. Any of the interfaces will do the job however be sure to purchase an external hard drive with the same type of port that your computer has. Your backup drive should have a capacity at least as big as your computer's largest hard drive. That will leave you with plenty of room to back up your important files or mirror/clone your current drive. You can also buy an external hard drive case and mount an internal hard drive inside it. This method will give you a choice of brands and models, and if anything goes wrong with your internal hard drive, you can simply install the external one inside your computer to replace it. Considerations for External Hard Drives One drawback to using external hard drives for backups is that they are still relatively new for home computer use. They come with Windows drivers; should Windows fail, you will not be able to access your external drive through DOS. There are DOS drivers available but they can be difficult to find and most manufacturers do not provide support for them. This isn't a frequent occurrence, just something to keep in mind as you select your external hard drive.", "parent_text": "Ultrabooks", "keyword_density": {"external hard": "4.0", "external hard drives": "3.8", "hard": "3.3", "drives": "1.5", "external": "2.8"}, "department_id": 2},
{"department_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26?name=Ultrabook-Accessories", "text": "Ultrabook Accessories", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "description_title": "Laptop Accessories", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks/Category/ID-259", "keyword_count": {"laptop accessories": 3, "laptop": 14}, "description_wc": 378, "description_text": "It seems like everyone has a laptop these days. While tablets may be lighter, depending on the specific make and model, almost no device can match the functionality and convenience of a portable computer. Buying the right laptop accessories could create an even better user experience by making devices safer and supplementing the hardware. One of a laptop's biggest conveniences is its portability, but it can be awkward to carry in hand and doing so increases the odds of an accident - like being dropped on the sidewalk. A padded backpack can carry a laptop of any size while protecting the device from the elements. Laptop bags and cases are designed to absorb most bumps and bruises, so any valuables stored inside are less likely to be damaged during transit. You might also want to protect your laptop from potential thieves. Putting a lock on a computer would make it difficult for anyone to just walk away with it. Many laptops come with a security slot, so you might want to take advantage of it for additional security measures. Heavier users may find it difficult to find a device that can meet all their demands. A laptop battery can lose power quickly when the machine is asked to handle too many tasks at once. Sometimes there might not be an available outlet, so a power adapter is necessary to provide the extra juice needed to finish an important project before the charge dies. Additionally, most batteries last longer if a laptop does not overheat. Unfortunately, it's easy for a system's internal fan to be obstructed because they are mostly located on the bottom. A cooling pad could supplement a laptop's fans and prevent damage caused by excessive heat. Most of these devices connect via a USB port but have additional outlets so users can still connect flash drives with their computer while the cooling pad is working. Newegg is proud to offer a variety of laptop accessories, including laptop batteries, AC adapters, extended warranties, add-on cards, laptop bags and cases, hard drives, memory, networking devices, luggage & bags, replicators, docking stations and solid state disks. Find the laptop accessories you\u2019re looking for while enjoying the smoothest, most pleasurable online shopping experience available at Newegg.com.", "parent_text": "Ultrabooks", "keyword_density": {"laptop accessories": "1.6", "laptop": "3.7"}, "department_id": 2},
{"department_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "nr_products": 151, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Replicators-Docking-Stations/SubCategory/ID-537", "text": "Replicators / Docking Stations", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "description_title": "Laptop Docking Stations", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26?name=Ultrabook-Accessories", "keyword_count": {"laptop docking stations": 1, "laptop": 7, "docking": 3, "docking stations": 2, "stations": 3}, "description_wc": 288, "description_text": "Laptops and tablets have become popular options for shoppers who want to bring their computers everywhere. Manufacturers have begun producing slimmer models of both devices at the expense of some features that users may need, like ethernet jacks or HDMI ports. For those who have replaced their desktop with a laptop or tablet, this lack of hardware support can be a problem. Attaching a device to a port replicator is a solution for those who need the extra outlets and hardware support. Port replicators connect to a laptop or tablet via the battery hook-up, so the peripheral acts as a base for the device. Some tablet stations include an external keyboard for consumers who don't like typing on the screen, while others may need extra USB slots to connect with other accessories. Many ultrabooks don't have a CD drive, but some laptop docking stations have disc readers if you need to access content from CDs and DVDs. Other models offer ethernet connections, USB ports and audio jacks but lack a disc reader. You can pick and choose which features you need to supplement your laptop's functionality. Port replicators can be quickly disconnected so a device is never tethered to a desk. Users can connect all peripheral devices, like external hard drives and printers, to a base so instead of unplugging multiple accessories only the docking station needs to be removed from a tablet or laptop. This convenient accessory is great for workers who bring their mobile computers to work each day. A slim device doesn't have to lack the functionality found in desktops and heavier machines. Docking stations provide users with all the features missing from their laptops and tablets without sacrificing mobility.", "parent_text": "Ultrabook Accessories", "keyword_density": {"laptop docking stations": "1.0", "laptop": "2.4", "docking": "1.0", "docking stations": "1.4", "stations": "1.0"}, "department_id": 2},
