{"department_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "nr_products": 15, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Networking/SubCategory/ID-34", "text": "Laptop Networking", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "description_title": "Laptop Wireless Cards", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26?name=Ultrabook-Accessories", "keyword_count": {"wireless": 7, "cards": 4, "laptop": 6, "wireless cards": 2, "laptop wireless cards": 1}, "description_wc": 313, "description_text": "Wi-Fi connectivity makes a laptop even more useful to its owner. Most people use their computers as gateways to the internet, so it can be frustrating if they can't go online because they can't find an ethernet cable. Consumers can buy wireless cards for laptops so their devices can connect with a signal from anywhere. These cards need to be installed to a computer's motherboard to use a wireless signal. Many of the available models come with tutorials and instruction guides, so even shoppers who aren't tech-savvy can easily install their new purchase. Laptop wireless cards act as internal receivers, allowing a computer to connect to the internet over the air without an ethernet cord. Users who are on the go need this added convenience so their devices can be fully functional anywhere there's a wireless signal. For example, college students can install a card so their laptops work in class and in the library - not just in their dorm rooms or apartments. A laptop must be within a certain proximity to a Wi-Fi router to receive the signal, as the card itself does not generate web connectivity. Fortunately, many establishments, ranging from coffee shops to public libraries, provide wireless web access, so everyone can find a place to go online. For users who want to add an ethernet connection to their notebook, there are cards with jacks for cords. Manufacturers have begun producing slim laptops that remove ethernet ports to reduce the devices' overall weight. Much like a wireless card, these units are installed internally but have an external attachment intended for a wired connection. You should make sure the wireless card you're thinking about purchasing matches your computer's hardware specifications. Access points must have driver support to function properly, so be sure to check what your system is capable of supporting.", "parent_text": "Ultrabook Accessories", "keyword_density": {"wireless": "2.2", "cards": "1.3", "laptop": "1.9", "wireless cards": "1.3", "laptop wireless cards": "1.0"}, "department_id": 2},
{"nr_products": 56, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Luggages-Bags/SubCategory/ID-483", "text": "Luggages & Bags", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26?name=Ultrabook-Accessories", "parent_text": "Ultrabook Accessories", "department_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "department_id": 2},
{"department_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "nr_products": 4989, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Cases-Bags/SubCategory/ID-482", "text": "Laptop Cases & Bags", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "description_title": "Laptop Cases and Bags", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26?name=Ultrabook-Accessories", "keyword_count": {"laptop": 9, "laptop cases": 4}, "description_wc": 273, "description_text": "Laptop cases are essential for students and professionals who need to be able to take their work everywhere. Because of the fragile nature of laptop PCs, a regular bag or backpack just won\u2019t cut it - you need to protect your valuable documents and media. Not only do laptop cases protect the exterior in the event of a bump or fall, but they offer added cushioning that ensures the sensitive interior hardware stays intact as well. At Newegg you\u2019ll find affordable, stylish options perfect for any professional. Need a way to tote your work while still looking sharp? Consider a laptop briefcase or over-the-shoulder messenger case. Our professional models are both rugged and stylish. Most include several lockable zipper compartments to store your office supplies, and feature ergonomic handles and/or and adjustable shoulder straps for maximum versatility. Those who travel frequently can find models that feature trolley straps, to ensure the case stays in place when stored on top of a rolling suitcase. Students may be more interested in a backpack laptop case, which are suitable for larger laptops and offer ample storage space for textbooks, notebooks and other supplies. Backpack laptop cases are easy to carry around campus, and many models offer lifetime warranties, so you know they\u2019ll be able to keep up with your busy lifestyle. If you don\u2019t travel much and need something a little simpler, consider a notebook sleeve. These items offer all the protection you need without the frills. A laptop is more than just a computer - it\u2019s an investment. Protect yours with one of our many specially designed laptop cases.", "parent_text": "Ultrabook Accessories", "keyword_density": {"laptop": "3.3", "laptop cases": "2.9"}, "department_id": 2},
