{"department_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "nr_products": 1950, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Mice/SubCategory/ID-65", "text": "Mice", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "description_title": "Wireless Mice, Optical Mice, Laser Mice and Trackball Mice", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26?name=Ultrabook-Accessories", "keyword_count": {"wireless": 4, "mice": 3}, "description_wc": 113, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Computer Mice in our Learning Center At Newegg you can choose from a massive selection of computer mice from industry leading manufacturers including wired and wireless products, as well as sleek space-saving designs for notebook computers and ergonomic mice for the utmost in user comfort and gaming performance regardless of hand-orientation. Brands featured at Newegg include Microsoft, Kensington, Logitech, Targus and others in configurations of RF wireless, Fast RF wireless, Bluetooth Wireless, and standard PS/2 and USB wired interfaces. With a mouse to fit every computer performance need Newegg has what you need. For more information, please see our Computer Mouse Buying Guide.", "parent_text": "Ultrabook Accessories", "keyword_density": {"wireless": "3.5", "mice": "2.7"}, "department_id": 2},
{"department_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "nr_products": 151, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Replicators-Docking-Stations/SubCategory/ID-537", "text": "Replicators / Docking Stations", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "description_title": "Laptop Docking Stations", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26?name=Ultrabook-Accessories", "keyword_count": {"laptop docking stations": 1, "laptop": 7, "docking": 3, "docking stations": 2, "stations": 3}, "description_wc": 288, "description_text": "Laptops and tablets have become popular options for shoppers who want to bring their computers everywhere. Manufacturers have begun producing slimmer models of both devices at the expense of some features that users may need, like ethernet jacks or HDMI ports. For those who have replaced their desktop with a laptop or tablet, this lack of hardware support can be a problem. Attaching a device to a port replicator is a solution for those who need the extra outlets and hardware support. Port replicators connect to a laptop or tablet via the battery hook-up, so the peripheral acts as a base for the device. Some tablet stations include an external keyboard for consumers who don't like typing on the screen, while others may need extra USB slots to connect with other accessories. Many ultrabooks don't have a CD drive, but some laptop docking stations have disc readers if you need to access content from CDs and DVDs. Other models offer ethernet connections, USB ports and audio jacks but lack a disc reader. You can pick and choose which features you need to supplement your laptop's functionality. Port replicators can be quickly disconnected so a device is never tethered to a desk. Users can connect all peripheral devices, like external hard drives and printers, to a base so instead of unplugging multiple accessories only the docking station needs to be removed from a tablet or laptop. This convenient accessory is great for workers who bring their mobile computers to work each day. A slim device doesn't have to lack the functionality found in desktops and heavier machines. Docking stations provide users with all the features missing from their laptops and tablets without sacrificing mobility.", "parent_text": "Ultrabook Accessories", "keyword_density": {"laptop docking stations": "1.0", "laptop": "2.4", "docking": "1.0", "docking stations": "1.4", "stations": "1.0"}, "department_id": 2},
{"department_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "nr_products": 15, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Networking/SubCategory/ID-34", "text": "Laptop Networking", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "description_title": "Laptop Wireless Cards", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26?name=Ultrabook-Accessories", "keyword_count": {"wireless": 7, "cards": 4, "laptop": 6, "wireless cards": 2, "laptop wireless cards": 1}, "description_wc": 313, "description_text": "Wi-Fi connectivity makes a laptop even more useful to its owner. Most people use their computers as gateways to the internet, so it can be frustrating if they can't go online because they can't find an ethernet cable. Consumers can buy wireless cards for laptops so their devices can connect with a signal from anywhere. These cards need to be installed to a computer's motherboard to use a wireless signal. Many of the available models come with tutorials and instruction guides, so even shoppers who aren't tech-savvy can easily install their new purchase. Laptop wireless cards act as internal receivers, allowing a computer to connect to the internet over the air without an ethernet cord. Users who are on the go need this added convenience so their devices can be fully functional anywhere there's a wireless signal. For example, college students can install a card so their laptops work in class and in the library - not just in their dorm rooms or apartments. A laptop must be within a certain proximity to a Wi-Fi router to receive the signal, as the card itself does not generate web connectivity. Fortunately, many establishments, ranging from coffee shops to public libraries, provide wireless web access, so everyone can find a place to go online. For users who want to add an ethernet connection to their notebook, there are cards with jacks for cords. Manufacturers have begun producing slim laptops that remove ethernet ports to reduce the devices' overall weight. Much like a wireless card, these units are installed internally but have an external attachment intended for a wired connection. You should make sure the wireless card you're thinking about purchasing matches your computer's hardware specifications. Access points must have driver support to function properly, so be sure to check what your system is capable of supporting.", "parent_text": "Ultrabook Accessories", "keyword_density": {"wireless": "2.2", "cards": "1.3", "laptop": "1.9", "wireless cards": "1.3", "laptop wireless cards": "1.0"}, "department_id": 2},
{"department_text": "Ultrabooks & Tablets", "nr_products": 483, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Memory/SubCategory/ID-381", "text": "Laptop Memory", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks-Tablets/Store/ID-125", "description_title": "Laptop / Notebook Memory", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26?name=Ultrabook-Accessories", "keyword_count": {"laptop notebook": 1, "notebook": 2, "notebook memory": 1, "memory": 7}, "description_wc": 196, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Notebook Memory in our Learning Center Prefer to run your computer with fewer restrictions? You can do this and run more programs simultaneously by adding more memory to your system. The memory referred to here is RAM (Random Access Memory), which is essentially the computer's workspace - the place where your computer temporarily stores data and programs. Memory performance is an important factor influencing total system performance as memory speed allows more data to be transferred in a given time for greater system response and performance in demanding applications and games. With prices for memory falling there is no better time to stock up and at Newegg you can select from a wide assortment of speeds and capacity. Whether it's 125MB, 256MB, 512MB, 1GB or 2GB in capacity or speeds covering PC 100, PC 133, DDR 266 (PC 2100), DDR 333 (PC 2700), DDR 400 (PC 3200), DDR2 400 (PC2 3200), DDR2 533 (PC2 4200), DDR2 667 (PC2 5300), DDR2 667 (PC2 5400), DDR2 800 (PC2 6400) and more we have the right solution for your laptop / notebook upgrade needs.", "parent_text": "Ultrabook Accessories", "keyword_density": {"laptop notebook": "1.1", "notebook": "1.1", "notebook memory": "1.1", "memory": "3.7"}, "department_id": 2},
