{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "level": 0, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Tablets/Category/ID-164", "text": "Tablets", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Tablets and Accessories", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "keyword_count": {"tablets": 5, "accessories": 4}, "description_wc": 283, "description_text": "Tablets combine the computing power of laptops with the mobility of smartphones, and the gadgets are lightweight and convenient. There are two operating systems - Windows 8 RT and Android - that make tablets even more functional by increasing processor speed and available options. Android tablets are consumer favorites because the software is very similar to the programs used on most smartphones. Users can add apps, games and features with only a couple of taps and gestures. Many people enjoy the familiarity and intuitive-nature of Android. You should always consider your options and find the device that is most suited for your needs. Windows 8 tablets are relatively new, but the devices combine popular features from Microsoft's operating system series with a mobile operating system. The tiled interface bears similarities to the Windows Phone, but it is more customizable and has a wider range of apps. Once you pick the perfect tablet, you'll need the right accessories. Detachable keyboards are a necessity if you want your mobile device to replace your laptop for all of your computing needs. The peripherals are very important if you buy a Windows 8 tablet so you can easily type in programs like Microsoft Word and Excel. Screen covers are among the most important tablet accessories. Tablets have large displays that are susceptible to scratches and scuff marks. You can either buy a plastic cover that blocks out dust or a protective sleeve that also saves prevents the bezel from damage. Some covers also feature keyboards so you can have two accessories in half the space. Accessories can make your tablet even more functional and help you replace your laptop or PC with a convenient mobile device.", "parent_text": "PCs & Laptops", "keyword_density": {"tablets": "1.8", "accessories": "1.4"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "level": 0, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "text": "Laptop Accessories", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop Accessories", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "keyword_count": {"laptop accessories": 3, "laptop": 14}, "description_wc": 378, "description_text": "It seems like everyone has a laptop these days. While tablets may be lighter, depending on the specific make and model, almost no device can match the functionality and convenience of a portable computer. Buying the right laptop accessories could create an even better user experience by making devices safer and supplementing the hardware. One of a laptop's biggest conveniences is its portability, but it can be awkward to carry in hand and doing so increases the odds of an accident - like being dropped on the sidewalk. A padded backpack can carry a laptop of any size while protecting the device from the elements. Laptop bags and cases are designed to absorb most bumps and bruises, so any valuables stored inside are less likely to be damaged during transit. You might also want to protect your laptop from potential thieves. Putting a lock on a computer would make it difficult for anyone to just walk away with it. Many laptops come with a security slot, so you might want to take advantage of it for additional security measures. Heavier users may find it difficult to find a device that can meet all their demands. A laptop battery can lose power quickly when the machine is asked to handle too many tasks at once. Sometimes there might not be an available outlet, so a power adapter is necessary to provide the extra juice needed to finish an important project before the charge dies. Additionally, most batteries last longer if a laptop does not overheat. Unfortunately, it's easy for a system's internal fan to be obstructed because they are mostly located on the bottom. A cooling pad could supplement a laptop's fans and prevent damage caused by excessive heat. Most of these devices connect via a USB port but have additional outlets so users can still connect flash drives with their computer while the cooling pad is working. Newegg is proud to offer a variety of laptop accessories, including laptop batteries, AC adapters, extended warranties, add-on cards, laptop bags and cases, hard drives, memory, networking devices, luggage & bags, replicators, docking stations and solid state disks. Find the laptop accessories you\u2019re looking for while enjoying the smoothest, most pleasurable online shopping experience available at Newegg.com.", "parent_text": "PCs & Laptops", "keyword_density": {"laptop accessories": "1.6", "laptop": "3.7"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "level": 0, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks/Category/ID-259", "text": "Ultrabooks", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "What is an Ultrabook?", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "keyword_count": {"ultrabook": 12}, "description_wc": 360, "description_text": "The Ultrabook concept, spearheaded by Intel, is essentially the next step in the evolution of netbooks. A netbooks is a small, lightweight laptop that has been created with portability in mind. An Ultrabook improves upon the netbook by giving users a more complete computing experience. These slim pieces of machinery also come packed with high-powered features, so you don\u2019t have to sacrifice performance for portability and style. Next-generation ultrabooks To actually qualify as an Ultrabook, a PC must meet certain Intel quality standards for speed and processing power. In addition to being lightweight like its netbook predecessor, an Ultrabook must be thin. Most weigh less than three pounds and are under an inch thick when closed. Also, the high-definition resolution of an Ultrabook is superior to most monitors available today. The everlasting battery A short charge is the bane of every laptop user's existence. To combat poor performance and running time, Intel requires ultrabooks to feature at least five hours of battery life. An all-day battery would be a dream come true for most consumers. Currently, the best ultrabooks offer about eight hours of battery life, which would be particularly convenient for users who can't constantly recharge their devices. For instance, college students and traveling businesspeople won't have to worry about their laptops if Intel keeps its promise. Touchscreen may be the future Ultrabooks and tablets are strong competitors among the tech industry mainly because the devices share a great deal of similarities. Both machines are convenient for mobile use and allow users to complete basic tasks. The biggest difference between tablets and ultrabooks is their software. Tablets run on mobile operating systems like Android and iOS, while ultrabooks feature Windows 7. With Windows 8 , however, the gap between the gadgets might close completely. The next-generation of ultrabooks will look completely different from today's computers. Technological innovations and increased performance standards will force manufacturers to build high-quality laptops. If computers with all-day battery life, touchscreen capabilities and 1080p resolution become the standard, then it's difficult to imagine that there are further improvements that manufacturers could make.", "parent_text": "PCs & Laptops", "keyword_density": {"ultrabook": "3.3"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "level": 0, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptops-Notebooks/Category/ID-223", "text": "Laptops / Notebooks", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Big Changes in Laptops 2013", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "keyword_count": {"laptops": 6, "changes": 1, "2013": 2}, "description_wc": 276, "description_text": "The distinction between laptops and ultrabooks can be somewhat confusing. As a matter of fact, Intel created guidelines for ultrabooks in 2011, which stipulate that the machines must be below a certain weight limit, meet performance standards, and cost less than $1000. Traditional notebooks , on the other hand, are more unique than their slim counterparts because companies don't have to adhere to the universal code. The devices offer high-quality performance and strong computing power. Additionally, laptops feature important components like optical drives that ultrabooks often lack. Manufacturers aren't resting on their laurels when it comes to laptops. In 2013, consumers can expect to see some groundbreaking hardware that may change the face mobile computing. Windows 8 Changes Everything Windows 8 , the new operating system from Microsoft, has been gaining popular appeal with its customizable Live Tiles interface, flexible hardware options, faster boot time, SkyDrive integration, and much more. In 2013, most laptops will run on Microsoft's latest operating systems. Future Plans from Intel In addition to Microsoft\u2019s Windows 8 operating system, Intel has some new plans in store for laptops as well. A primary goal for Intel would be to improve the battery life of every laptop with its new processors. Mashable writes that Haswell will consume less than 7 watts of power, which will increase battery life to over 17 hours of continuous use. The company has even higher hopes for ultrabooks and promises all-day battery life for slim notebooks. Consumers will see some amazing new laptops hit the market in the coming months. Groundbreaking innovations from companies like Microsoft and Intel will change consumer electronics forever.", "parent_text": "PCs & Laptops", "keyword_density": {"laptops": "2.2", "changes": "0.4", "2013": "0.7"}, "department_id": 3},
