{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Input-Devices/Category/ID-29", "text": "Input Devices", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Input Device", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Desktop-PCs/Category/ID-228", "keyword_count": {"input device": 2}, "description_wc": 90, "description_text": "Input Devices include Keyboard, Mouse, Microphone, Headset, Hub, KVM Switch, Game Controller, Tablet Input Device and Webcam. Newegg has these products from world\u2019s best manufacturers including Microsoft, Logitech, Saitek, Creative Labs, Kensington, Rosewill, BTC, Belkin, Bytecc, Macally, ideazon, Gyration, RAZER, Targus, Fellowes and Tripp Lite, etc. WARNING: Products with exposed solder may contain lead, a chemical known to the State of California to cause cancer, birth defects and other reproductive harm. Please wash hands after handling internal components and motherboards and avoid inhalation of fumes if heating the solder.", "parent_text": "Desktop PCs", "keyword_density": {"input device": "4.4"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 1950, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Mice/SubCategory/ID-65", "text": "Mice", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Wireless Mice, Optical Mice, Laser Mice and Trackball Mice", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "keyword_count": {"wireless": 4, "mice": 3}, "description_wc": 113, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Computer Mice in our Learning Center At Newegg you can choose from a massive selection of computer mice from industry leading manufacturers including wired and wireless products, as well as sleek space-saving designs for notebook computers and ergonomic mice for the utmost in user comfort and gaming performance regardless of hand-orientation. Brands featured at Newegg include Microsoft, Kensington, Logitech, Targus and others in configurations of RF wireless, Fast RF wireless, Bluetooth Wireless, and standard PS/2 and USB wired interfaces. With a mouse to fit every computer performance need Newegg has what you need. For more information, please see our Computer Mouse Buying Guide.", "parent_text": "Laptop Accessories", "keyword_density": {"wireless": "3.5", "mice": "2.7"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 101, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Mac-Hard-Drives/SubCategory/ID-552", "text": "Mac Hard Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "External Hard Drives for Macs", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/External-Hard-Drives/Category/ID-344?name=External-Hard-Drives", "keyword_count": {"external hard": 2, "hard": 6, "drives": 2, "external": 3}, "description_wc": 313, "description_text": "Mac users need to sync an external hard drive with their computer to use Time Machine, Apple's built-in file backup system. Shoppers can find and choose the right Mac hard drive by thinking about storage and portability needs. To figure out what size hard drive you should buy, think about how much computing you do each day and how many files you save. If you're a heavy user, consider buying a drive with terabytes (TB) of available storage. You'll be able to save an entire system to a device with that much room, so if you need a new computer, you will be able to reinstall everything as it was previously. These units are beneficial to people who work in creative industries and have libraries that are too expansive for a single Mac external hard drive. For example, a photographer who has hundreds of thousands of pictures saved on his or her desktop won't be able to back everything up with a smaller unit. Casual consumers should consider drives with a few hundred gigabytes (GB) of space. Buying a device with TBs of data storage would result in a great deal of wasted space for users who only have a couple thousand files that need to be saved. If you plan on bringing your external Mac hard drive everywhere you go, you'll want to purchase a unit that is light and damage-resistant. Some drives are smaller than most tablets, while other devices are large enough to be confused with video game consoles. If you're prone to damaging your gadgets, consider a drive with pads and shock protectors to defend against significant bumps and bruises. Time Machine is a convenient program to help ensure that every file is saved, and buying the right Mac hard drive can help Mac users make the most of the program.", "parent_text": "External Hard Drives", "keyword_density": {"external hard": "1.3", "hard": "1.9", "drives": "0.6", "external": "1.0"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "text": "Laptop Accessories", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop Accessories", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Chromebooks/Category/ID-269", "keyword_count": {"laptop accessories": 3, "laptop": 14}, "description_wc": 378, "description_text": "It seems like everyone has a laptop these days. While tablets may be lighter, depending on the specific make and model, almost no device can match the functionality and convenience of a portable computer. Buying the right laptop accessories could create an even better user experience by making devices safer and supplementing the hardware. One of a laptop's biggest conveniences is its portability, but it can be awkward to carry in hand and doing so increases the odds of an accident - like being dropped on the sidewalk. A padded backpack can carry a laptop of any size while protecting the device from the elements. Laptop bags and cases are designed to absorb most bumps and bruises, so any valuables stored inside are less likely to be damaged during transit. You might also want to protect your laptop from potential thieves. Putting a lock on a computer would make it difficult for anyone to just walk away with it. Many laptops come with a security slot, so you might want to take advantage of it for additional security measures. Heavier users may find it difficult to find a device that can meet all their demands. A laptop battery can lose power quickly when the machine is asked to handle too many tasks at once. Sometimes there might not be an available outlet, so a power adapter is necessary to provide the extra juice needed to finish an important project before the charge dies. Additionally, most batteries last longer if a laptop does not overheat. Unfortunately, it's easy for a system's internal fan to be obstructed because they are mostly located on the bottom. A cooling pad could supplement a laptop's fans and prevent damage caused by excessive heat. Most of these devices connect via a USB port but have additional outlets so users can still connect flash drives with their computer while the cooling pad is working. Newegg is proud to offer a variety of laptop accessories, including laptop batteries, AC adapters, extended warranties, add-on cards, laptop bags and cases, hard drives, memory, networking devices, luggage & bags, replicators, docking stations and solid state disks. Find the laptop accessories you\u2019re looking for while enjoying the smoothest, most pleasurable online shopping experience available at Newegg.com.", "parent_text": "Chromebooks", "keyword_density": {"laptop accessories": "1.6", "laptop": "3.7"}, "department_id": 3},
{"nr_products": 163, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Product/ProductList.aspx?Submit=ENE&N=100022991&IsNodeId=1&bop=And&ActiveSearchResult=True&SrchInDesc=portable&Page=1&PageSize=20&cm_sp=External344-_-VisNav-_-PortableExternal&name=Portable-Hard-Drives", "text": "Portable Hard Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/External-Hard-Drives/Category/ID-344?name=External-Hard-Drives", "parent_text": "External Hard Drives", "department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 151, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Replicators-Docking-Stations/SubCategory/ID-537", "text": "Replicators / Docking Stations", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop Docking Stations", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "keyword_count": {"laptop docking stations": 1, "laptop": 7, "docking": 3, "docking stations": 2, "stations": 3}, "description_wc": 288, "description_text": "Laptops and tablets have become popular options for shoppers who want to bring their computers everywhere. Manufacturers have begun producing slimmer models of both devices at the expense of some features that users may need, like ethernet jacks or HDMI ports. For those who have replaced their desktop with a laptop or tablet, this lack of hardware support can be a problem. Attaching a device to a port replicator is a solution for those who need the extra outlets and hardware support. Port replicators connect to a laptop or tablet via the battery hook-up, so the peripheral acts as a base for the device. Some tablet stations include an external keyboard for consumers who don't like typing on the screen, while others may need extra USB slots to connect with other accessories. Many ultrabooks don't have a CD drive, but some laptop docking stations have disc readers if you need to access content from CDs and DVDs. Other models offer ethernet connections, USB ports and audio jacks but lack a disc reader. You can pick and choose which features you need to supplement your laptop's functionality. Port replicators can be quickly disconnected so a device is never tethered to a desk. Users can connect all peripheral devices, like external hard drives and printers, to a base so instead of unplugging multiple accessories only the docking station needs to be removed from a tablet or laptop. This convenient accessory is great for workers who bring their mobile computers to work each day. A slim device doesn't have to lack the functionality found in desktops and heavier machines. Docking stations provide users with all the features missing from their laptops and tablets without sacrificing mobility.", "parent_text": "Laptop Accessories", "keyword_density": {"laptop docking stations": "1.0", "laptop": "2.4", "docking": "1.0", "docking stations": "1.4", "stations": "1.0"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 558, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/All-External-Hard-Drives/SubCategory/ID-414", "text": "All External Hard Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "External Hard Drives", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/External-Hard-Drives/Category/ID-344?name=External-Hard-Drives", "keyword_count": {"external hard": 8, "external hard drives": 5, "hard": 13, "drives": 6, "external": 11}, "description_wc": 398, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on External Hard Drives in our Learning Center External hard drives are ideal for backing up your hard drive or storing additional media separately from your main hard drive. Photos, videos, and digital music have all become so popular in recent years that people need a place to put it all. CDs and DVDs do not have the capacity to hold PC backups and are not all that convenient. However, the prices of external hard drives have come down so much that they are perfect for backing up your important data. The two most common interfaces for hooking up external drives to your computer are USB and FireWire with eSata now becoming popular also. USB has been around for years and are standard on just about all computers today while FireWire ports are newer and if you use a digital video camera with your computer you probably already have one. In terms of access speeds the latest eSata standard offers the fastest connection however that comes with a price. USB 2.0 and Firewire can cover most of your general needs without having to upgrade your system with a new eSata card. Any of the interfaces will do the job however be sure to purchase an external hard drive with the same type of port that your computer has. Your backup drive should have a capacity at least as big as your computer's largest hard drive. That will leave you with plenty of room to back up your important files or mirror/clone your current drive. You can also buy an external hard drive case and mount an internal hard drive inside it. This method will give you a choice of brands and models, and if anything goes wrong with your internal hard drive, you can simply install the external one inside your computer to replace it. Considerations for External Hard Drives One drawback to using external hard drives for backups is that they are still relatively new for home computer use. They come with Windows drivers; should Windows fail, you will not be able to access your external drive through DOS. There are DOS drivers available but they can be difficult to find and most manufacturers do not provide support for them. This isn't a frequent occurrence, just something to keep in mind as you select your external hard drive.", "parent_text": "External Hard Drives", "keyword_density": {"external hard": "4.0", "external hard drives": "3.8", "hard": "3.3", "drives": "1.5", "external": "2.8"}, "department_id": 3},
{"level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Printers-Scanners-Supplies/Category/ID-33", "text": "Printers / Scanners & Supplies", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Desktop-PCs/Category/ID-228", "description_wc": 43, "description_text": "WARNING: Products with exposed solder may contain lead, a chemical known to the State of California to cause cancer, birth defects and other reproductive harm. Please wash hands after handling internal components and motherboards and avoid inhalation of fumes if heating the solder.", "parent_text": "Desktop PCs", "department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 15, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Networking/SubCategory/ID-34", "text": "Laptop Networking", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop Wireless Cards", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "keyword_count": {"wireless": 7, "cards": 4, "laptop": 6, "wireless cards": 2, "laptop wireless cards": 1}, "description_wc": 313, "description_text": "Wi-Fi connectivity makes a laptop even more useful to its owner. Most people use their computers as gateways to the internet, so it can be frustrating if they can't go online because they can't find an ethernet cable. Consumers can buy wireless cards for laptops so their devices can connect with a signal from anywhere. These cards need to be installed to a computer's motherboard to use a wireless signal. Many of the available models come with tutorials and instruction guides, so even shoppers who aren't tech-savvy can easily install their new purchase. Laptop wireless cards act as internal receivers, allowing a computer to connect to the internet over the air without an ethernet cord. Users who are on the go need this added convenience so their devices can be fully functional anywhere there's a wireless signal. For example, college students can install a card so their laptops work in class and in the library - not just in their dorm rooms or apartments. A laptop must be within a certain proximity to a Wi-Fi router to receive the signal, as the card itself does not generate web connectivity. Fortunately, many establishments, ranging from coffee shops to public libraries, provide wireless web access, so everyone can find a place to go online. For users who want to add an ethernet connection to their notebook, there are cards with jacks for cords. Manufacturers have begun producing slim laptops that remove ethernet ports to reduce the devices' overall weight. Much like a wireless card, these units are installed internally but have an external attachment intended for a wired connection. You should make sure the wireless card you're thinking about purchasing matches your computer's hardware specifications. Access points must have driver support to function properly, so be sure to check what your system is capable of supporting.", "parent_text": "Laptop Accessories", "keyword_density": {"wireless": "2.2", "cards": "1.3", "laptop": "1.9", "wireless cards": "1.3", "laptop wireless cards": "1.0"}, "department_id": 3},
