{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 938, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Speakers/SubCategory/ID-60", "text": "Speakers", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Computer Speakers", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Speakers-Headsets/Category/ID-37", "keyword_count": {"speakers": 6, "computer": 6, "computer speakers": 3}, "description_wc": 311, "description_text": "It's not a given when you buy a new computer that it's going to have a sound card built in, and even if it does, there's no guarantee that it's going to be good. To get the best possible performance for streaming movies and video playback, as well as in-game audio experiences, it's essential that you get the best computer speakers to round out your machine. A standard set of side-by-side speakers will let you hear what's happening more clearly than using an onboard sound device. Without a tool like this, you may not get any audio with your playback at all, so this should be considered a basic purchase to go along with upgrading a keyboard and mouse. If you want a real experience with your media, try purchasing a heftier system. Something with a subwoofer and additional high-powered speakers can make it feel like you have a surround sound experience in your computer chair. Purchasing a speaker system also means considering how these will be connected. Some systems have USB hook-ups or other plugs and cables that won't require as many dedicated sockets, but there are expanders and other solutions to increase the maximum number of USB devices you can have going at once. Some devices will also be able to pull power right from the computer they're attached to, but in some cases they have a dedicated power supply that will need its own wall outlet. You may need to buy a separate power strip on top of speakers to make sure the entire system will function correctly. Buying the best computer speakers will ensure high-quality gaming and viewing from your machine. While devices come equipped in some cases with onboard sound capability, these tools can't compare to a system of computer speakers.", "parent_text": "Speakers & Headsets", "keyword_density": {"speakers": "1.9", "computer": "1.9", "computer speakers": "1.9"}, "department_id": 3},
{"nr_products": 124, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Product/ProductList.aspx?Submit=ENE&N=100013626%20600010974&IsNodeId=1&name=Sport", "text": "Sport", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Headphones/Category/ID-158", "parent_text": "Headphones", "department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 214, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Web-Cams/SubCategory/ID-152", "text": "Web Cams", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Webcams", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Input-Devices/Category/ID-29", "keyword_count": {"webcams": 5}, "description_wc": 217, "description_text": "Here at Newegg, we offer a wide variety of webcams that vary in function and level of sophistication. The most basic webcams are intended for internet chat use and give viewers a good picture of the person sitting at the computer. High-level webcams, on the other hand, produce fluid streaming video and can be used for business conferences, surveillance, and home security. Reading the Specifications of Webcams Available at Newegg One of the most telling specifications of any webcam is the frame rate. This measures how many frames the camera captures every second. When a camera records just one frame per second (fps), the video appears very choppy. You will see very little correspondence between the person's mouth and the words he or she is speaking. A webcam with a frame rate of 30 fps, on the other hand, will produce video almost as fluid as a television broadcast. Another important measurement is effective pixels. The more effective pixels your web cam has, the clearer the image will be. The most basic webcams produce good images, but viewers may not be able to discern certain details. Features that should appear curved may look rectangular. 1.3 MP or more of effective pixels is ideal however lower amounts of pixels will work for most general purposes.", "parent_text": "Input Devices", "keyword_density": {"webcams": "2.3"}, "department_id": 3},
