{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 176, "level": -3, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Sound-Cards/SubCategory/ID-57", "text": "Sound Cards", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Sound Cards", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Sound-Cards/Category/ID-36", "keyword_count": {"sound": 11, "sound cards": 5}, "description_wc": 300, "description_text": "All computers that can play audio already have sound cards. However, not all PCs come equipped with sound cards that can produce the type of audio you want. If you use a computer as a home theater, music player, or gaming system, it is ideal to have the capability for 5.1 surround sound. 5.1 means there are five speakers and one subwoofer. Sound cards send different audio signals to each of the five speakers, so the speakers all play a different portion of the overall sound. Rather than simply hearing the audio from a computer, a listener becomes immersed in whatever is playing. This intensifies the video gaming experience and enhances your enjoyment of music and movies. Sound Card Features to Look for If you plan on using a computer to record or play music, consider purchasing a sound card with MIDI. MIDI is a standard for connecting electronic musical instruments. Having MIDI is especially helpful to musicians who like to write and record their own songs. With the right software programs and a sound card with MIDI, it is possible for one musician to play five different instruments (one at a time) and then overlap the recordings together to make one song on the computer. Other important sound card specifications include whether or not the card has a microphone plug, and the operating systems that can read the card. It is especially important to check this latter detail if you are using an older operating system. Some of the newer sound cards only work with newer operating systems. Here at Newegg, we have dozens of sound cards that can transform your computer into a state-of-the-art stereo system. Our electronics are sold at discounted prices, so you will find quality products at great values on our website.", "parent_text": "Sound Cards", "keyword_density": {"sound": "3.7", "sound cards": "3.3"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 232, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Specialized-Scanners/SubCategory/ID-761", "text": "Specialized Scanners", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Scanners", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Printers-Scanners-Supplies/Category/ID-33", "keyword_count": {"scanners": 5}, "description_wc": 151, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Scanners in our Learning Center Providing a world of digital imaging possibilities right at your fingertips, a scanner digitizes photo prints or other printed materials onto your computer for further manipulation or long-term archiving. You will be able to view the scanned pictures on the computer monitor or on a TV, or share them with friends and family via email. Scanners will also translate and transfer printed or handwritten documents and books into computer editable and searchable text for the utmost in home and office convenience. You can get document scanners that will scan hundreds of pages, on both sides, at speed. There are scanners especially for anything large-format artwork down to ones just for scanning business cards, or even scanning 35mm slides, filmstrips or negatives. Newegg carries scanners from Canon, Epson, HP, Plustek, Fujitsu, Visioneer, Kodak, Microtek, and many, many more!", "parent_text": "Printers / Scanners & Supplies", "keyword_density": {"scanners": "3.3"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 434, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Fax-Machines-Copiers/SubCategory/ID-351", "text": "Fax Machines & Copiers", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Fax Machines", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Printers-Scanners-Supplies/Category/ID-33", "keyword_count": {"fax": 8, "fax machines": 5, "machines": 6}, "description_wc": 211, "description_text": "Many fax machines are integrated with telephones, copiers, and computer printers. If you need one of each, purchasing a four-in-one or three-in-one device can save you a considerable amount of money, especially if you purchase your fax machine here at Newegg. We offer state-of-the-art technology at the best prices you will find at any store. Features and Applications of Our Fax Machines Scanning and printing capabilities are two of the most important aspects of any fax machine, photo copier, or printer. If you prefer to have the capability to send and receive color documents, there are plenty of color fax machines in our online catalog. Surprisingly, color fax machines are not much more expensive than black-and-white-only machines. Modem speed is probably the most important thing you will look for in a fax machine. The slower the speed the lower the amount of pages you can transmit in a minute. Most fax machines today are in the 14.4Kbps or 33.6Kbs ranges and perform quite quick with transmission speeds between 6 seconds (slower models) and 2 seconds (faster models) per page. Manufacturers that we carry include Brother, Xerox, Hewlett-Packard, and Canon all with print options of color inkjet, thermal inkjet, or laser.", "parent_text": "Printers / Scanners & Supplies", "keyword_density": {"fax": "3.8", "fax machines": "4.7", "machines": "2.8"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 122, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Dot-Matrix-Printers/SubCategory/ID-631", "text": "Dot Matrix Printers", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Printers & Multifunction Devices", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Printers-Scanners-Supplies/Category/ID-33", "keyword_count": {"printers": 5, "multifunction devices": 1}, "description_wc": 220, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Printers and Multifunction Devices in our Learning Center Thinking about printing color photos and text documents in the comfort of your own living room or office? Newegg.com provides an extensive selection of ink jet and laser printers, as well as compact photo printers and all-in-one units (Fax/scanner/printer) from a portfolio of established manufacturers, from HP and Xerox, to Samsung, Canon, Brother, Epson, Kodak, Okidata, Panasonic and more to make sure you find the printer that most closely meets your requirements. In choosing a printer, you need to determine first what your main use will be. If it's text documents, it's one sort; if photos and brochures, something else. Think about the size of the documents you'll be printing -- letter and legal can be handled by almost all of them, but if you need a printer that can handle tabloid or larger jobs, you'll need something more powerful. Specialty photo printers offer a compact alternative if all you're doing is making copies of pix from your digital camera. Consider whether you need a networked or workgroup printer, capable of handling input from a number of computers. The All-in-One printers/scanner/fax machines offer a collection of services in one versatile yet compact machine.", "parent_text": "Printers / Scanners & Supplies", "keyword_density": {"multifunction devices": "0.9", "printers": "2.3"}, "department_id": 3},
