{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 1738, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Barcode-Scanners/SubCategory/ID-583", "text": "Barcode Scanners", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Barcode Scanners", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Printers-Scanners-Supplies/Category/ID-33", "keyword_count": {"barcode scanners": 4, "barcode": 6, "scanners": 5}, "description_wc": 289, "description_text": "The point of sale (POS) terminal is one of the most important locations in every business, whether it's a multinational chain or a local convenience store. It's inefficient for employees to manually enter every Universal Product Code (UPC). If customers have large purchase orders, it may take awhile for those transactions to be completed. Barcode scanners can simplify the entire process and save time during checkouts. These devices read barcodes and enter the product information directly to your registers. Employees simply wave the readers over items to check the prices. Every POS terminal is different and there are various scanner models for every system. USB barcode scanners can be used with almost every register. As long you have an available USB port you can sync the reader to your system and start ringing items. Employees shouldn't struggle with their hardware. Small problems can cause delays that frustrate customers who are tired of waiting. If a scanner's cord is tangled, associates have to stop helping patrons and untie the knots. Wireless barcode scanners are easy to use and don't require any additional steps to sync with POS terminals. Scanners have many advantages over entering prices or UPCs for every purchase. For example, if your employees manually enter item totals, there's no way to track inventory. Barcode scanners can help connect your registers to your stockroom so you can monitor which products are selling quickly and should be restocked soon. Barcode readers also help employees complete more transactions. Associates only need to press a button to scan an item through. Additionally, workers can interact with patrons and deliver stronger customer service because staffers don't have to read long codes and type them repeatedly.", "parent_text": "Printers / Scanners & Supplies", "keyword_density": {"barcode scanners": "2.8", "barcode": "2.1", "scanners": "1.7"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 483, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Memory/SubCategory/ID-381", "text": "Laptop Memory", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop / Notebook Memory", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "keyword_count": {"laptop notebook": 1, "notebook": 2, "notebook memory": 1, "memory": 7}, "description_wc": 196, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Notebook Memory in our Learning Center Prefer to run your computer with fewer restrictions? You can do this and run more programs simultaneously by adding more memory to your system. The memory referred to here is RAM (Random Access Memory), which is essentially the computer's workspace - the place where your computer temporarily stores data and programs. Memory performance is an important factor influencing total system performance as memory speed allows more data to be transferred in a given time for greater system response and performance in demanding applications and games. With prices for memory falling there is no better time to stock up and at Newegg you can select from a wide assortment of speeds and capacity. Whether it's 125MB, 256MB, 512MB, 1GB or 2GB in capacity or speeds covering PC 100, PC 133, DDR 266 (PC 2100), DDR 333 (PC 2700), DDR 400 (PC 3200), DDR2 400 (PC2 3200), DDR2 533 (PC2 4200), DDR2 667 (PC2 5300), DDR2 667 (PC2 5400), DDR2 800 (PC2 6400) and more we have the right solution for your laptop / notebook upgrade needs.", "parent_text": "Laptop Accessories", "keyword_density": {"laptop notebook": "1.1", "notebook": "1.1", "notebook memory": "1.1", "memory": "3.7"}, "department_id": 3},
{"level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Scanners/Category/ID-209", "text": "Scanners", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Printers-Scanners-Supplies/Category/ID-33", "parent_text": "Printers / Scanners & Supplies", "department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 4989, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Cases-Bags/SubCategory/ID-482", "text": "Laptop Cases & Bags", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop Cases and Bags", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "keyword_count": {"laptop": 9, "laptop cases": 4}, "description_wc": 273, "description_text": "Laptop cases are essential for students and professionals who need to be able to take their work everywhere. Because of the fragile nature of laptop PCs, a regular bag or backpack just won\u2019t cut it - you need to protect your valuable documents and media. Not only do laptop cases protect the exterior in the event of a bump or fall, but they offer added cushioning that ensures the sensitive interior hardware stays intact as well. At Newegg you\u2019ll find affordable, stylish options perfect for any professional. Need a way to tote your work while still looking sharp? Consider a laptop briefcase or over-the-shoulder messenger case. Our professional models are both rugged and stylish. Most include several lockable zipper compartments to store your office supplies, and feature ergonomic handles and/or and adjustable shoulder straps for maximum versatility. Those who travel frequently can find models that feature trolley straps, to ensure the case stays in place when stored on top of a rolling suitcase. Students may be more interested in a backpack laptop case, which are suitable for larger laptops and offer ample storage space for textbooks, notebooks and other supplies. Backpack laptop cases are easy to carry around campus, and many models offer lifetime warranties, so you know they\u2019ll be able to keep up with your busy lifestyle. If you don\u2019t travel much and need something a little simpler, consider a notebook sleeve. These items offer all the protection you need without the frills. A laptop is more than just a computer - it\u2019s an investment. Protect yours with one of our many specially designed laptop cases.", "parent_text": "Laptop Accessories", "keyword_density": {"laptop": "3.3", "laptop cases": "2.9"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 1018760, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Batteries-AC-Adapters/SubCategory/ID-538", "text": "Laptop Batteries / AC Adapters", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop Batteries & Chargers", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "keyword_count": {"chargers": 1, "laptop": 8, "batteries": 4, "laptop batteries": 1}, "description_wc": 310, "description_text": "There aren't many devices that can compete with the computing power and mobility that laptops offer. You can take notebooks anywhere as long as the battery is fully charged or there's an electrical outlet available to serve as a power source. Unfortunately, laptop batteries degrade over time - they store less electricity and die faster as they age. Even the best power supplies start to wear down after months of consistent use. For laptops that have a removable battery, it's easy find a replacement unit. If you know the make and model of your laptop, you can find the right battery easily. Because computers have different connection ports, it's important to find the power supply built specifically for your line of laptop. Some manufacturers offer universal batteries for notebooks that they no longer produce or support. A functioning AC adapter is another necessity for every computer, as no battery can last more than a few hours on a single charge. Like the batteries, it's important to find a compatible laptop charger for a notebook's electrical jack. Some users bring their laptops everywhere - from home to work or school and everywhere in between. Chargers can wear out from being repeatedly unplugged, and if they break there's no way to keep the notebooks they are connected to from losing power. Having a backup on hand in case of emergencies eliminates any unnecessary stress caused by waiting for a replacement. For added convenience, use one as a travel charger and leave the other at home, so you don't have to constantly unplug an adapter every time you go out. Until computer companies invent and produce everlasting batteries, it's important to have the necessary electrical equipment for a laptop. Without the right battery or charger, no computer will be functional after a single day of use.", "parent_text": "Laptop Accessories", "keyword_density": {"chargers": "0.3", "laptop": "2.6", "batteries": "1.3", "laptop batteries": "0.6"}, "department_id": 3},
