{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 1738, "level": -3, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Barcode-Scanners/SubCategory/ID-583", "text": "Barcode Scanners", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Barcode Scanners", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Scanners/Category/ID-209", "keyword_count": {"barcode scanners": 4, "barcode": 6, "scanners": 5}, "description_wc": 289, "description_text": "The point of sale (POS) terminal is one of the most important locations in every business, whether it's a multinational chain or a local convenience store. It's inefficient for employees to manually enter every Universal Product Code (UPC). If customers have large purchase orders, it may take awhile for those transactions to be completed. Barcode scanners can simplify the entire process and save time during checkouts. These devices read barcodes and enter the product information directly to your registers. Employees simply wave the readers over items to check the prices. Every POS terminal is different and there are various scanner models for every system. USB barcode scanners can be used with almost every register. As long you have an available USB port you can sync the reader to your system and start ringing items. Employees shouldn't struggle with their hardware. Small problems can cause delays that frustrate customers who are tired of waiting. If a scanner's cord is tangled, associates have to stop helping patrons and untie the knots. Wireless barcode scanners are easy to use and don't require any additional steps to sync with POS terminals. Scanners have many advantages over entering prices or UPCs for every purchase. For example, if your employees manually enter item totals, there's no way to track inventory. Barcode scanners can help connect your registers to your stockroom so you can monitor which products are selling quickly and should be restocked soon. Barcode readers also help employees complete more transactions. Associates only need to press a button to scan an item through. Additionally, workers can interact with patrons and deliver stronger customer service because staffers don't have to read long codes and type them repeatedly.", "parent_text": "Scanners", "keyword_density": {"barcode scanners": "2.8", "barcode": "2.1", "scanners": "1.7"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 141, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/PC-Game-Controllers/SubCategory/ID-123", "text": "PC Game Controllers", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Game Controllers", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Input-Devices/Category/ID-29", "keyword_count": {"controllers": 5, "game": 12, "game controllers": 1}, "description_wc": 312, "description_text": "Whether you use a PC or a console, the right game controller can make all the difference when you're playing your favorite titles. It can be frustrating to navigate digital worlds with mouse clicks and keyboard commands. Some controllers are meant for general use and can be frustrating to use during certain games that require other peripheral devices. Fortunately, there are game controllers available for almost every scenario and game genre. For racing fans, pedals and steering wheels may be comfortable to use while playing. Instead of relying on buttons and triggers, gamers can control their vehicles just like their own cars. Complicated commands don't have to be entered with these driving simulators, as players can hit the gas as soon as they're ready to move. If you're a fan of aerial action or are using a flight simulation game, it may be best to use equipment similar to that found in many cockpits. The best of these peripherals are accurate recreations of the tools and gauges that pilots use while in flight. There are even gadgets that act as radar systems for on-screen action, so gamers learn to focus on more than on-screen action. PC game lovers don't have to restrict themselves to their keyboards any longer, as desktop controllers are available. Many of these devices are resemble the devices used by consoles, so players should be comfortable with the layouts. Gamers who don't want to sit too closely to their displays should consider wireless controllers that sync automatically with their systems. Even though videogame consoles typically come with a controller, a second device is necessary to play with another person. There are peripherals available for many of the major systems, like the Xbox 360, so gamers can play with their friends. Sensor controllers are also available for fans of motion-based games.", "parent_text": "Input Devices", "keyword_density": {"controllers": "1.6", "game": "3.8", "game controllers": "0.6"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 227, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Microphones/SubCategory/ID-122", "text": "Microphones", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "USB Microphones", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Input-Devices/Category/ID-29", "keyword_count": {"microphones": 2, "usb": 4}, "description_wc": 297, "description_text": "Ever want to talk to somebody on the other side of the world but yelling at your computer screen just doesn't seem to work? Paying for an international call isn't necessary if you have a USB mic for your PC or laptop, making talking to anyone around the world as easy as turning on the device. These gadgets connect quickly and easily, are functional with any computer and provide unlimited high-quality audio to anyone you can connect with. These are also handy for online gaming with programs like Ventrillo, which allow for in-game communication, so long as you have the right technology on your end. Built-in microphones just don't offer the same quality as an external USB microphone, with enhanced clarity and sound customization that gives them superior performance to a base-level device. If you've ever wanted to do audio and sound work with your computer or electrical instruments, these are essential for getting studio-grade results. The more upscale models still offer the same plug-and-play connectivity, but with automatic level adjustment, analog controls and signal muting, some rival even professional-grade tools. A USB microphone of high caliber frees you from the anchor of a computer, letting you set it up with a wired or wireless connection to provide the best possible customization and function. Whether you're chatting with a friend on Skype, owning noobs in World of Warcraft or cutting a new album with your garage band, microphones that come attached to your computer just won't give you the same level of performance that a USB microphone can provide. With dozens of options for quality, clarity and control, there's no limit to how far you can take your voice using these devices.", "parent_text": "Input Devices", "keyword_density": {"microphones": "0.7", "usb": "1.3"}, "department_id": 3},
{"nr_products": 1461, "level": -3, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Printer-Scanner-Fax-Accessories/SubCategory/ID-284", "text": "Printer / Scanner / Fax Accessories", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Scanners/Category/ID-209", "parent_text": "Scanners", "department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 636, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/KVM-Switches/SubCategory/ID-143", "text": "KVM Switches", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "KVM Switches", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Input-Devices/Category/ID-29", "keyword_count": {"kvm": 6, "kvm switches": 4}, "description_wc": 247, "description_text": "Suppose you have more than one computer in the same room but you do not have enough room for a second monitor. Or, you have a laptop and want to use it with your home computer's keyboard, mouse and monitor, without changing your current setup. The answer lies in a handy device called a KVM switch. KVM stands for keyboard, video, mouse. The keyboard, video, and mouse set collectively is called a \"console.\" KVM switches allow you to connect a console to more than one computer. You simply connect your console cables to the output jacks of the switch and connect the switch to the connections on your computer that the keyboard mouse and monitor would normally be plugged into. It's that simple. KVM Switches Let You Switch between Consoles To switch consoles, you just push a button on the switch and it allows you to use the other console. KVM switches save you money because you won't have to purchase separate keyboards, mice, and monitors for each computer you use. It makes it very easy when one person uses more than one computer at work, for example. They are also useful for server farms with one staff person accessing each computer periodically, one at a time. When buying KVM switches, it is important to fully understand your needs before you buy anything. Make sure the switch you choose will support your monitor refresh rates and resolution so that the signals are not degraded.", "parent_text": "Input Devices", "keyword_density": {"kvm": "2.4", "kvm switches": "3.2"}, "department_id": 3},
