{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 316, "level": -3, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Document-Scanners/SubCategory/ID-634", "text": "Document Scanners", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Scanners", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Scanners/Category/ID-209", "keyword_count": {"scanners": 5}, "description_wc": 151, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Scanners in our Learning Center Providing a world of digital imaging possibilities right at your fingertips, a scanner digitizes photo prints or other printed materials onto your computer for further manipulation or long-term archiving. You will be able to view the scanned pictures on the computer monitor or on a TV, or share them with friends and family via email. Scanners will also translate and transfer printed or handwritten documents and books into computer editable and searchable text for the utmost in home and office convenience. You can get document scanners that will scan hundreds of pages, on both sides, at speed. There are scanners especially for anything large-format artwork down to ones just for scanning business cards, or even scanning 35mm slides, filmstrips or negatives. Newegg carries scanners from Canon, Epson, HP, Plustek, Fujitsu, Visioneer, Kodak, Microtek, and many, many more!", "parent_text": "Scanners", "keyword_density": {"scanners": "3.3"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 12680, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Keyboards/SubCategory/ID-63", "text": "Keyboards", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Keyboards", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Input-Devices/Category/ID-29", "keyword_count": {"keyboards": 4}, "description_wc": 392, "description_text": "The keyboard is without a doubt one of the most important computer accessories available. The computer keyboard is an input device that sends commands and text inputs to the computer, and is the main interface that we use to communicate or control the computer in combination with the mouse. Unfortunately, not every computer's keyboard is comfortable and sturdy. Without these two characteristics, productivity may decline as working becomes a hassle and can even be painful. You may believe that your typing technique requires improvement, but more often than not faulty hardware is the root of your discomfort. Not every model has wrist supports and you can hurt your arms while you type without assistance. Ergonomic keyboards are designed to help you use your computer without any pain. These models have larger bases, letting you rest your wrists and palms while typing. Instead of uncomfortably hovering over your keyboard, your hands have the necessary support to prevent any strain and reduce the likelihood of developing physical ailments like carpal tunnel syndrome. Pads are commonly found on gaming keyboards as those are meant for more casual use. During a marathon game session, players must usually enter a great deal of key commands. With a standard keyboard, this can lead to pain or discomfort, as their hands continually move without support or rest. Some gaming models, by contrast, have features that can improve a gamer's performance as well. Wireless keyboards are also available - these ensure that users aren't tethered to their desks. If you have a large enough screen, you can use your device while sitting away from your computer. Working without wires also allows you to find a relaxed position, so you aren't confined to a single table. Buying a new keyboard can improve your typing proficiency, whether you're writing a term paper or playing a video game. The right device can raise your comfort levels while also making it easier to use your computer through key commands. Brands featured at Newegg include Microsoft, KeyTronic, Adesso, Logitech and many others. Available in multiple styles and versions you can find one to suit your unique needs rather it's multimedia, gaming, or just looking for the latest new thing. At Newegg you'll find what you need. Use this link for more information on Computer Keyboards in our Learning Center", "parent_text": "Input Devices", "keyword_density": {"keyboards": "1.0"}, "department_id": 3},
