{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 128, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Graphics-Tablets/SubCategory/ID-296", "text": "Graphics Tablets", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Graphics Tablet", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Input-Devices/Category/ID-29", "keyword_count": {"graphics tablet": 2, "tablet": 8}, "description_wc": 319, "description_text": "Tablets have made computing easier and more convenient by combining the functionality of a laptop with the portability of an e-reader or smartphone. Some devices have been built for more specific functions, allowing consumers to buy a tablet that suits their individual needs. For artists and graphic designers, a drawing tablet might be the best option. These devices are basically digital sketchbooks. Instead of drawing a design or an image and then recreating it on a laptop, a graphics tablet comes equipped with software so users can create their artwork, save it and share the file with other devices via an internet or wired connection. There are pen tablets available for designers who aren't quite ready to make the leap to touchscreen technology. Most of these devices' screens are sensitive enough that they'll respond to the pen in natural way to create different shades, styles and lines. If you aren't comfortable with the pen that a tablet came packaged with, there are other peripherals available. You can shop around until you find the pen that feels most comfortable in your hand. There are replacement parts available for some pens, which could be useful if you're worried that you'll quickly wear out your drawing tool. Consumers who don't want to untangle wires every time they need to share a new file with another device should consider buying a wireless connection kit. A USB wireless connector enables sharing with any PC, even if the design tablet was not built with wireless sharing. Don't forget to buy a carrying case, so your device is well-protected during transport. Screens are very sensitive and will be susceptible to scratches and scuff marks if left exposed to the elements. A graphics tablet could be the perfect device for any artist who wants to work digitally but feels limited by the creation tools available on a computer.", "parent_text": "Input Devices", "keyword_density": {"graphics tablet": "1.3", "tablet": "2.5"}, "department_id": 3},
