{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 176, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Sound-Cards/SubCategory/ID-57", "text": "Sound Cards", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Sound Cards", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Speakers-Headsets/Category/ID-37", "keyword_count": {"sound": 11, "sound cards": 5}, "description_wc": 300, "description_text": "All computers that can play audio already have sound cards. However, not all PCs come equipped with sound cards that can produce the type of audio you want. If you use a computer as a home theater, music player, or gaming system, it is ideal to have the capability for 5.1 surround sound. 5.1 means there are five speakers and one subwoofer. Sound cards send different audio signals to each of the five speakers, so the speakers all play a different portion of the overall sound. Rather than simply hearing the audio from a computer, a listener becomes immersed in whatever is playing. This intensifies the video gaming experience and enhances your enjoyment of music and movies. Sound Card Features to Look for If you plan on using a computer to record or play music, consider purchasing a sound card with MIDI. MIDI is a standard for connecting electronic musical instruments. Having MIDI is especially helpful to musicians who like to write and record their own songs. With the right software programs and a sound card with MIDI, it is possible for one musician to play five different instruments (one at a time) and then overlap the recordings together to make one song on the computer. Other important sound card specifications include whether or not the card has a microphone plug, and the operating systems that can read the card. It is especially important to check this latter detail if you are using an older operating system. Some of the newer sound cards only work with newer operating systems. Here at Newegg, we have dozens of sound cards that can transform your computer into a state-of-the-art stereo system. Our electronics are sold at discounted prices, so you will find quality products at great values on our website.", "parent_text": "Speakers & Headsets", "keyword_density": {"sound": "3.7", "sound cards": "3.3"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 672, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Headsets-Accessories/SubCategory/ID-707", "text": "Headsets & Accessories", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Headsets", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Speakers-Headsets/Category/ID-37", "keyword_count": {"headsets": 4}, "description_wc": 287, "description_text": "Gamers see their hobby as serious business, so having the right tools to maximize playtime is essential. Nobody wants to mess around with desk microphones with unnecessary feedback or large computer speakers that garble in-game music and distort what other players are saying. Serious gaming requires serious headsets, and finding one that works best for you is what raises your in-game performance. Like standard pairs of headphones , headsets have a variety of styles and sizes. Some have bands that go over the top of the head, others wrap behind and still others do away with bands altogether and clip to ears to avoid stressing the temples. A wireless set may be more up a gamer's alley, as these relieve the exasperation a tethered headset can provide. The real added benefit of a headset comes from the onboard microphone, a feature that not all headsets provide but one that's worth looking for. This function gives you the ability to talk and listen without getting excessive feedback from keyboard or electronic activity, as well as reducing the amount of interference on your end so that other people in your conversation can hear you more easily. As any gamer knows, a successful raid relies partly on good communication, so it's essential that everyone in the party knows who you're dotting before someone kites the group. Headsets come in a variety of colors and styles, and picking the right one with the best additional features will depend on your preferences. Noise reducing, wireless or wired, with a slew of different wearing options and the ability to talk more easily while hammering on your keyboard, a headset is an integral part of successful online communication.", "parent_text": "Speakers & Headsets", "keyword_density": {"headsets": "1.4"}, "department_id": 3},
