{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Store/PromotionStore/ID-2125620?name=Gaming-Entertainment", "text": "Gaming & Entertainment", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Gaming PCs", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Desktop-PCs/Category/ID-228", "keyword_count": {"gaming": 3, "pcs": 2}, "description_wc": 144, "description_text": "Use this link for more on Desktop PCs in our Learning Center Looking for a powerful, ready-to-use computer for the home or office? A desktop PC here refers to a completely pre-built desktop computer, which is the antithesis of the self-built or DIY (do it yourself) desktop computer system. Gaming PC is offered by brandname manufacturers, like ASUS, DELL, Hewlett-Packard, Acer, Lenovo, and SIs (Systems Integrators) and are typically offered with full system warranties. About midway between Home and Workstation desktop PCs are the gaming PC. These have sufficient 3D processing power to generate the graphics and physics effects prevalent in modern video games with enough performance left over for background applications such as antivirus software. Gaming PC feature mid-to-high end processors, high density RAM, and usually have at least one performance to high-end graphics card.", "parent_text": "Desktop PCs", "keyword_density": {"gaming": "2.1", "pcs": "1.4"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Store/PromotionStore/ID-2125004?name=Business-Desktops-Workstations", "text": "Business Desktops & Workstations", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Business Desktop PCs", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Desktop-PCs/Category/ID-228", "keyword_count": {"business": 21, "business desktop pcs": 5, "pcs": 10, "desktop": 22, "business desktop": 16, "desktop pcs": 8}, "description_wc": 727, "description_text": "Use this link for more on Desktop PCs in our Learning Center Looking for a powerful, ready-to-use computer for the home or office? A desktop PC here refers to a completely pre-built desktop computer, which is the antithesis of the self-built or DIY (do it yourself) desktop computer system. Desktop PCs are offered by brandname manufacturers, like ASUS, DELL, Hewlett-Packard, Compaq, Acer, Lenovo, Gateway and Sony VAIO or SIs (Systems Integrators) and are typically offered with full system warranties. Business desktop PCs is your run-of-the mill desktop PCs, usually featuring standard components with enough power to run a typical user\u2019s applications. Reliability is also the key factor in choosing business desktop Pcs as this type is generally hands free maintenance and should last without any problems. .SEOContent_TableAlignment td {vertical-align: top;} #bcaShopWindowSEO a { color: blue; text-decoration: underline; } #bcaShopWindowSEO a:active { color: red; } #bcaShopWindowSEO a:visited { color: purple; } #bcaShopWindowSEO a:hover { border: none; } .seo { color: #202020; line-height: 125%; font-family: calibri, verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;}.seo h2 { font-weight: bold; color: #043566; font-size: 14pt !important; margin-bottom: 5px; margin-top: 0px;}.seo h3 { font-weight: bold; color: #043566; font-size: 11pt !important; margin-bottom: 5px;}.seo p { margin-top: 0px; }/** Box Sizing **/.column_left { width: 47%; padding-right: 3%; float: left; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; }.column_right { width: 47%; padding-left: 3%; float: right; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; } Laptops may be getting more popular for some businesses, but a business desktop PC is still ideal for many small to medium sized organizations that do not have staff traveling with their workstation computers. On top of being typically faster and cheaper than laptops, an business desktop PC is easier to upgrade and usually can be repaired without being sent back to the manufacturer. With so many choices, it can be hard to find the best business desktop PC for your organization, but Newegg.com will break down what you should be looking for when shopping for a business desktop PC below. Consider the following criteria when purchasing a business desktop PC for your organization: Traditionally, a business desktop PC meant a large tower coupled with a monitor. Business desktop PCs now have towers that range from full-size to compact, with some no more than a foot tall. There are even all-in-one PCs that eliminate the tower by combining the monitor and tower into one compact unit, which can free up some space in a crowded office. A business Desktop PC that will be used for general office administration and word processing will not need huge amounts of processing power, and an octa-core processor is usually not required. Find a workable balance where the processor is powerful enough for the tasks you intend to use it for. Solid state drives are very popular, but not all business desktop PCs will need the increased read and access times that they provide. Consider getting solid state drives for business desktop PC that require fast read and write speeds for specialized jobs or fast boot speeds. Otherwise, a traditional hard drive will be sufficient for most tasks. Most business desktop PCs used for general administrative tasks and word processing will not require dedicated graphics cards, so you can reduce costs by purchasing PCs with onboard video. However, an exception may be made for business-grade graphics cards if your organization is purchasing a business desktop PC for design, simulation, rendering, or any other graphics related tasks. Also, if the tasks that the business PC will be performing require a lot of screen space, consider getting a business desktop PC with a capable of outputting video to multiple displays to improve productivity and efficiency. Many basic business desktops come with DVD writers, which should be sufficient for general use, but you can always add a Blu-ray drive if it is required for the tasks that the business PC will be doing. Keep those key points in mind when shopping for a business PC and you will find one that fulfills its role and fits your organization\u2019s budget. Avoid over-spending by buying one with specifications that are above and beyond what is needed. The ideal workstation PC should be sufficient for its function without being unnecessarily expensive and laden with necessary features.", "parent_text": "Desktop PCs", "keyword_density": {"business": "2.9", "business desktop pcs": "2.1", "pcs": "1.4", "desktop": "3.0", "business desktop": "4.4", "desktop pcs": "2.2"}, "department_id": 3},
