{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 309, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/All-Laptop-Hard-Drives/SubCategory/ID-380?name=Laptop-Hard-Drives", "text": "Laptop Hard Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop / Notebook Hard Drives", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptops-Notebooks/Category/ID-223", "keyword_count": {"laptop notebook hard drives": 1, "hard drives": 2, "laptop": 2, "hard": 4, "drives": 4, "notebook hard": 2, "notebook": 4}, "description_wc": 135, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Laptop / Notebook Hard Drives in our Learning Center Looking for a replacement notebook hard drive or simply not satisfied with the performance of the original hard drive in your notebook computer? Newegg.com offers a large selection of notebook/laptop hard drives with storage capacities perfectly tailored to your requirements, as well as products that can contribute to higher levels of system performance for maximum enjoyment from your movies, pictures and games. Select from manufacturers such as Hitachi, Fujitsu, Seagate, Toshiba, Western Digital and Samsung with capacity limits ranging from 40GB to 320GB. Additionally, while most drives are SATA 1.5Gb/s we also carry a fair share of ATA-6 and SATA 3.0Gb/s drives too. Speed are in standard formats of 4200 RPM, 5400 RPM, and 7200 RPM.", "parent_text": "Laptops / Notebooks", "keyword_density": {"laptop notebook hard drives": "3.0", "hard drives": "3.0", "laptop": "1.5", "hard": "3.0", "drives": "3.0", "notebook hard": "3.0", "notebook": "3.0"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "text": "Laptop Accessories", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop Accessories", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptops-Notebooks/Category/ID-223", "keyword_count": {"laptop accessories": 3, "laptop": 14}, "description_wc": 378, "description_text": "It seems like everyone has a laptop these days. While tablets may be lighter, depending on the specific make and model, almost no device can match the functionality and convenience of a portable computer. Buying the right laptop accessories could create an even better user experience by making devices safer and supplementing the hardware. One of a laptop's biggest conveniences is its portability, but it can be awkward to carry in hand and doing so increases the odds of an accident - like being dropped on the sidewalk. A padded backpack can carry a laptop of any size while protecting the device from the elements. Laptop bags and cases are designed to absorb most bumps and bruises, so any valuables stored inside are less likely to be damaged during transit. You might also want to protect your laptop from potential thieves. Putting a lock on a computer would make it difficult for anyone to just walk away with it. Many laptops come with a security slot, so you might want to take advantage of it for additional security measures. Heavier users may find it difficult to find a device that can meet all their demands. A laptop battery can lose power quickly when the machine is asked to handle too many tasks at once. Sometimes there might not be an available outlet, so a power adapter is necessary to provide the extra juice needed to finish an important project before the charge dies. Additionally, most batteries last longer if a laptop does not overheat. Unfortunately, it's easy for a system's internal fan to be obstructed because they are mostly located on the bottom. A cooling pad could supplement a laptop's fans and prevent damage caused by excessive heat. Most of these devices connect via a USB port but have additional outlets so users can still connect flash drives with their computer while the cooling pad is working. Newegg is proud to offer a variety of laptop accessories, including laptop batteries, AC adapters, extended warranties, add-on cards, laptop bags and cases, hard drives, memory, networking devices, luggage & bags, replicators, docking stations and solid state disks. Find the laptop accessories you\u2019re looking for while enjoying the smoothest, most pleasurable online shopping experience available at Newegg.com.", "parent_text": "Laptops / Notebooks", "keyword_density": {"laptop accessories": "1.6", "laptop": "3.7"}, "department_id": 3},
{"nr_products": 64, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Gaming-Notebooks/SubCategory/ID-3365", "text": "Gaming Notebooks", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Gaming-Notebooks/Category/ID-363", "parent_text": "Gaming Notebooks", "department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Projectors/Category/ID-343", "text": "Projectors", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Business Projectors", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptops-Notebooks/Category/ID-223", "keyword_count": {"business": 2, "projectors": 5, "business projectors": 1}, "description_wc": 136, "description_text": "Use this link for more on Business Projectors in our Learning Center Newegg.com offers a rich selection of projectors using LCD or DLP and from mainstream to professional.We carry projectors from Epson, InFocus, Mitsubishi, Sony, NEC and others. These days, projectors come in a wide range of resolutions and luminosities, for small offices or large lecture halls! Home and business users alike will be able to find projectors that fit and function perfectly both for the office and the home and enjoy maximum visual quality and impact as well as enhanced work efficiency. WARNING: Products with exposed solder may contain lead, a chemical known to the State of California to cause cancer, birth defects and other reproductive harm. Please wash hands after handling internal components and motherboards and avoid inhalation of fumes if heating the solder.", "parent_text": "Laptops / Notebooks", "keyword_density": {"business projectors": "1.5", "projectors": "3.7", "business": "1.5"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Chromebooks/Category/ID-269", "text": "Chromebooks", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Chromebook", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptops-Notebooks/Category/ID-223", "keyword_count": {"chromebook": 13}, "description_wc": 434, "description_text": "The laptop has enjoyed several incarnations since it was first embraced on a wide scale. Netbooks first appeared as an answer to the mobility provided by the iPhone and enjoyed, however briefly, massive popularity. One of the closest relatives to the netbook is the Chromebook. Developed initially by Google, the Chromebook is a small laptop optimized for use with the Internet. While it may seem \"pidgeon-holed\" by its Google designation, many other manufacturers have seen promise in the device, developing their own Chromebooks and generating massive interest for a laptop in the age of tablets . How Chromebook works, what it does To be designated a Chromebook, a laptop must be running Chrome OS, which is essentially a variation of the Chrome web browser that allows for work to be done offline. Supplemented by small, fast flash storage, the cloud does most of the work for these machines. By serving more as a portal to the Internet and as less of an operating system, Chromebook users avoid constant security updates, out-of-date hardware and the sluggishness that comes with an aging system - new versions of the browser are the only system maintenance that needs to be addressed. Without a hard drive, Chromebooks experience fast boot times and enjoy extended battery life when compared to traditional laptops. Proponents of these computers praise it for its streamlined capabilities and ease of use. This sort of technology is perfect for students, and Dell 's first foray into Chromebook development was fueled by how it could be used in classrooms. Other manufacturers Google may have created it and coined its name off their own web browser, but other companies like Dell are also putting big money into the Chromebook game. Taiwanese company Acer has even developed a touchscreen unit, continuing to bridge the gap between laptops and tablets (Google has also created a touchscreen version of their Chromebook called the Pixel). Longtime computer giants HP and Samsung are some other of the notable names to also dip their toes into the market's waters. Chromebooks Affordability Chromebooks, like the netbooks that came before them, also receive admiration for their cost-effectiveness. With the notable exception of Google's new Pixel (over $1,000), most units are well under $300, making them great for productivity on a budget and ideal for students or as secondary machines to laptops that have more processing power. If all that is needed out of a laptop is some streaming, browsing, organizing and writing, and a tablet is not going to cut it, then a Chromebook may be a perfect solution.", "parent_text": "Laptops / Notebooks", "keyword_density": {"chromebook": "3.0"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Projectors/Category/ID-343", "text": "Projectors", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Business Projectors", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks/Category/ID-259", "keyword_count": {"business": 2, "projectors": 5, "business projectors": 1}, "description_wc": 136, "description_text": "Use this link for more on Business Projectors in our Learning Center Newegg.com offers a rich selection of projectors using LCD or DLP and from mainstream to professional.We carry projectors from Epson, InFocus, Mitsubishi, Sony, NEC and others. These days, projectors come in a wide range of resolutions and luminosities, for small offices or large lecture halls! Home and business users alike will be able to find projectors that fit and function perfectly both for the office and the home and enjoy maximum visual quality and impact as well as enhanced work efficiency. WARNING: Products with exposed solder may contain lead, a chemical known to the State of California to cause cancer, birth defects and other reproductive harm. Please wash hands after handling internal components and motherboards and avoid inhalation of fumes if heating the solder.", "parent_text": "Ultrabooks", "keyword_density": {"business projectors": "1.5", "projectors": "3.7", "business": "1.5"}, "department_id": 3},
{"nr_products": 48, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Product/ProductList.aspx?Submit=Property&Subcategory=10&Description=&Type=&N=100019096&IsNodeId=1&IsPowerSearch=1&srchInDesc=&MinPrice=&MaxPrice=&OEMMark=0&OEMMark=N&OEMMark=1&Manufactory=44837&Manufactory=10418&Manufactory=44828&PropertyCodeValue=3089%3A20937", "text": "Lenovo Commerical Desktop", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Store/PromotionStore/ID-2125004?name=Business-Desktops-Workstations", "parent_text": "Business Desktops & Workstations", "department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "department_id": 3},
{"nr_products": 101, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/External-CD-DVD-Blu-Ray-Drives/SubCategory/ID-420", "text": "External CD / DVD / Blu-Ray Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks/Category/ID-259", "parent_text": "Ultrabooks", "department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks/Category/ID-259", "text": "Ultrabooks", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "What is an Ultrabook?", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptops-Notebooks/Category/ID-223", "keyword_count": {"ultrabook": 12}, "description_wc": 360, "description_text": "The Ultrabook concept, spearheaded by Intel, is essentially the next step in the evolution of netbooks. A netbooks is a small, lightweight laptop that has been created with portability in mind. An Ultrabook improves upon the netbook by giving users a more complete computing experience. These slim pieces of machinery also come packed with high-powered features, so you don\u2019t have to sacrifice performance for portability and style. Next-generation ultrabooks To actually qualify as an Ultrabook, a PC must meet certain Intel quality standards for speed and processing power. In addition to being lightweight like its netbook predecessor, an Ultrabook must be thin. Most weigh less than three pounds and are under an inch thick when closed. Also, the high-definition resolution of an Ultrabook is superior to most monitors available today. The everlasting battery A short charge is the bane of every laptop user's existence. To combat poor performance and running time, Intel requires ultrabooks to feature at least five hours of battery life. An all-day battery would be a dream come true for most consumers. Currently, the best ultrabooks offer about eight hours of battery life, which would be particularly convenient for users who can't constantly recharge their devices. For instance, college students and traveling businesspeople won't have to worry about their laptops if Intel keeps its promise. Touchscreen may be the future Ultrabooks and tablets are strong competitors among the tech industry mainly because the devices share a great deal of similarities. Both machines are convenient for mobile use and allow users to complete basic tasks. The biggest difference between tablets and ultrabooks is their software. Tablets run on mobile operating systems like Android and iOS, while ultrabooks feature Windows 7. With Windows 8 , however, the gap between the gadgets might close completely. The next-generation of ultrabooks will look completely different from today's computers. Technological innovations and increased performance standards will force manufacturers to build high-quality laptops. If computers with all-day battery life, touchscreen capabilities and 1080p resolution become the standard, then it's difficult to imagine that there are further improvements that manufacturers could make.", "parent_text": "Laptops / Notebooks", "keyword_density": {"ultrabook": "3.3"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 2208, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/All-Laptops-Notebooks/SubCategory/ID-32", "text": "All Laptops / Notebooks", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "We Have a Laptop Computer for You", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptops-Notebooks/Category/ID-223", "keyword_count": {"laptop computer": 2, "laptop": 12, "computer": 5}, "description_wc": 327, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Laptop and Notebook Computers in our Learning Center Laptop or notebook computers have entered 2013 with an ever-growing list of features. More and more, workers who travel frequently are using laptops in place of unwieldy desktop systems. The popularity of the laptop is growing exponentially as more people have a need for portability of information. Taking your work home is also easier on the laptop computer. The laptop requires much less space than a desktop and offers the convenience of sitting in a comfortable recliner, lounging outdoors, or making use of time spent in flight. You can even enjoy gaming while traveling. Laptops come in a wide range of shapes and forms. For example, the latest generation of laptops, known as Ultrabooks , offers road warriors an ultraportable machine with stylish design at a bargain price. The features to consider in the purchase of a laptop will be determined largely by the purpose for buying the computer. If you do a lot of networking, the best way to go is wireless. Wi-Fi is available in most hotels and in many restaurants for the convenience of the patrons. You can surf the Internet, download, or upload information as needed with a wireless setup. If necessary, you can purchase a wireless broadband service and card that will allow you to connect literally anywhere your cellphone reaches! At Newegg.com we offer the lowest prices on a wide variety of laptop computer systems. We carry laptops from manufacturers like Lenovo, ASUS, HP, Sony VAIO, Acer, Toshiba, Apple and others. If you do a lot of graphics or games, or want to watch your DVDs, you'll need a top-quality graphics card and a large enough hard drive to hold it all. Hard drive sizes and the processor speed will vary considerably among the various notebook brands. Let us help you find the laptop that you will use for years to come.", "parent_text": "Laptops / Notebooks", "keyword_density": {"laptop computer": "1.2", "laptop": "3.7", "computer": "1.5"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 558, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/All-External-Hard-Drives/SubCategory/ID-414", "text": "All External Hard Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "External Hard Drives", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks/Category/ID-259", "keyword_count": {"external hard": 8, "external hard drives": 5, "hard": 13, "drives": 6, "external": 11}, "description_wc": 398, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on External Hard Drives in our Learning Center External hard drives are ideal for backing up your hard drive or storing additional media separately from your main hard drive. Photos, videos, and digital music have all become so popular in recent years that people need a place to put it all. CDs and DVDs do not have the capacity to hold PC backups and are not all that convenient. However, the prices of external hard drives have come down so much that they are perfect for backing up your important data. The two most common interfaces for hooking up external drives to your computer are USB and FireWire with eSata now becoming popular also. USB has been around for years and are standard on just about all computers today while FireWire ports are newer and if you use a digital video camera with your computer you probably already have one. In terms of access speeds the latest eSata standard offers the fastest connection however that comes with a price. USB 2.0 and Firewire can cover most of your general needs without having to upgrade your system with a new eSata card. Any of the interfaces will do the job however be sure to purchase an external hard drive with the same type of port that your computer has. Your backup drive should have a capacity at least as big as your computer's largest hard drive. That will leave you with plenty of room to back up your important files or mirror/clone your current drive. You can also buy an external hard drive case and mount an internal hard drive inside it. This method will give you a choice of brands and models, and if anything goes wrong with your internal hard drive, you can simply install the external one inside your computer to replace it. Considerations for External Hard Drives One drawback to using external hard drives for backups is that they are still relatively new for home computer use. They come with Windows drivers; should Windows fail, you will not be able to access your external drive through DOS. There are DOS drivers available but they can be difficult to find and most manufacturers do not provide support for them. This isn't a frequent occurrence, just something to keep in mind as you select your external hard drive.", "parent_text": "Ultrabooks", "keyword_density": {"external hard": "4.0", "external hard drives": "3.8", "hard": "3.3", "drives": "1.5", "external": "2.8"}, "department_id": 3},
