{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 558, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/All-External-Hard-Drives/SubCategory/ID-414", "text": "All External Hard Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "External Hard Drives", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks/Category/ID-259", "keyword_count": {"external hard": 8, "external hard drives": 5, "hard": 13, "drives": 6, "external": 11}, "description_wc": 398, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on External Hard Drives in our Learning Center External hard drives are ideal for backing up your hard drive or storing additional media separately from your main hard drive. Photos, videos, and digital music have all become so popular in recent years that people need a place to put it all. CDs and DVDs do not have the capacity to hold PC backups and are not all that convenient. However, the prices of external hard drives have come down so much that they are perfect for backing up your important data. The two most common interfaces for hooking up external drives to your computer are USB and FireWire with eSata now becoming popular also. USB has been around for years and are standard on just about all computers today while FireWire ports are newer and if you use a digital video camera with your computer you probably already have one. In terms of access speeds the latest eSata standard offers the fastest connection however that comes with a price. USB 2.0 and Firewire can cover most of your general needs without having to upgrade your system with a new eSata card. Any of the interfaces will do the job however be sure to purchase an external hard drive with the same type of port that your computer has. Your backup drive should have a capacity at least as big as your computer's largest hard drive. That will leave you with plenty of room to back up your important files or mirror/clone your current drive. You can also buy an external hard drive case and mount an internal hard drive inside it. This method will give you a choice of brands and models, and if anything goes wrong with your internal hard drive, you can simply install the external one inside your computer to replace it. Considerations for External Hard Drives One drawback to using external hard drives for backups is that they are still relatively new for home computer use. They come with Windows drivers; should Windows fail, you will not be able to access your external drive through DOS. There are DOS drivers available but they can be difficult to find and most manufacturers do not provide support for them. This isn't a frequent occurrence, just something to keep in mind as you select your external hard drive.", "parent_text": "Ultrabooks", "keyword_density": {"external hard": "4.0", "external hard drives": "3.8", "hard": "3.3", "drives": "1.5", "external": "2.8"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "text": "Laptop Accessories", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop Accessories", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Gaming-Notebooks/Category/ID-363", "keyword_count": {"laptop accessories": 3, "laptop": 14}, "description_wc": 378, "description_text": "It seems like everyone has a laptop these days. While tablets may be lighter, depending on the specific make and model, almost no device can match the functionality and convenience of a portable computer. Buying the right laptop accessories could create an even better user experience by making devices safer and supplementing the hardware. One of a laptop's biggest conveniences is its portability, but it can be awkward to carry in hand and doing so increases the odds of an accident - like being dropped on the sidewalk. A padded backpack can carry a laptop of any size while protecting the device from the elements. Laptop bags and cases are designed to absorb most bumps and bruises, so any valuables stored inside are less likely to be damaged during transit. You might also want to protect your laptop from potential thieves. Putting a lock on a computer would make it difficult for anyone to just walk away with it. Many laptops come with a security slot, so you might want to take advantage of it for additional security measures. Heavier users may find it difficult to find a device that can meet all their demands. A laptop battery can lose power quickly when the machine is asked to handle too many tasks at once. Sometimes there might not be an available outlet, so a power adapter is necessary to provide the extra juice needed to finish an important project before the charge dies. Additionally, most batteries last longer if a laptop does not overheat. Unfortunately, it's easy for a system's internal fan to be obstructed because they are mostly located on the bottom. A cooling pad could supplement a laptop's fans and prevent damage caused by excessive heat. Most of these devices connect via a USB port but have additional outlets so users can still connect flash drives with their computer while the cooling pad is working. Newegg is proud to offer a variety of laptop accessories, including laptop batteries, AC adapters, extended warranties, add-on cards, laptop bags and cases, hard drives, memory, networking devices, luggage & bags, replicators, docking stations and solid state disks. Find the laptop accessories you\u2019re looking for while enjoying the smoothest, most pleasurable online shopping experience available at Newegg.com.", "parent_text": "Gaming Notebooks", "keyword_density": {"laptop accessories": "1.6", "laptop": "3.7"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26?name=Ultrabook-Accessories", "text": "Ultrabook Accessories", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop Accessories", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Ultrabooks/Category/ID-259", "keyword_count": {"laptop accessories": 3, "laptop": 14}, "description_wc": 378, "description_text": "It seems like everyone has a laptop these days. While tablets may be lighter, depending on the specific make and model, almost no device can match the functionality and convenience of a portable computer. Buying the right laptop accessories could create an even better user experience by making devices safer and supplementing the hardware. One of a laptop's biggest conveniences is its portability, but it can be awkward to carry in hand and doing so increases the odds of an accident - like being dropped on the sidewalk. A padded backpack can carry a laptop of any size while protecting the device from the elements. Laptop bags and cases are designed to absorb most bumps and bruises, so any valuables stored inside are less likely to be damaged during transit. You might also want to protect your laptop from potential thieves. Putting a lock on a computer would make it difficult for anyone to just walk away with it. Many laptops come with a security slot, so you might want to take advantage of it for additional security measures. Heavier users may find it difficult to find a device that can meet all their demands. A laptop battery can lose power quickly when the machine is asked to handle too many tasks at once. Sometimes there might not be an available outlet, so a power adapter is necessary to provide the extra juice needed to finish an important project before the charge dies. Additionally, most batteries last longer if a laptop does not overheat. Unfortunately, it's easy for a system's internal fan to be obstructed because they are mostly located on the bottom. A cooling pad could supplement a laptop's fans and prevent damage caused by excessive heat. Most of these devices connect via a USB port but have additional outlets so users can still connect flash drives with their computer while the cooling pad is working. Newegg is proud to offer a variety of laptop accessories, including laptop batteries, AC adapters, extended warranties, add-on cards, laptop bags and cases, hard drives, memory, networking devices, luggage & bags, replicators, docking stations and solid state disks. Find the laptop accessories you\u2019re looking for while enjoying the smoothest, most pleasurable online shopping experience available at Newegg.com.", "parent_text": "Ultrabooks", "keyword_density": {"laptop accessories": "1.6", "laptop": "3.7"}, "department_id": 3},
