{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 456, "level": -3, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Internal-SSDs/SubCategory/ID-636", "text": "Internal SSDs", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Solid State Drives", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "keyword_count": {"solid state": 2, "drives": 7, "solid state drives": 1}, "description_wc": 299, "description_text": "A hard disk drive (HDD) stores every file that is saved to a computer. The units hold data and spin when users access their content. This process requires a great deal of electricity to function properly, which can cause a delay in the speed with which information is displayed on-screen. Solid state drives (SSDs) are becoming a popular alternative to the factory-installed drives. SSDs resemble HDDs on the outside, but their internal processes don't have much in common. The newer drives don't have any moving parts - unlike hard drives that have two magnetic, spinning plates. There are two key advantages to this structural design - it requires less power and provides faster access to saved data. Because files can be read straight from the SSDs, laptops are able to boot up without delay. Users have individual storage needs, so some might not find one SSD as useful as others. There are some drives with only 32 gigabytes (GB) of space, which may be enough for casual use but not enough to save large libraries or backup entire systems. Luckily, there are SSD deals available for every size unit from various manufacturers. This makes it simple to find the correct piece of equipment for every PC, as the two devices must be compatible to work properly. Some universal drives have brackets allowing them to be installed into various pieces of hardware, regardless of system specifications. Users should be sure they know how to install an SSD before making their purchase. Some drives come bundled with instructional DVDs and manuals that guide amateurs through the installation process step-by-step so they don't accidentally damage their system. Upgrading to a solid state drive from a hard drive can make any computer more efficient and convenient to use.", "parent_text": "Laptop Accessories", "keyword_density": {"solid state": "1.3", "drives": "2.3", "solid state drives": "1.0"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 4989, "level": -3, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Cases-Bags/SubCategory/ID-482", "text": "Laptop Cases & Bags", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop Cases and Bags", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "keyword_count": {"laptop": 9, "laptop cases": 4}, "description_wc": 273, "description_text": "Laptop cases are essential for students and professionals who need to be able to take their work everywhere. Because of the fragile nature of laptop PCs, a regular bag or backpack just won\u2019t cut it - you need to protect your valuable documents and media. Not only do laptop cases protect the exterior in the event of a bump or fall, but they offer added cushioning that ensures the sensitive interior hardware stays intact as well. At Newegg you\u2019ll find affordable, stylish options perfect for any professional. Need a way to tote your work while still looking sharp? Consider a laptop briefcase or over-the-shoulder messenger case. Our professional models are both rugged and stylish. Most include several lockable zipper compartments to store your office supplies, and feature ergonomic handles and/or and adjustable shoulder straps for maximum versatility. Those who travel frequently can find models that feature trolley straps, to ensure the case stays in place when stored on top of a rolling suitcase. Students may be more interested in a backpack laptop case, which are suitable for larger laptops and offer ample storage space for textbooks, notebooks and other supplies. Backpack laptop cases are easy to carry around campus, and many models offer lifetime warranties, so you know they\u2019ll be able to keep up with your busy lifestyle. If you don\u2019t travel much and need something a little simpler, consider a notebook sleeve. These items offer all the protection you need without the frills. A laptop is more than just a computer - it\u2019s an investment. Protect yours with one of our many specially designed laptop cases.", "parent_text": "Laptop Accessories", "keyword_density": {"laptop": "3.3", "laptop cases": "2.9"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 1018760, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Batteries-AC-Adapters/SubCategory/ID-538", "text": "Laptop Batteries / AC Adapters", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop Batteries & Chargers", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26?name=Ultrabook-Accessories", "keyword_count": {"chargers": 1, "laptop": 8, "batteries": 4, "laptop batteries": 1}, "description_wc": 310, "description_text": "There aren't many devices that can compete with the computing power and mobility that laptops offer. You can take notebooks anywhere as long as the battery is fully charged or there's an electrical outlet available to serve as a power source. Unfortunately, laptop batteries degrade over time - they store less electricity and die faster as they age. Even the best power supplies start to wear down after months of consistent use. For laptops that have a removable battery, it's easy find a replacement unit. If you know the make and model of your laptop, you can find the right battery easily. Because computers have different connection ports, it's important to find the power supply built specifically for your line of laptop. Some manufacturers offer universal batteries for notebooks that they no longer produce or support. A functioning AC adapter is another necessity for every computer, as no battery can last more than a few hours on a single charge. Like the batteries, it's important to find a compatible laptop charger for a notebook's electrical jack. Some users bring their laptops everywhere - from home to work or school and everywhere in between. Chargers can wear out from being repeatedly unplugged, and if they break there's no way to keep the notebooks they are connected to from losing power. Having a backup on hand in case of emergencies eliminates any unnecessary stress caused by waiting for a replacement. For added convenience, use one as a travel charger and leave the other at home, so you don't have to constantly unplug an adapter every time you go out. Until computer companies invent and produce everlasting batteries, it's important to have the necessary electrical equipment for a laptop. Without the right battery or charger, no computer will be functional after a single day of use.", "parent_text": "Ultrabook Accessories", "keyword_density": {"chargers": "0.3", "laptop": "2.6", "batteries": "1.3", "laptop batteries": "0.6"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 309, "level": -3, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/All-Laptop-Hard-Drives/SubCategory/ID-380", "text": "All Laptop Hard Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop / Notebook Hard Drives", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "keyword_count": {"laptop notebook hard drives": 1, "hard drives": 2, "laptop": 2, "hard": 4, "drives": 4, "notebook hard": 2, "notebook": 4}, "description_wc": 135, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Laptop / Notebook Hard Drives in our Learning Center Looking for a replacement notebook hard drive or simply not satisfied with the performance of the original hard drive in your notebook computer? Newegg.com offers a large selection of notebook/laptop hard drives with storage capacities perfectly tailored to your requirements, as well as products that can contribute to higher levels of system performance for maximum enjoyment from your movies, pictures and games. Select from manufacturers such as Hitachi, Fujitsu, Seagate, Toshiba, Western Digital and Samsung with capacity limits ranging from 40GB to 320GB. Additionally, while most drives are SATA 1.5Gb/s we also carry a fair share of ATA-6 and SATA 3.0Gb/s drives too. Speed are in standard formats of 4200 RPM, 5400 RPM, and 7200 RPM.", "parent_text": "Laptop Accessories", "keyword_density": {"laptop notebook hard drives": "3.0", "hard drives": "3.0", "laptop": "1.5", "hard": "3.0", "drives": "3.0", "notebook hard": "3.0", "notebook": "3.0"}, "department_id": 3},
