{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 73, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Home-Theater-Projectors/SubCategory/ID-513", "text": "Home Theater Projectors", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Home Theater Projectors", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Projectors/Category/ID-343", "keyword_count": {"home theater": 5, "projectors": 2}, "description_wc": 337, "description_text": "Putting together a home theater system can be difficult. All the equipment needs to be compatible to give an audience the best viewing experience. Due to strides in technology, audio devices can make movies and television shows sound crystal clear, but a standard high-definition television's picture might lag behind a sound system's performance. Buying the best home theater projector could level the playing field. If you're going to be watching a great deal of programming, a projector might be easier on the eyes than an LCD or LED television. The devices are backlit to create a sharper image on screen, while sending light directly into your vision. This is what usually causes eye strain after watching for an extended period of time. Projectors are only directing light toward the screen, making it more comfortable to enjoy a movie marathon. There is more flexibility with a home theater projector, as well. Instead of having a television with a set size, a projector can be adjusted to fill bigger and smaller display areas. Moving the device further away from the screen creates a bigger image, while moving it closer shrinks it. This is a convenient adjustment for users who want to use their device in more than one room. It is important to note the minimum and maximum size settings on each projector, because picture quality will deteriorate if moved beyond those thresholds. You may want to consider the lamp life of a projector before making a purchase. Light bulbs don't last forever, so at some point you'll need to replace one in your device. Most projectors offer settings designed to lengthen a bulb's life, but these options may reduce viewing quality while cutting down on power consumption. It's important to consider all your needs before buying a home theater projector. Make sure you have figured out what you expect from the device and what you'll use it for, so you can buy the best one for your home theater.", "parent_text": "Projectors", "keyword_density": {"home theater": "3.0", "projectors": "0.6"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 466, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Business-Projectors/SubCategory/ID-42", "text": "Business Projectors", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Business Projectors", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Projectors/Category/ID-343", "keyword_count": {"business": 2, "projectors": 5, "business projectors": 1}, "description_wc": 119, "description_text": "Use this link for more on Business Projectors in our Learning Center Newegg.com offers a rich selection of projectors using LCD or DLP and from mainstream to professional.We carry projectors from Epson, InFocus, Mitsubishi, Sony, NEC and others. These days, projectors come in a wide range of resolutions and luminosities, for small offices or large lecture halls! Home and business users alike will be able to find projectors that fit and function perfectly both for the office and the home and enjoy maximum visual quality and impact as well as enhanced work efficiency. WARNING: The products listed on this page may contain chemicals known to the State of California to cause cancer, or birth defects or other reproductive harm.", "parent_text": "Projectors", "keyword_density": {"business projectors": "1.7", "projectors": "4.2", "business": "1.7"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 483, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Memory/SubCategory/ID-381", "text": "Laptop Memory", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop / Notebook Memory", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "keyword_count": {"laptop notebook": 1, "notebook": 2, "notebook memory": 1, "memory": 7}, "description_wc": 196, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Notebook Memory in our Learning Center Prefer to run your computer with fewer restrictions? You can do this and run more programs simultaneously by adding more memory to your system. The memory referred to here is RAM (Random Access Memory), which is essentially the computer's workspace - the place where your computer temporarily stores data and programs. Memory performance is an important factor influencing total system performance as memory speed allows more data to be transferred in a given time for greater system response and performance in demanding applications and games. With prices for memory falling there is no better time to stock up and at Newegg you can select from a wide assortment of speeds and capacity. Whether it's 125MB, 256MB, 512MB, 1GB or 2GB in capacity or speeds covering PC 100, PC 133, DDR 266 (PC 2100), DDR 333 (PC 2700), DDR 400 (PC 3200), DDR2 400 (PC2 3200), DDR2 533 (PC2 4200), DDR2 667 (PC2 5300), DDR2 667 (PC2 5400), DDR2 800 (PC2 6400) and more we have the right solution for your laptop / notebook upgrade needs.", "parent_text": "Laptop Accessories", "keyword_density": {"laptop notebook": "1.1", "notebook": "1.1", "notebook memory": "1.1", "memory": "3.7"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 151, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Replicators-Docking-Stations/SubCategory/ID-537", "text": "Replicators / Docking Stations", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop Docking Stations", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "keyword_count": {"laptop docking stations": 1, "laptop": 7, "docking": 3, "docking stations": 2, "stations": 3}, "description_wc": 288, "description_text": "Laptops and tablets have become popular options for shoppers who want to bring their computers everywhere. Manufacturers have begun producing slimmer models of both devices at the expense of some features that users may need, like ethernet jacks or HDMI ports. For those who have replaced their desktop with a laptop or tablet, this lack of hardware support can be a problem. Attaching a device to a port replicator is a solution for those who need the extra outlets and hardware support. Port replicators connect to a laptop or tablet via the battery hook-up, so the peripheral acts as a base for the device. Some tablet stations include an external keyboard for consumers who don't like typing on the screen, while others may need extra USB slots to connect with other accessories. Many ultrabooks don't have a CD drive, but some laptop docking stations have disc readers if you need to access content from CDs and DVDs. Other models offer ethernet connections, USB ports and audio jacks but lack a disc reader. You can pick and choose which features you need to supplement your laptop's functionality. Port replicators can be quickly disconnected so a device is never tethered to a desk. Users can connect all peripheral devices, like external hard drives and printers, to a base so instead of unplugging multiple accessories only the docking station needs to be removed from a tablet or laptop. This convenient accessory is great for workers who bring their mobile computers to work each day. A slim device doesn't have to lack the functionality found in desktops and heavier machines. Docking stations provide users with all the features missing from their laptops and tablets without sacrificing mobility.", "parent_text": "Laptop Accessories", "keyword_density": {"laptop docking stations": "1.0", "laptop": "2.4", "docking": "1.0", "docking stations": "1.4", "stations": "1.0"}, "department_id": 3},
{"nr_products": 3252, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Cooling/SubCategory/ID-319", "text": "Laptop Cooling", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "parent_text": "Laptop Accessories", "department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 15, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Networking/SubCategory/ID-34", "text": "Laptop Networking", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop Wireless Cards", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "keyword_count": {"wireless": 7, "cards": 4, "laptop": 6, "wireless cards": 2, "laptop wireless cards": 1}, "description_wc": 313, "description_text": "Wi-Fi connectivity makes a laptop even more useful to its owner. Most people use their computers as gateways to the internet, so it can be frustrating if they can't go online because they can't find an ethernet cable. Consumers can buy wireless cards for laptops so their devices can connect with a signal from anywhere. These cards need to be installed to a computer's motherboard to use a wireless signal. Many of the available models come with tutorials and instruction guides, so even shoppers who aren't tech-savvy can easily install their new purchase. Laptop wireless cards act as internal receivers, allowing a computer to connect to the internet over the air without an ethernet cord. Users who are on the go need this added convenience so their devices can be fully functional anywhere there's a wireless signal. For example, college students can install a card so their laptops work in class and in the library - not just in their dorm rooms or apartments. A laptop must be within a certain proximity to a Wi-Fi router to receive the signal, as the card itself does not generate web connectivity. Fortunately, many establishments, ranging from coffee shops to public libraries, provide wireless web access, so everyone can find a place to go online. For users who want to add an ethernet connection to their notebook, there are cards with jacks for cords. Manufacturers have begun producing slim laptops that remove ethernet ports to reduce the devices' overall weight. Much like a wireless card, these units are installed internally but have an external attachment intended for a wired connection. You should make sure the wireless card you're thinking about purchasing matches your computer's hardware specifications. Access points must have driver support to function properly, so be sure to check what your system is capable of supporting.", "parent_text": "Laptop Accessories", "keyword_density": {"wireless": "2.2", "cards": "1.3", "laptop": "1.9", "wireless cards": "1.3", "laptop wireless cards": "1.0"}, "department_id": 3},
{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 4989, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Cases-Bags/SubCategory/ID-482", "text": "Laptop Cases & Bags", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop Cases and Bags", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "keyword_count": {"laptop": 9, "laptop cases": 4}, "description_wc": 273, "description_text": "Laptop cases are essential for students and professionals who need to be able to take their work everywhere. Because of the fragile nature of laptop PCs, a regular bag or backpack just won\u2019t cut it - you need to protect your valuable documents and media. Not only do laptop cases protect the exterior in the event of a bump or fall, but they offer added cushioning that ensures the sensitive interior hardware stays intact as well. At Newegg you\u2019ll find affordable, stylish options perfect for any professional. Need a way to tote your work while still looking sharp? Consider a laptop briefcase or over-the-shoulder messenger case. Our professional models are both rugged and stylish. Most include several lockable zipper compartments to store your office supplies, and feature ergonomic handles and/or and adjustable shoulder straps for maximum versatility. Those who travel frequently can find models that feature trolley straps, to ensure the case stays in place when stored on top of a rolling suitcase. Students may be more interested in a backpack laptop case, which are suitable for larger laptops and offer ample storage space for textbooks, notebooks and other supplies. Backpack laptop cases are easy to carry around campus, and many models offer lifetime warranties, so you know they\u2019ll be able to keep up with your busy lifestyle. If you don\u2019t travel much and need something a little simpler, consider a notebook sleeve. These items offer all the protection you need without the frills. A laptop is more than just a computer - it\u2019s an investment. Protect yours with one of our many specially designed laptop cases.", "parent_text": "Laptop Accessories", "keyword_density": {"laptop": "3.3", "laptop cases": "2.9"}, "department_id": 3},
