{"department_text": "PCs & Laptops", "nr_products": 483, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Memory/SubCategory/ID-381", "text": "Laptop Memory", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PCs-Laptops/Store", "description_title": "Laptop / Notebook Memory", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Accessories/Category/ID-26", "keyword_count": {"laptop notebook": 1, "notebook": 2, "notebook memory": 1, "memory": 7}, "description_wc": 196, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Notebook Memory in our Learning Center Prefer to run your computer with fewer restrictions? You can do this and run more programs simultaneously by adding more memory to your system. The memory referred to here is RAM (Random Access Memory), which is essentially the computer's workspace - the place where your computer temporarily stores data and programs. Memory performance is an important factor influencing total system performance as memory speed allows more data to be transferred in a given time for greater system response and performance in demanding applications and games. With prices for memory falling there is no better time to stock up and at Newegg you can select from a wide assortment of speeds and capacity. Whether it's 125MB, 256MB, 512MB, 1GB or 2GB in capacity or speeds covering PC 100, PC 133, DDR 266 (PC 2100), DDR 333 (PC 2700), DDR 400 (PC 3200), DDR2 400 (PC2 3200), DDR2 533 (PC2 4200), DDR2 667 (PC2 5300), DDR2 667 (PC2 5400), DDR2 800 (PC2 6400) and more we have the right solution for your laptop / notebook upgrade needs.", "parent_text": "Laptop Accessories", "keyword_density": {"laptop notebook": "1.1", "notebook": "1.1", "notebook memory": "1.1", "memory": "3.7"}, "department_id": 3},
