{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 79, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Workstation-Graphics-Cards/SubCategory/ID-449", "text": "Workstation Graphics Cards", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Video Cards", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Video-Cards-Video-Devices/Category/ID-38", "keyword_count": {"video cards": 1, "video": 8}, "description_wc": 108, "description_text": "Understanding Video Card Specifications The video card processes all graphics related work (especially 3D) and delivers the resultant output to a connected display/monitor. Video card improvements move along at breakneck speeds - a new generation of video cards often replaces the old within 3-6 months. The GPU (Graphics Processing Unit) basically determines the features (e.g. DirectX/OpenGL, HDR, and SLI or CrossFire) and performance level of a video card. Besides the GPU, the video memory specs (including video memory type, size and clock speed), interface (AGP or PCI Express), and I/O ports are should all be taken into account before purchasing a video card.", "parent_text": "Video Cards & Video Devices", "keyword_density": {"video cards": "1.9", "video": "7.5"}, "department_id": 1},
{"nr_products": 239, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Video-Devices-TV-Tuners/SubCategory/ID-47", "text": "Video Devices & TV Tuners", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Video-Cards-Video-Devices/Category/ID-38", "description_wc": 167, "description_text": "Welcome to the Newegg Video Solution Center. Here we provide the latest innovations to bring HDTV to your PC and a lot of other solutions to make your life easier. Do you want to bring HDTV to your PC with an internal TV Tuner Card , watch HDTV anywhere with a USB TV Tuner Stick on a notebook, change your display to a full-function HDTV via an External TV Tuner Box ? We have all the solutions here. In addition, we also have Video Capture tools to help you record all your favorite HDTV programs and gaming videos, and play them back with an HD Media Player on a big TV. What\u2019s more, use our PC to TV products to help you watch whatever you see on your PC screen, like HD online movies from Netflix and more! And with Video Adapters , you will easily access high efficiency with a multi-display working environment. Learn more with Newegg's TV Tuner & Video Device Learning Center !", "parent_text": "Video Cards & Video Devices", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 605, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Desktop-Graphics-Cards/SubCategory/ID-48", "text": "Desktop Graphics Cards", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Video Cards", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Video-Cards-Video-Devices/Category/ID-38", "keyword_count": {"video cards": 2, "video": 11}, "description_wc": 178, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Video Cards in our Learning Center Want to play the latest, most advanced PC games or watch true high definition (HDTV) videos? Newegg.com always provides the hottest video card products from the manufacturers you trust. Now you can even double the graphics performance of your computer with NVIDIA SLI technology or ATI Crossfire technology for a gaming experience that is second to none! Understanding Video Card Specifications The video card processes all graphics related work (especially 3D) and delivers the resultant output to a connected display/monitor. Video card improvements move along at breakneck speeds - a new generation of video cards often replaces the old within 3-6 months. The GPU (Graphics Processing Unit) basically determines the features (e.g. DirectX/OpenGL, HDR, and SLI or CrossFire) and performance level of a video card. Besides the GPU, the video memory specs (including video memory type, size and clock speed), interface (AGP or PCI Express), and I/O ports are should all be taken into account before purchasing a video card.", "parent_text": "Video Cards & Video Devices", "keyword_density": {"video cards": "2.3", "video": "6.2"}, "department_id": 1},
