{"department_text": "Electronics", "nr_products": 232, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Specialized-Scanners/SubCategory/ID-761", "text": "Specialized Scanners", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Electronics/Store", "description_title": "Scanners", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Office-Equipment/Category/ID-27", "keyword_count": {"scanners": 5}, "description_wc": 151, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Scanners in our Learning Center Providing a world of digital imaging possibilities right at your fingertips, a scanner digitizes photo prints or other printed materials onto your computer for further manipulation or long-term archiving. You will be able to view the scanned pictures on the computer monitor or on a TV, or share them with friends and family via email. Scanners will also translate and transfer printed or handwritten documents and books into computer editable and searchable text for the utmost in home and office convenience. You can get document scanners that will scan hundreds of pages, on both sides, at speed. There are scanners especially for anything large-format artwork down to ones just for scanning business cards, or even scanning 35mm slides, filmstrips or negatives. Newegg carries scanners from Canon, Epson, HP, Plustek, Fujitsu, Visioneer, Kodak, Microtek, and many, many more!", "parent_text": "Office Equipment", "keyword_density": {"scanners": "3.3"}, "department_id": 4},
{"department_text": "Electronics", "nr_products": 54, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Network-Print-Servers/SubCategory/ID-387", "text": "Network Print Servers", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Electronics/Store", "description_title": "Printer Servers", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Office-Equipment/Category/ID-27", "keyword_count": {"printer": 7, "servers": 3}, "description_wc": 318, "description_text": "You have been struggling with your network for a little while, but you think you have all the kinks worked out finally. You have a half-dozen computers working together, sending and receiving documents, collaborating on projects, communicating quickly and easily without the interference and lag of a general connection, and you're confident that your network is running properly. Then, you realize that you have to print something. Getting printers set up and accessible within a network structure can be frustrating, especially when working with remote servers and accessing machines, but print servers can assist with getting these devices working more quickly. Whether wired or wireless, these devices plug in to printer network connection ports, granting usage for authorized users and those within the system. As not every manufacturer makes printers compatible with every kind of network or every other print device on the market, a print server can override this incompatibility, making a device usable as long as it has the right adapter. It's also great for offices with multiple printers. A network can host so many machines that it's cumbersome to have all print jobs routed to the same printer, especially when a device is built to handle multiple functions. A printer can also be a scanner, copier and fax machine, making it necessary to have more than one machine to fit unit-task needs, so routing them all into a single client can make it easy for users in a vast network to select a device that's not busy. This also helps when one of these printers inevitably gets jammed. Print servers hook devices into a network in a way that makes them most useful to the greatest number of users. These devices are affordable and easy to install, increase the productivity and flexibility of those working with them and can help make an office a much saner place to work.", "parent_text": "Office Equipment", "keyword_density": {"printer": "2.2", "servers": "0.9"}, "department_id": 4},
{"department_text": "Electronics", "nr_products": 626, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laser-Printers/SubCategory/ID-630", "text": "Laser Printers", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Electronics/Store", "description_title": "Printers & Multifunction Devices", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Office-Equipment/Category/ID-27", "keyword_count": {"printers": 5, "multifunction devices": 1}, "description_wc": 220, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Printers and Multifunction Devices in our Learning Center Thinking about printing color photos and text documents in the comfort of your own living room or office? Newegg.com provides an extensive selection of ink jet and laser printers, as well as compact photo printers and all-in-one units (Fax/scanner/printer) from a portfolio of established manufacturers, from HP and Xerox, to Samsung, Canon, Brother, Epson, Kodak, Okidata, Panasonic and more to make sure you find the printer that most closely meets your requirements. In choosing a printer, you need to determine first what your main use will be. If it's text documents, it's one sort; if photos and brochures, something else. Think about the size of the documents you'll be printing -- letter and legal can be handled by almost all of them, but if you need a printer that can handle tabloid or larger jobs, you'll need something more powerful. Specialty photo printers offer a compact alternative if all you're doing is making copies of pix from your digital camera. Consider whether you need a networked or workgroup printer, capable of handling input from a number of computers. The All-in-One printers/scanner/fax machines offer a collection of services in one versatile yet compact machine.", "parent_text": "Office Equipment", "keyword_density": {"multifunction devices": "0.9", "printers": "2.3"}, "department_id": 4},
{"department_text": "Electronics", "nr_products": 171, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Voice-Recorders/SubCategory/ID-374", "text": "Voice Recorders", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Electronics/Store", "description_title": "Voice Recorders", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Office-Equipment/Category/ID-27", "keyword_count": {"recorders": 6, "voice": 7, "voice recorders": 2}, "description_wc": 465, "description_text": "Do you like to record thoughts and ideas as they come to you, rather than trying to remember them later? Writing them down on the go can be troublesome, especially if you are in a moving vehicle. Voice recorders are the perfect way to record your brilliant ideas without the need for cassette tapes or writing instruments. You can record memos, business meetings, an audio journal, and your phone conversations with these. Instead of storing the information on tape, the machines store them in digital formats. You can then transfer them to your computer to play them back or archive them, or send the audio files to other people through email. If you only need occasional voice recordings or basic functionality, a PDA or MP3 player with voice recording capability will probably suit your needs. However, if you're someone who needs to record conversations, you're better off with a dedicated digital voice recorder. Browse our site to find a large selection and the lowest prices on digital voice recording devices. While smartphones can do almost everything, their generalized functionality prevents the devices from excelling at some tasks. In addition, they have limited storage, and media files like recordings require large amounts of space. Content can easily be lost amid all of the documents stored on such devices, meaning that valuable information could be all but inaccessible. Additionally, some recorders have over 4GB of memory, meaning they can hold sizable libraries. Digital voice recorders only store audio files and can easily be connected to computers to export all documents. Some of these devices are equipped with built-in USB drives allowing you to easily save your notes once you're done recording. These specific models don't require wires, so they're more convenient to use while on the go. Sometimes you'll need to listen to something immediately, so reliable playback is a necessity. There are recorders with speakers and headphone jacks so you can listen to everything instantly without allowing anyone else to hear. Recorders feature strong battery life, so you never have to worry about them dying at an inopportune time. For instance, if you're recording a lecture, you shouldn't worry that you'll miss the conclusion because of a dead battery. Some audiophiles quickly notice the poor quality, especially in digital devices, and prefer analog gadgets. As an alternative, cassette recorders are also available. Some may argue that tapes are inefficient because they don't have large storage capacities, though tapes can be recycled so you don't have to frequently buy new ones. Whether you need to listen in on a business meeting after its conclusion or take personal notes throughout the day, a voice recorder may be one of the best possible gadgets for your job.", "parent_text": "Office Equipment", "keyword_density": {"voice recorders": "0.9", "voice": "1.5", "recorders": "1.3"}, "department_id": 4},
