{"department_text": "Electronics", "nr_products": 1055, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/GPS-Navigation/SubCategory/ID-357", "text": "GPS Navigation", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Electronics/Store", "description_title": "GPS Receivers", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/GPS-Accessories/Category/ID-277", "keyword_count": {"gps": 9, "gps receivers": 4, "receivers": 9}, "description_wc": 272, "description_text": "Use this link for more information about GPS Navigation Systems in our Learning Center GPS (global positioning system) receivers are quickly making atlas maps obsolete. No matter where you are located or how lost you are, a GPS receiver will not only pinpoint your location but also tell you exactly where to go. When you make wrong turns, a GPS receiver will recalculate the route for you. Need a gas station? The more advanced receivers can lead you to the nearest one. Here at Newegg, we offer GPS receivers manufactured by the top companies in the industry. Our extensive collection includes receivers at a wide range of prices. Receivers also vary in terms of accuracy, display, and function. Our online catalog provides detailed specifications for all GPS receivers, which makes it easy for you to find something that meets your needs. How to Choose a GPS Receiver Almost all receivers are accurate within 15 meters, but some are even more exact. Another factor to consider is whether you need voice directions. If you frequently drive alone to new places, voice directions are desirable. While many GPS receivers have well-lit LCD displays, it can still be difficult to read while driving. You can always turn the voice off when you do not need it. If you like to measure distances or track your average speed, many GPS receivers can do this for you. And if you take long road trips that include several destinations, you may want a receiver that can store up to 50 locations. As you can see, there are many things you can do with a global positioning system.", "parent_text": "GPS & Accessories", "keyword_density": {"gps receivers": "2.9", "receivers": "3.3", "gps": "3.3"}, "department_id": 4},
