{"department_text": "Electronics", "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Audio-Video-Cables/Category/ID-184", "text": "Audio / Video Cables", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Electronics/Store", "description_title": "AV Cables", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Home-Theater-Accessories/Category/ID-224", "keyword_count": {"cables": 6, "av": 2}, "description_wc": 293, "description_text": "Audio/video cables can deliver you picture and sound with just a single cord, but can also give you the ability to customize your television, gaming and movie experience by choosing how extensive you want to get with your home audio and video setup. If you've ever dreamed of creating an all-in-one system, audio and video cables can bring all your devices together when you've got them hooked together properly. In terms of bringing external signals into your receiver, a coaxial cable can bring you satellite or cable television, unless you're working with some old-school gaming hardware, in which case a splitter can help you hook multiples of this cable together. More recent audio and visual devices will use DVI or HDMI cables, which will provide connectivity for basically every television, computer, home theater and music device you may want to hook together. Composite cables come in a rainbow of colors to help you get high-definition video and stereo sound with just a single connection, but with HD televisions and newer gaming consoles, the variety has grown to epic proportions with endless customization possible. Firewire cables can even come in handy for connecting computers with televisions, in case you want to share your Internet experience with a group of people or just want a single monitor or television in your home to provide you with all your entertainment needs. Creating a fluid home entertainment experience can't be easier with proper audio and video cables to get maximum synergy going with your whole suite of technological toys. Whether you're looking for a single input or have multiple jacks to work with, you can make your receivers work at optimum levels with correct av cable coupling.", "parent_text": "Home Theater Accessories", "keyword_density": {"cables": "2.0", "av": "0.7"}, "department_id": 4},
