{"department_text": "Electronics", "nr_products": 227, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Microphones/SubCategory/ID-122", "text": "Microphones", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Electronics/Store", "description_title": "USB Microphones", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Portable-Devices/Category/ID-8", "keyword_count": {"microphones": 2, "usb": 4}, "description_wc": 297, "description_text": "Ever want to talk to somebody on the other side of the world but yelling at your computer screen just doesn't seem to work? Paying for an international call isn't necessary if you have a USB mic for your PC or laptop, making talking to anyone around the world as easy as turning on the device. These gadgets connect quickly and easily, are functional with any computer and provide unlimited high-quality audio to anyone you can connect with. These are also handy for online gaming with programs like Ventrillo, which allow for in-game communication, so long as you have the right technology on your end. Built-in microphones just don't offer the same quality as an external USB microphone, with enhanced clarity and sound customization that gives them superior performance to a base-level device. If you've ever wanted to do audio and sound work with your computer or electrical instruments, these are essential for getting studio-grade results. The more upscale models still offer the same plug-and-play connectivity, but with automatic level adjustment, analog controls and signal muting, some rival even professional-grade tools. A USB microphone of high caliber frees you from the anchor of a computer, letting you set it up with a wired or wireless connection to provide the best possible customization and function. Whether you're chatting with a friend on Skype, owning noobs in World of Warcraft or cutting a new album with your garage band, microphones that come attached to your computer just won't give you the same level of performance that a USB microphone can provide. With dozens of options for quality, clarity and control, there's no limit to how far you can take your voice using these devices.", "parent_text": "Portable Devices", "keyword_density": {"microphones": "0.7", "usb": "1.3"}, "department_id": 4},
