{"department_text": "Cell Phones & Cell Phone Accessories", "nr_products": 13953, "level": 0, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Mounts-Holders/SubCategory/ID-2957", "text": "Mounts & Holders", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Cell-Phones-Cell-Phone-Accessories/Store/ID-140", "description_title": "Mounts for your Cell Phone", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Cell-Phones-Cell-Phone-Accessories/Store/ID-140", "keyword_count": {"mounts": 2, "phone": 13, "cell phone": 1}, "description_wc": 305, "description_text": "Cell phones are necessities for most people. Some drivers choose to use their mobile devices while on the road, which is a very dangerous practice. Operating a vehicle requires complete concentration, and talking on the phone can lead to serious accidents. Installing a mount could be the best solution if you need to use your phone while driving. Instead of holding your gadget, you can clip it onto a base so that you can answer calls with a push of a button and put your hand back on the wheel. There are universal mounts that can support any feature phone or smartphone. The holders have adjustable straps and sockets so that the devices won't slide or fall out of place. Additionally, drivers can find cradles that can be attached to their seatbelts, dashboards, air vents or windshields. Consumers can pick the right option for their needs so they can safely and conveniently answer their phones while behind the wheel. Alternatively, you can also find mounts for different smartphone models. Picking a specially designed cradle can provide extra security for your device and even improve its functionality. Some options feature signal boosting technology so you're never outside of your coverage area. iPhone 5 owners can also buy cradles that connect their phones with their cars. It may be beneficial to have a mount that charges a smartphone during long rides. Other models sync with a vehicle's sound system so that the iPhone's playback features can be used to replace the radio. Consider your needs before buying the perfect mount. For instance, if you frequently use your smartphone's GPS, consider a dashboard cradle so you can quickly check directions without taking your eyes off the road. Buying the right mount can help you stay safe while simultaneously driving and using your phone.", "parent_text": "Cell Phones & Cell Phone Accessories", "keyword_density": {"mounts": "0.7", "phone": "4.3", "cell phone": "0.7"}, "department_id": 7},
{"department_text": "Cell Phones & Cell Phone Accessories", "level": 0, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Batteries/Category/ID-246", "text": "Batteries", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Cell-Phones-Cell-Phone-Accessories/Store/ID-140", "description_title": "Batteries for your Cell Phone", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Cell-Phones-Cell-Phone-Accessories/Store/ID-140", "keyword_count": {"phone": 14, "batteries": 6}, "description_wc": 304, "description_text": "The battery is arguably the most important component of any smartphone. Mobile devices that can't hold a charge are unreliable and are frustrating to use. Replacement batteries are sometimes necessary when current models start to wear out and gradually begin to hold less power. Fortunately, new power packs are available for many popular phones like the Samsung Galaxy S3 and the HTC Thunderbolt. Installing a new battery can extend the life of any smartphone, as other hardware components don't lose functionality as quickly as the power sources. Some smartphones like the iPhone 5 and HTC Radar don't feature removable backs and require technical skill to replace the batteries. Mobile charging devices and special cases can provide extra power so that similar models don't become useless when their batteries die. Portable charging stations are available for some versions of the iPhone. The peripheral device connects to the phone's charging port. The mobile chargers are smaller than the iPhone, so they're convenient to carry and don't add unnecessary bulk. Many phones can be put into cases that have additional batteries. Similar to a mobile charger, the covers connect to phones and can double battery life. These devices must be regularly charged, but can usually last longer than smartphones without be connected to an external power source. The cases also protect smartphones from damage like scratches, cracks and chips. Alternatively, you could buy a mobile charger that runs on AA batteries. It can be inconvenient to have to charge your phone and a backup power source, so having a charger that runs on affordable batteries could be a simpler solution. If you're looking for an eco-friendly alternative, there are solar chargers available. The green power devices can help you reduce your carbon footprint while keeping your smartphone alive.", "parent_text": "Cell Phones & Cell Phone Accessories", "keyword_density": {"phone": "4.6", "batteries": "2.0"}, "department_id": 7},
