{"department_text": "Electronics", "nr_products": 219, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Home-Theater-in-a-Box/SubCategory/ID-501", "text": "Home Theater in a Box", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Electronics/Store", "description_title": "Home Theater Systems", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Home-Video/Category/ID-59", "keyword_count": {"home theater systems": 1, "home theater": 5, "systems": 4}, "description_wc": 323, "description_text": "There's nothing that compares to the sonic and visual experience you can achieve through a home theater set-up consisting of the best possible equipment. We've made it a priority to carry home theater systems at prices that anyone can appreciate. Take a look at a few examples, which run the gamut from incredibly affordable systems to the most high-quality models. The primary draw, for many of those looking to acquire a home theater system, is the surround sound - hearing and feeling the strains of the musical score, sound effects and dialogue swirl around you and transport you to another place. A system worth its salt, so to speak, should have four satellite speakers, a center channel and a powerful subwoofer, to experience the loudest bass booms and the quietest dialogue in crystal clarity. Many systems at various price tiers feature that exact speaker layout. Those looking for a set-up that's a little bit simpler and involves less chance of cables becoming confusingly intertwined can find systems with wireless speakers. While no sound system can be truly \"wireless,\" some feature two or more speakers that use an infra-red connection and help you cut down on clutter. Despite all that talk about sound, the image is - of course - just as important. Your primary choice will be between a home theater with a Blu-ray or DVD player. The former can play films on either format, and obviously provides high sound and picture quality in resolution as high as 1080p. A system featuring the latter, meanwhile, will be significantly cheaper in almost all instances. That said, Blu-ray is becoming a more common format in today's market, and as such it's more affordable for the average consumer than ever before. Take a close look and you'll be sure to find a home theater system that meets your needs and doesn't make you break the bank.", "parent_text": "Home Video", "keyword_density": {"home theater systems": "0.9", "home theater": "3.1", "systems": "1.2"}, "department_id": 4},
{"department_text": "Electronics", "nr_products": 510, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/LED-TVs/SubCategory/ID-798", "text": "LED TVs", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Electronics/Store", "description_title": "LED TVs", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Televisions/Category/ID-264", "keyword_count": {"led tvs": 2, "led": 8}, "description_wc": 299, "description_text": "An LED TV is a variation of an LCD TV - using light-emitting diodes (LEDs) instead of fluorescent backlights to illuminate the screen. When you choose an LED TV, you\u2019ll get an energy-efficient unit that is extremely thin and produces a high-quality picture. Whether you are in the mood to watch an action-packed movie or hunt zombies in the middle of a virtual apocalypse, a LED TV can provide an exceptional visual experience. Check out our wide range of affordable units if you are in the market for a new TV! Students looking to outfit their dorm room with an affordable television set may want to consider one of our smaller, more compact models. These devices are economical, easy to use and ideal for placement atop a desk or bureau without taking up too much space. Students with limited space will appreciate the wide viewing angle, allowing them to get a great view no matter where they\u2019re sitting. For those looking for a larger unit, there\u2019s plenty in store! Bigger screens offer more dynamic and expansive viewing and ensure movies and video games look their best at almost any angle, and their flat screens mean you can see the big picture without having to give up on space-saving features. In addition, a number of recent LED TV models also comply with the U.S. Department of Energy\u2019s ENERGY STAR standards, helping you save money. All of our LED TVs include LED backlight, allowing colors to feature beautiful contrast. Additionally, with Wi-Fi and Ethernet internet connectivity, you can browse online, stream videos, play games and check your email \u2013 all through your television! Regardless of your needs, LED TVs offer a high-quality visual experience without breaking the bank or gobbling up electricity.", "parent_text": "Televisions", "keyword_density": {"led tvs": "1.3", "led": "2.7"}, "department_id": 4},
{"department_text": "Electronics", "nr_products": 49, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Plasma-TV/SubCategory/ID-385", "text": "Plasma TV", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Electronics/Store", "description_title": "Plasma TV's", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Televisions/Category/ID-264", "keyword_count": {"tv": 3, "plasma": 6, "plasma tv": 2}, "description_wc": 217, "description_text": "Use this link for more on Plasma TV's in our Learning Center Plasma TV's begin at 42-inch screen sizes. For sizes smaller than that your looking at an LCD monitor. The two technologies are different although they both offer high resolution and clear pictures. Plasma Is Emissive , LCD Is Transmissive With LCD, a liquid crystal display solution is sandwiched between two sheets of glass that make up the front panel. A bulb behind the glass lights up the display whenever a current is passed through the LCD solution. Plasma screens also have two sheets of glass but between them is a layer of phosphor pixels. When UV rays strike the pixels, the gas in them glows. Essentially, each pixel is its own fluorescent light bulb. On large TV screens, such as those in the 60 to 63 inch range, plasma displays typically outperform LCD displays with plasma units displaying a brighter, crisper image even at large sizes. Top LCD's have gotten close in performance, however, it will cost you. A major selling point and advantage to both types of monitors is their thin, flat size. This not only reduces eyestrain, it also takes up less space. Both types offer micro-thin monitors that average about 4\" deep and can be wall mountable.", "parent_text": "Televisions", "keyword_density": {"tv": "1.4", "plasma": "2.8", "plasma tv": "1.9"}, "department_id": 4},
