{"department_text": "Electronics", "nr_products": 234, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/DVD-Players/SubCategory/ID-489", "text": "DVD Players", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Electronics/Store", "description_title": "DVD Players", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Home-Video/Category/ID-59", "keyword_count": {"dvd": 6}, "description_wc": 284, "description_text": "Want to watch a movie but don't want to pay every month for Netflix or watch on your computer? You'll need a DVD player, something to hook up to your TV, sound and entertainment systems to get the best possible viewing experience, with HD playback or even Blu-ray capability. Rather than trying to play a movie in a video game console and burning out the motor, buying a device that's specifically meant to handle the fast playback of DVD movies and television programs can give you a much better viewing experience. These machines are made to be incorporated with home entertainment systems, featuring a variety of connections to assist with hooking it into as complex or simplistic as your home system features. They also may be equipped also with high definition playback capable of 1080p upconversion, should your disc or television not be compatible with that function. Additionally, they can far exceed playback on a computer or laptop. While these devices are suited to running DVDs and stand less of a chance of being damaged by viewing, they are more limited by onboard graphics and sound cards, screen dimensions and usually diminutive speakers. There are also situations where a television and DVD player combination is necessary for playback. Region codes on certain disk and subtitle features would make the disk inoperable in most computers and gaming consoles, but a DVD player can handle the demand, if you purchase the right unit. They're easier and more reliable to work with and make a great addition to any home entertainment system. Buy the best DVD player, sit down with a bowl of popcorn and get ready for a home movie night.", "parent_text": "Home Video", "keyword_density": {"dvd": "2.1"}, "department_id": 4},
