{"department_text": "Gaming", "level": 0, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/PlayStation-3-PS3/Category/ID-282", "text": "PlayStation 3(PS3)", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Gaming/Store", "description_title": "PlayStation 3", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Gaming/Store", "keyword_count": {"playstation": 9, "3": 10, "playstation 3": 4}, "description_wc": 438, "description_text": "PlayStation 3 (officially marketed PLAYSTATION 3, commonly abbreviated PS3) is the third home video game console produced by Sony Computer Entertainment, and the successor to the PlayStation 2 as part of the PlayStation series. A major feature that distinguishes the PlayStation 3 from its predecessors is it's unified online gaming service, the PlayStation Network, which contrasts with Sony's former policy of relying on game developers for online play. Other major features of the console include its robust multimedia capabilities, connectivity with the PlayStation Portable, and its use of a high-definition optical disc format, Blu-ray Disc, as its primary storage medium. The PS3 was also the first Blu-ray 2.0-compliant Blu-ray player on the market. PS3 Games Imagine you own a PlayStation 3. It plays movies, connects to the internet, lets you hang out and chat with your friends and gives you Hulu and Netflix at the touch of a button. But let's be honest, you didn't buy it to play downloadable games or shoot the breeze with your friends. You're looking to shoot aliens, storm castles, explore unknown lands and have silly, wacky adventures. For that you're going to need some PS3 games. If you've walked into a game store recently you've probably noticed there are hundreds of titles to choose from, and walking in circles and staring at the walls isn't the best way to find out more about a title. Box art may look cool, but it won't necessarily give you information on HUD interfaces, gameplay graphics or continuity of storyline. Deciding on a genre is always a great place to start. First-person shooters, role playing, driving, action, adventure, horror, strategy, sports and fighting titles from various game studios are out in force. That's right, you also have to decide if you like Rockstar to Konami, EA over Activision, or Square Enix more than Namco. One of the other things to take into account is the rating. Not everyone wants to see blood and gore, but some gamers like the realistic intensity of games with more mature ratings. When buying as a gift, it may not be the best decision to buy an M-rated game, so be mindful of the ESRB's handy guidelines while selecting your games. Purchasing PS3 games can take a little time, but usually it will be love at first sight. Go with your gut, pick a genre and a plotline you love, and sit down for hours of quality time with your PlayStation once you have all the PS3 games to rock it with.", "parent_text": "Gaming", "keyword_density": {"playstation": "2.1", "3": "2.3", "playstation 3": "1.8"}, "department_id": 6},
{"department_text": "Gaming", "nr_products": 2672, "level": 0, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Xbox-360-Accessories/SubCategory/ID-517?name=Xbox-Accessories", "text": "Xbox Accessories", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Gaming/Store", "description_title": "Xbox 360 Accessories", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Gaming/Store", "keyword_count": {"xbox 360": 1, "360": 3, "xbox": 3}, "description_wc": 303, "description_text": "The Xbox 360 is a user-friendly device that offers countless ways to stay entertained. The console offers access to music, movies, sports, and, of course, video games. It may be a great media hub, but without the right peripheral devices it may be difficult to enjoy the 360's full potential. If you want to go online with the console you need a subscription to Xbox LIVE. The service is offered in monthly increments, so you can decide what time frame meets your needs to avoid wasteful spending on a subscription. If you want to buy any games, movies, or music from Microsoft's online store make sure you have plenty of Microsoft Points. Spare controllers are necessary for gamers who plan on playing with others. Rechargeable batteries and charging stations are available so gamers don't have to find a new pair of AA's every time power is running low. You could also replace the controller with your own movements by adding Kinect to your 360. Adding the motion sensor bar to the console gives you the ability to control your content with gestures and voice commands. While starting a movie by telling your Xbox to \"play disc\" may be convenient, playing games on Kinect may be awkward for some users who need an object to interact with and can't just act out certain activities. For example, a bowling ball replica may make bowling more fun and feel less like a game of charades. Make sure your device is well-connected with all the right wires and cords. Kinect's motion sensor can be moved further away from a television to prevent any motion-related accidents. Finally, don't forget an HDMI cable so all your favorite games, movies and shows are displayed in the highest possible picture quality.", "parent_text": "Gaming", "keyword_density": {"xbox 360": "0.7", "360": "1.0", "xbox": "1.0"}, "department_id": 6},
