{"department_text": "Software", "nr_products": 141, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/PC-Game-Controllers/SubCategory/ID-123", "text": "PC Game Controllers", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Software/Store", "description_title": "Game Controllers", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PC-Games-Accessories/Category/ID-275", "keyword_count": {"controllers": 5, "game": 12, "game controllers": 1}, "description_wc": 312, "description_text": "Whether you use a PC or a console, the right game controller can make all the difference when you're playing your favorite titles. It can be frustrating to navigate digital worlds with mouse clicks and keyboard commands. Some controllers are meant for general use and can be frustrating to use during certain games that require other peripheral devices. Fortunately, there are game controllers available for almost every scenario and game genre. For racing fans, pedals and steering wheels may be comfortable to use while playing. Instead of relying on buttons and triggers, gamers can control their vehicles just like their own cars. Complicated commands don't have to be entered with these driving simulators, as players can hit the gas as soon as they're ready to move. If you're a fan of aerial action or are using a flight simulation game, it may be best to use equipment similar to that found in many cockpits. The best of these peripherals are accurate recreations of the tools and gauges that pilots use while in flight. There are even gadgets that act as radar systems for on-screen action, so gamers learn to focus on more than on-screen action. PC game lovers don't have to restrict themselves to their keyboards any longer, as desktop controllers are available. Many of these devices are resemble the devices used by consoles, so players should be comfortable with the layouts. Gamers who don't want to sit too closely to their displays should consider wireless controllers that sync automatically with their systems. Even though videogame consoles typically come with a controller, a second device is necessary to play with another person. There are peripherals available for many of the major systems, like the Xbox 360, so gamers can play with their friends. Sensor controllers are also available for fans of motion-based games.", "parent_text": "PC Games & Accessories", "keyword_density": {"controllers": "1.6", "game": "3.8", "game controllers": "0.6"}, "department_id": 5},
{"department_text": "Software", "nr_products": 505, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/PC-Games/SubCategory/ID-372", "text": "PC Games", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Software/Store", "description_title": "PC Games", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/PC-Games-Accessories/Category/ID-275", "keyword_count": {"pc games": 2, "games": 11}, "description_wc": 314, "description_text": "While the video games available for various consoles may sometimes steal the spotlight, PC games still command the attention of millions of gamers all over the world. In the past year, numerous high-profile titles have been released to wide acclaim from both critics and casual players. That said, plenty of computer gamers are just as dedicated to the classics - if not more so - than the newest games available. Luckily, we've got classics, new favorites and everything in between. Fans of first-person shooters or similarly combat-heavy games will certainly have plenty of options on their hands. As far as genres go, these action-packed titles run the gamut from Renaissance-era swashbuckling and sci-fi dystopia to modern warfare and crime sagas. Additionally, intense role-playing games (RPGs) and real-time strategy (RTS) titles are available. Options in this category include games from established franchises like Diablo, Starcraft and Age of Empires to newer favorite series such as Fallout and The Elder Scrolls. However, those games aren't for everyone, and some are rated either T for Teen or M for Mature - intended for adults and teenagers of a certain age and maturity level. Parents, never fear - we've got plenty of other options for younger gamers and those uninterested in combat. These also encompass a wide variety of genres, as you could be creating entire new worlds in games like The Sims, planning culinary domination in Restaurant Empire or testing your wits with puzzle- and gambling-themed titles. You'll even have no trouble finding sports games or options that are suitable for even the youngest players. Our wide stock and affordable pricing - many titles are under $20 and even some newer computer games are well below their original MSRP - guarantees you'll be able to find the PC games best suited to your tastes, as well as your wallet!", "parent_text": "PC Games & Accessories", "keyword_density": {"pc games": "1.3", "games": "3.5"}, "department_id": 5},
