{"department_text": "Software", "nr_products": 133, "level": 0, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Graphic-Design/SubCategory/ID-376", "text": "Graphic & Design", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Software/Store", "description_title": "Digital Imaging And Editing Software", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Software/Store", "keyword_count": {"digital imaging and editing software": 4, "software": 7, "editing": 9, "editing software": 5, "digital": 5}, "description_wc": 298, "description_text": "With digital imaging and editing software, even the novice user can improve photographs and create interesting graphics. Professionals are fond of Adobe Photoshop and InDesign, but others find that they take too much time to learn or cost too much for the average home user. Fortunately, here at Newegg, you'll find all sorts of image editing software for all your creative needs. Less expensive digital imaging and editing software programs are not always less than adequate. Some offer great value and may or may not be easier to use. Mid-level programs contain more features than the basics yet are easier to learn than advanced programs like Photoshop. However, if you are designing documents that will be commercially printed and need color separation, make sure the software supports CMYK. PaintShop Pro is one example of a mid-level program that is affordable enough for the average user and easier to learn than Photoshop. Graphics Suites with Digital Imaging and Editing Software Programs Suites of image editing programs will help you with vector-based drawing and pixel-based image editing. Some come with organizational tools that help you categorize your photos, mark them for editing and printing, as well as improve them with color correction and other effects. You'll have creative control as well as an easy time learning how to use the software. You can also turn your photos into slide shows or video productions to share with family and friends. CorelDraw Graphics Suite is one such suite that competes very well with Photoshop and Illustrator. It helps you with image editing, digital painting, Web graphics, animation, and vector drawing. Keep in mind that many of these digital imaging and editing software programs also have plug-ins available so you can add helpful features to them.", "parent_text": "Software", "keyword_density": {"digital imaging and editing software": "6.7", "editing software": "3.4", "editing": "3.0", "digital": "1.7", "software": "2.3"}, "department_id": 5},
