{"department_text": "Home & Outdoors", "nr_products": 612, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Air-Conditioners/SubCategory/ID-718", "text": "Air Conditioners", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Home-Outdoors/Store?name=Home-Outdoors", "description_title": "Air Conditioners", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/A-Cs-Fans/Category/ID-106", "keyword_count": {"air conditioners": 4, "air": 8}, "description_wc": 312, "description_text": "Even with the best technology it's impossible to predict the weather. Warm fronts can sweep through one day, but then later that night you could see record low temperatures. With something as unpredictable as the climate, it's best to be prepared for any possibility. Installing air conditioners can keep any space comfortable, no matter what the conditions are outside. If your home or office is too warm, you'll likely be uncomfortable, and you might be unable to relax because you can't cool down or stop sweating. AC units can regulate the temperature and let you breathe easy. Air conditioners do more than keep a room cool. The machines circulate air and filter out pollutants like smoke, allergens and dust, so the air is cleaner than it would be if you used a fan. This can also help eliminate airborne germs by taking them out of circulation, or at least sending them outside. Some units aren't powerful enough to filter air in multiple rooms, and not every consumer can afford to buy multiple ACs. Portable models or fans can provide the same functionality as those that sit in windows, while being easier to move. Most of these machines have wheels so they can be pushed from room to room with little effort. You can find more air conditioners online than you could in retail outlets. Stores carry limited stock, especially during the cooler months, and as such you won't always find the right model for your needs. Additionally, buying an AC from a digital storefront means the machine will be delivered right to your door so you don't have to carry it from the register to your car to your home. Air conditioners can make your home or office comfortable and cool. Instead of suffering through warmer days, you can enjoy controlled temperatures using your unit.", "parent_text": "A/Cs & Fans", "keyword_density": {"air conditioners": "2.6", "air": "2.6"}, "department_id": 8},
