{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 73, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Home-Theater-Projectors/SubCategory/ID-513", "text": "Home Theater Projectors", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Home Theater Projectors", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Projectors/Category/ID-343", "keyword_count": {"home theater": 5, "projectors": 2}, "description_wc": 337, "description_text": "Putting together a home theater system can be difficult. All the equipment needs to be compatible to give an audience the best viewing experience. Due to strides in technology, audio devices can make movies and television shows sound crystal clear, but a standard high-definition television's picture might lag behind a sound system's performance. Buying the best home theater projector could level the playing field. If you're going to be watching a great deal of programming, a projector might be easier on the eyes than an LCD or LED television. The devices are backlit to create a sharper image on screen, while sending light directly into your vision. This is what usually causes eye strain after watching for an extended period of time. Projectors are only directing light toward the screen, making it more comfortable to enjoy a movie marathon. There is more flexibility with a home theater projector, as well. Instead of having a television with a set size, a projector can be adjusted to fill bigger and smaller display areas. Moving the device further away from the screen creates a bigger image, while moving it closer shrinks it. This is a convenient adjustment for users who want to use their device in more than one room. It is important to note the minimum and maximum size settings on each projector, because picture quality will deteriorate if moved beyond those thresholds. You may want to consider the lamp life of a projector before making a purchase. Light bulbs don't last forever, so at some point you'll need to replace one in your device. Most projectors offer settings designed to lengthen a bulb's life, but these options may reduce viewing quality while cutting down on power consumption. It's important to consider all your needs before buying a home theater projector. Make sure you have figured out what you expect from the device and what you'll use it for, so you can buy the best one for your home theater.", "parent_text": "Projectors", "keyword_density": {"home theater": "3.0", "projectors": "0.6"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 176, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Sound-Cards/SubCategory/ID-57", "text": "Sound Cards", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Sound Cards", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Speakers-Headsets/Category/ID-37", "keyword_count": {"sound": 11, "sound cards": 5}, "description_wc": 300, "description_text": "All computers that can play audio already have sound cards. However, not all PCs come equipped with sound cards that can produce the type of audio you want. If you use a computer as a home theater, music player, or gaming system, it is ideal to have the capability for 5.1 surround sound. 5.1 means there are five speakers and one subwoofer. Sound cards send different audio signals to each of the five speakers, so the speakers all play a different portion of the overall sound. Rather than simply hearing the audio from a computer, a listener becomes immersed in whatever is playing. This intensifies the video gaming experience and enhances your enjoyment of music and movies. Sound Card Features to Look for If you plan on using a computer to record or play music, consider purchasing a sound card with MIDI. MIDI is a standard for connecting electronic musical instruments. Having MIDI is especially helpful to musicians who like to write and record their own songs. With the right software programs and a sound card with MIDI, it is possible for one musician to play five different instruments (one at a time) and then overlap the recordings together to make one song on the computer. Other important sound card specifications include whether or not the card has a microphone plug, and the operating systems that can read the card. It is especially important to check this latter detail if you are using an older operating system. Some of the newer sound cards only work with newer operating systems. Here at Newegg, we have dozens of sound cards that can transform your computer into a state-of-the-art stereo system. Our electronics are sold at discounted prices, so you will find quality products at great values on our website.", "parent_text": "Speakers & Headsets", "keyword_density": {"sound": "3.7", "sound cards": "3.3"}, "department_id": 1},
{"nr_products": 158932, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Posters/SubCategory/ID-2232", "text": "Posters", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Office-Products-Point-of-Sale/Store/ID-133", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Room-Accessories/Category/ID-683", "parent_text": "Room Accessories", "department_text": "Office Products & Point of Sale", "department_id": 11},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 938, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Speakers/SubCategory/ID-60", "text": "Speakers", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Computer Speakers", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Speakers-Headsets/Category/ID-37", "keyword_count": {"speakers": 6, "computer": 6, "computer speakers": 3}, "description_wc": 311, "description_text": "It's not a given when you buy a new computer that it's going to have a sound card built in, and even if it does, there's no guarantee that it's going to be good. To get the best possible performance for streaming movies and video playback, as well as in-game audio experiences, it's essential that you get the best computer speakers to round out your machine. A standard set of side-by-side speakers will let you hear what's happening more clearly than using an onboard sound device. Without a tool like this, you may not get any audio with your playback at all, so this should be considered a basic purchase to go along with upgrading a keyboard and mouse. If you want a real experience with your media, try purchasing a heftier system. Something with a subwoofer and additional high-powered speakers can make it feel like you have a surround sound experience in your computer chair. Purchasing a speaker system also means considering how these will be connected. Some systems have USB hook-ups or other plugs and cables that won't require as many dedicated sockets, but there are expanders and other solutions to increase the maximum number of USB devices you can have going at once. Some devices will also be able to pull power right from the computer they're attached to, but in some cases they have a dedicated power supply that will need its own wall outlet. You may need to buy a separate power strip on top of speakers to make sure the entire system will function correctly. Buying the best computer speakers will ensure high-quality gaming and viewing from your machine. While devices come equipped in some cases with onboard sound capability, these tools can't compare to a system of computer speakers.", "parent_text": "Speakers & Headsets", "keyword_density": {"speakers": "1.9", "computer": "1.9", "computer speakers": "1.9"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 466, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Business-Projectors/SubCategory/ID-42", "text": "Business Projectors", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Business Projectors", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Projectors/Category/ID-343", "keyword_count": {"business": 2, "projectors": 5, "business projectors": 1}, "description_wc": 119, "description_text": "Use this link for more on Business Projectors in our Learning Center Newegg.com offers a rich selection of projectors using LCD or DLP and from mainstream to professional.We carry projectors from Epson, InFocus, Mitsubishi, Sony, NEC and others. These days, projectors come in a wide range of resolutions and luminosities, for small offices or large lecture halls! Home and business users alike will be able to find projectors that fit and function perfectly both for the office and the home and enjoy maximum visual quality and impact as well as enhanced work efficiency. WARNING: The products listed on this page may contain chemicals known to the State of California to cause cancer, or birth defects or other reproductive harm.", "parent_text": "Projectors", "keyword_density": {"business projectors": "1.7", "projectors": "4.2", "business": "1.7"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 176, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Sound-Cards/SubCategory/ID-57", "text": "Sound Cards", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Sound Cards", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Sound-Cards/Category/ID-36", "keyword_count": {"sound": 11, "sound cards": 5}, "description_wc": 300, "description_text": "All computers that can play audio already have sound cards. However, not all PCs come equipped with sound cards that can produce the type of audio you want. If you use a computer as a home theater, music player, or gaming system, it is ideal to have the capability for 5.1 surround sound. 5.1 means there are five speakers and one subwoofer. Sound cards send different audio signals to each of the five speakers, so the speakers all play a different portion of the overall sound. Rather than simply hearing the audio from a computer, a listener becomes immersed in whatever is playing. This intensifies the video gaming experience and enhances your enjoyment of music and movies. Sound Card Features to Look for If you plan on using a computer to record or play music, consider purchasing a sound card with MIDI. MIDI is a standard for connecting electronic musical instruments. Having MIDI is especially helpful to musicians who like to write and record their own songs. With the right software programs and a sound card with MIDI, it is possible for one musician to play five different instruments (one at a time) and then overlap the recordings together to make one song on the computer. Other important sound card specifications include whether or not the card has a microphone plug, and the operating systems that can read the card. It is especially important to check this latter detail if you are using an older operating system. Some of the newer sound cards only work with newer operating systems. Here at Newegg, we have dozens of sound cards that can transform your computer into a state-of-the-art stereo system. Our electronics are sold at discounted prices, so you will find quality products at great values on our website.", "parent_text": "Sound Cards", "keyword_density": {"sound": "3.7", "sound cards": "3.3"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 227, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Microphones/SubCategory/ID-122", "text": "Microphones", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "USB Microphones", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Speakers-Headsets/Category/ID-37", "keyword_count": {"microphones": 2, "usb": 4}, "description_wc": 297, "description_text": "Ever want to talk to somebody on the other side of the world but yelling at your computer screen just doesn't seem to work? Paying for an international call isn't necessary if you have a USB mic for your PC or laptop, making talking to anyone around the world as easy as turning on the device. These gadgets connect quickly and easily, are functional with any computer and provide unlimited high-quality audio to anyone you can connect with. These are also handy for online gaming with programs like Ventrillo, which allow for in-game communication, so long as you have the right technology on your end. Built-in microphones just don't offer the same quality as an external USB microphone, with enhanced clarity and sound customization that gives them superior performance to a base-level device. If you've ever wanted to do audio and sound work with your computer or electrical instruments, these are essential for getting studio-grade results. The more upscale models still offer the same plug-and-play connectivity, but with automatic level adjustment, analog controls and signal muting, some rival even professional-grade tools. A USB microphone of high caliber frees you from the anchor of a computer, letting you set it up with a wired or wireless connection to provide the best possible customization and function. Whether you're chatting with a friend on Skype, owning noobs in World of Warcraft or cutting a new album with your garage band, microphones that come attached to your computer just won't give you the same level of performance that a USB microphone can provide. With dozens of options for quality, clarity and control, there's no limit to how far you can take your voice using these devices.", "parent_text": "Speakers & Headsets", "keyword_density": {"microphones": "0.7", "usb": "1.3"}, "department_id": 1},
