{"department_text": "Office Products & Point of Sale", "nr_products": 171, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Voice-Recorders/SubCategory/ID-374", "text": "Voice Recorders", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Office-Products-Point-of-Sale/Store/ID-133", "description_title": "Voice Recorders", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Office-Machines/Category/ID-669", "keyword_count": {"recorders": 6, "voice": 7, "voice recorders": 2}, "description_wc": 465, "description_text": "Do you like to record thoughts and ideas as they come to you, rather than trying to remember them later? Writing them down on the go can be troublesome, especially if you are in a moving vehicle. Voice recorders are the perfect way to record your brilliant ideas without the need for cassette tapes or writing instruments. You can record memos, business meetings, an audio journal, and your phone conversations with these. Instead of storing the information on tape, the machines store them in digital formats. You can then transfer them to your computer to play them back or archive them, or send the audio files to other people through email. If you only need occasional voice recordings or basic functionality, a PDA or MP3 player with voice recording capability will probably suit your needs. However, if you're someone who needs to record conversations, you're better off with a dedicated digital voice recorder. Browse our site to find a large selection and the lowest prices on digital voice recording devices. While smartphones can do almost everything, their generalized functionality prevents the devices from excelling at some tasks. In addition, they have limited storage, and media files like recordings require large amounts of space. Content can easily be lost amid all of the documents stored on such devices, meaning that valuable information could be all but inaccessible. Additionally, some recorders have over 4GB of memory, meaning they can hold sizable libraries. Digital voice recorders only store audio files and can easily be connected to computers to export all documents. Some of these devices are equipped with built-in USB drives allowing you to easily save your notes once you're done recording. These specific models don't require wires, so they're more convenient to use while on the go. Sometimes you'll need to listen to something immediately, so reliable playback is a necessity. There are recorders with speakers and headphone jacks so you can listen to everything instantly without allowing anyone else to hear. Recorders feature strong battery life, so you never have to worry about them dying at an inopportune time. For instance, if you're recording a lecture, you shouldn't worry that you'll miss the conclusion because of a dead battery. Some audiophiles quickly notice the poor quality, especially in digital devices, and prefer analog gadgets. As an alternative, cassette recorders are also available. Some may argue that tapes are inefficient because they don't have large storage capacities, though tapes can be recycled so you don't have to frequently buy new ones. Whether you need to listen in on a business meeting after its conclusion or take personal notes throughout the day, a voice recorder may be one of the best possible gadgets for your job.", "parent_text": "Office Machines", "keyword_density": {"voice recorders": "0.9", "voice": "1.5", "recorders": "1.3"}, "department_id": 11},
