{"department_text": "Office Products & Point of Sale", "nr_products": 1738, "level": -3, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Barcode-Scanners/SubCategory/ID-583", "text": "Barcode Scanners", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Office-Products-Point-of-Sale/Store/ID-133", "description_title": "Barcode Scanners", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Scanners/Category/ID-209", "keyword_count": {"barcode scanners": 4, "barcode": 6, "scanners": 5}, "description_wc": 289, "description_text": "The point of sale (POS) terminal is one of the most important locations in every business, whether it's a multinational chain or a local convenience store. It's inefficient for employees to manually enter every Universal Product Code (UPC). If customers have large purchase orders, it may take awhile for those transactions to be completed. Barcode scanners can simplify the entire process and save time during checkouts. These devices read barcodes and enter the product information directly to your registers. Employees simply wave the readers over items to check the prices. Every POS terminal is different and there are various scanner models for every system. USB barcode scanners can be used with almost every register. As long you have an available USB port you can sync the reader to your system and start ringing items. Employees shouldn't struggle with their hardware. Small problems can cause delays that frustrate customers who are tired of waiting. If a scanner's cord is tangled, associates have to stop helping patrons and untie the knots. Wireless barcode scanners are easy to use and don't require any additional steps to sync with POS terminals. Scanners have many advantages over entering prices or UPCs for every purchase. For example, if your employees manually enter item totals, there's no way to track inventory. Barcode scanners can help connect your registers to your stockroom so you can monitor which products are selling quickly and should be restocked soon. Barcode readers also help employees complete more transactions. Associates only need to press a button to scan an item through. Additionally, workers can interact with patrons and deliver stronger customer service because staffers don't have to read long codes and type them repeatedly.", "parent_text": "Scanners", "keyword_density": {"barcode scanners": "2.8", "barcode": "2.1", "scanners": "1.7"}, "department_id": 11},
{"department_text": "Office Products & Point of Sale", "nr_products": 316, "level": -3, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Document-Scanners/SubCategory/ID-634", "text": "Document Scanners", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Office-Products-Point-of-Sale/Store/ID-133", "description_title": "Scanners", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Scanners/Category/ID-209", "keyword_count": {"scanners": 5}, "description_wc": 151, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Scanners in our Learning Center Providing a world of digital imaging possibilities right at your fingertips, a scanner digitizes photo prints or other printed materials onto your computer for further manipulation or long-term archiving. You will be able to view the scanned pictures on the computer monitor or on a TV, or share them with friends and family via email. Scanners will also translate and transfer printed or handwritten documents and books into computer editable and searchable text for the utmost in home and office convenience. You can get document scanners that will scan hundreds of pages, on both sides, at speed. There are scanners especially for anything large-format artwork down to ones just for scanning business cards, or even scanning 35mm slides, filmstrips or negatives. Newegg carries scanners from Canon, Epson, HP, Plustek, Fujitsu, Visioneer, Kodak, Microtek, and many, many more!", "parent_text": "Scanners", "keyword_density": {"scanners": "3.3"}, "department_id": 11},
