{"nr_products": 571, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Card-Readers/SubCategory/ID-69", "text": "Card Readers", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Flash-Memory-Readers/Category/ID-324", "description_wc": 43, "description_text": "WARNING: Products with exposed solder may contain lead, a chemical known to the State of California to cause cancer, birth defects and other reproductive harm. Please wash hands after handling internal components and motherboards and avoid inhalation of fumes if heating the solder.", "parent_text": "Flash Memory & Readers", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 6203, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/USB-Flash-Drives/SubCategory/ID-522", "text": "USB Flash Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Flash Drives", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Flash-Memory-Readers/Category/ID-324", "keyword_count": {"flash": 5, "flash drives": 2}, "description_wc": 326, "description_text": "Not everyone wants every file they've ever created available in the cloud. It can put data at risk - not just from hackers or spammers or nosey bosses, but with some providers offering shady terms, you could lose the intellectual rights to anything uploaded. Having a portable memory drive means you don't have to sacrifice mobility for security, though, making flash drives an ideal solution for business people on the go. These are great to have when traveling abroad, too. If you should happen to need a secure link to personal data, are operating outside your network range or should lose your valuables, you can keep a flash drive handy containing ID and serial numbers for personal devices. To ensure this information isn't stolen as well, having a locked flash drive can keep anyone from viewing your files should the drive fall into the wrong hands. Tiny and portable, they easily slip into a pants or coat pocket, in a computer bag or purse, and come in a variety of shapes and sizes. External keypads add an additional level of security to portable memory, meaning a viewer must first input a numerical code to gain access to files. These in turn can be encrypted and password protected, deterring serious threats to personal security. Flash drives are also cost-effective. You can securely store a few dozen gigabytes of data for less than $30, and these devices range in storage capacity, price and overall size - equal to the amount you're willing to invest. Some even have special features like lanyards, locks, belt clips and key fobs to make them easier to carry and keep track of. Having a way to handle and maintain personal information is essential in a digital age, but not everyone wants the world to be privy to their data. For that purpose, having a flash drive to securely store files at home or on the go is a perfect solution.", "parent_text": "Flash Memory & Readers", "keyword_density": {"flash": "1.5", "flash drives": "1.2"}, "department_id": 1},
