{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 55, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Water-Liquid-Cooling/SubCategory/ID-575", "text": "Water / Liquid Cooling", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Water Cooling for PCs", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Fans-PC-Cooling/Category/ID-11", "keyword_count": {"water": 11, "water cooling": 4, "cooling": 11}, "description_wc": 231, "description_text": "Water cooling is an alternative to using air cooling to remove the heat from computer components. The CPU can produce a lot of heat and is kept within a preset level by thermal sensors. Watercooling is often used to remove the heat above that which the air cooling is able to handle. The use of this type of cooling is especially popular among overclockers. Water cooling is much quieter than the air cooled systems. In addition to computer processing units, it is used on graphics processing units, and some hard drives. You will find everything you need for cooling with water at newegg.com. We have a wide selection of water cooling systems for Intel, AMD. Buy Water Cooling Supplies and Systems Online A fanless system includes the radiator, water pump, and reservoir. It is compatible with the Intel ,and many of the AMD combinations. Pay close attention to the requirements for the type of water to be used with the cooling system. Distilled water or special coolant may be required for long-lasting use. Some of the cooling systems are designed with quick connect capabilities and a transparent display to observe the movement of the water. The material of many of the systems that cool with water is made of pure copper and aluminum. Real time temperature reading is available on many of the units for quick monitoring of the system.", "parent_text": "Fans & PC Cooling", "keyword_density": {"water": "4.8", "water cooling": "3.5", "cooling": "4.8"}, "department_id": 1},
