{"nr_products": 690, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/External-Enclosures/SubCategory/ID-92", "text": "External Enclosures", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Hard-Drives/Category/ID-15", "description_wc": 124, "description_text": "External Enclosures Adding additional external storage space to your system helps protect your data and allows you to transfer it from one system to another. You can take former internal drives, put them in a new FireWire (IEEE 1394), USB, IDE, SATA/eSATA or other enclosure, and take your data with you. You can find enclosures for 1.8\" drives, 2.5\" drives, 3.5\" drives and 5.25\" drives, made from aluminum, plastic or other metal, and in a variety of colors. We offer enclosures from Crucial, OKGEAR, AcomData, EAGLE TECH, Enermax, Powmax, Addonics Technologies, Rosewill, GWC, Sabrent, AMC, ICY DOCK, Silverstone, Antec, INOI, STARTECH, IOGEAR, Syba, i-rocks, TAGAN, Kingwin, Thermaltake, Belkin, Koutech, Transcend, Vantec, Bytecc, Macally, Cooler Master, Mapower, XION, CoolMax, MASSCOOL and Zonet.", "parent_text": "Hard Drives", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"nr_products": 46, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Product/ProductList.aspx?Submit=ENE&DEPA=0&Order=BESTMATCH&Description=PPSSWPOSSNLEEK&name=Refurbished-Hard-Drives", "text": "Refurbished Hard Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Hard-Drives/Category/ID-15", "parent_text": "Hard Drives", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 101, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Mac-Hard-Drives/SubCategory/ID-552", "text": "Mac Hard Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "External Hard Drives for Macs", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Hard-Drives/Category/ID-15", "keyword_count": {"external hard": 2, "hard": 6, "drives": 2, "external": 3}, "description_wc": 313, "description_text": "Mac users need to sync an external hard drive with their computer to use Time Machine, Apple's built-in file backup system. Shoppers can find and choose the right Mac hard drive by thinking about storage and portability needs. To figure out what size hard drive you should buy, think about how much computing you do each day and how many files you save. If you're a heavy user, consider buying a drive with terabytes (TB) of available storage. You'll be able to save an entire system to a device with that much room, so if you need a new computer, you will be able to reinstall everything as it was previously. These units are beneficial to people who work in creative industries and have libraries that are too expansive for a single Mac external hard drive. For example, a photographer who has hundreds of thousands of pictures saved on his or her desktop won't be able to back everything up with a smaller unit. Casual consumers should consider drives with a few hundred gigabytes (GB) of space. Buying a device with TBs of data storage would result in a great deal of wasted space for users who only have a couple thousand files that need to be saved. If you plan on bringing your external Mac hard drive everywhere you go, you'll want to purchase a unit that is light and damage-resistant. Some drives are smaller than most tablets, while other devices are large enough to be confused with video game consoles. If you're prone to damaging your gadgets, consider a drive with pads and shock protectors to defend against significant bumps and bruises. Time Machine is a convenient program to help ensure that every file is saved, and buying the right Mac hard drive can help Mac users make the most of the program.", "parent_text": "Hard Drives", "keyword_density": {"external hard": "1.3", "hard": "1.9", "drives": "0.6", "external": "1.0"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Internal-Hard-Drives/Category/ID-338", "text": "Internal Hard Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Internal Hard Drive", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Hard-Drives/Category/ID-15", "keyword_count": {"internal hard drive": 5, "hard": 20, "drive": 21, "hard drive": 18}, "description_wc": 519, "description_text": "Much in the same way that the human body is defined by the brain inside of it, computers are judged often by their hard drive . The hard drive is the epicenter of the computer, providing processing power and storage for the people who use them. Simply put, computing as we know it would be impossible without them. But, like all hardware that has moving parts, hard drives can wear down with time and become unusable. When this occurs, replacement is necessary. It may also be that the hard drive that came standard with a new PC . just is not doing the job it needs to and requires an upgrade. Internal hard drives are available for purchase that can fit any need or desire, be it better graphics or a total system overhaul. In order to maximize computer performance, hard drives should be periodically evaluated in terms of user satisfaction and physical condition. Options of internal hard drive There are countless options when seeking out a new internal hard drive. Newegg has a large selection of products that will meet your needs. Many of the usual big names like HP , Lenovo , Toshiba , ASUS and Dell all have entries in the market. Western Digital and Seagate are also very popular brands of internal hard drive, including popular models such as WD Velociraptor and the Seagate Terascale Hard Drive. Lifespan of a hard drive The reality of technology is that all hardware has an expiration date, and hard drives are no exception. Generally speaking, if a hard drive is in constant use, then the three or four year mark is generally where device failure will start to crop up. There is some debate regarding this, as drives running for as long as eight years have been reported to still function effectively. That all being said, if a computer is put to use long enough, then there will definitely come a time when it needs to be replaced. This is all dependent, however, on what it is used for and how frequently it is put to work. Putting old hard drives to good use In many situations, however, hard drives need only be replaced because they are insufficient for what they are needed for. These old drives might still be in perfect working order, but something else is required for optimal performance. If a desktop computer has an extra drive bay, the new hard drive can be installed to work in tandem with the old one, providing a little extra storage space or performance power. For the laptop users or even the more DIY-minded, old internal hard drives can even be converted into external storage with the installation of a USB enclosure. If there is no extra space, these still-useful devices can be donated to schools or non-profits that might be able to use them. It is advised that a full, comprehensive wipe of the hard drive is performed before being handed over to someone else, however. After all, nobody wants their bank information to inadvertently end up somewhere that it is not supposed to.", "parent_text": "Hard Drives", "keyword_density": {"internal hard drive": "2.9", "hard": "3.9", "drive": "4.1", "hard drive": "7.0"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 389, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Controllers-RAID-Cards/SubCategory/ID-410", "text": "Controllers / RAID Cards", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Hard Drive Controllers", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Hard-Drives/Category/ID-15", "keyword_count": {"controllers": 4, "hard": 16, "drive": 21, "hard drive controllers": 1, "hard drive": 13}, "description_wc": 306, "description_text": "Hard drive controllers do exactly what they sound like: control your computer's hard disk. They are the circuitry involved in running hard disks and getting them to do what they are supposed to. On IDE drives, the hard drive controller is actually part of the drive. In older hard drives, controllers were separate boards. With a typical IDE hard drive, you can have up to four devices directly connected to the motherboard. An example would be the hard drive, floppy drive, CD-ROM, and DVD drives. If all the spots are used up, you would need to purchase another hard drive controller card. Sometimes the hard drive controller can fail and you will need to replace it. You need the same type of controller as your hard drive. For example, IDE drives are only compatible with IDE controllers, and SCSI drives need SCSI controllers. Hard Drive Controller Errors If you get an error that says \"HDD controller failure\" upon booting your computer, it usually means the hard disk drive (HDD) controller has failed. Sometimes, you will get a 1701 error, which means the hard drive controller and the drive are having trouble communicating. This might be due to a loose connection. The best way to avoid losing data is to prevent loss by backing up. With the low cost of external hard drives this is a ideal solution. By making regular copies of your important files, or by cloning your entire hard drive setup, you'll save yourself a ton of trouble in the event that your hard drive ever goes bad. WARNING: Products with exposed solder may contain lead, a chemical known to the State of California to cause cancer, birth defects and other reproductive harm. Please wash hands after handling internal components and motherboards and avoid inhalation of fumes if heating the solder.", "parent_text": "Hard Drives", "keyword_density": {"controllers": "1.3", "hard": "5.2", "drive": "6.9", "hard drive controllers": "1.0", "hard drive": "8.5"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Network-Attached-Storage-NAS/Category/ID-241", "text": "Network Attached Storage (NAS)", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Network-attached storage (NAS)", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Hard-Drives/Category/ID-15", "keyword_count": {"network": 11, "nas": 8, "storage nas": 3, "storage": 15, "network attached storage": 4, "network attached storage nas": 1}, "description_wc": 431, "description_text": "You want cloud, you do, really, but it's got all those other people there. All those threats. All those data security issues. You want the cloud, but you're afraid of DropBox, and that's understandable, but you want your own cloud. In a world where we can have everything customized, from our electronics to our cars, pets, homes, clothes and our own bodies, there's no reason you can't have a storage solution that's as cheap, effective and accessible as the cloud without worrying about someone else's terms of service or use agreements. That's why network attached storage is such a handy product for those in the know. Network-attached storage (NAS) is data storage or a data storage device, such as a hard drive or RAID array, connected to a computer network, providing data access to different network clients. When you have a few computers working in tandem, it's essential that they have access to the same collaborative tools and files necessary to get projects completed. An enterprise-level solution like NAS gives all these machines access to the same documents whenever they need, so long as they can access the network. Wired or wireless options are possible with network attached storage. Wi-Fi capable, internet-ready and able to house a few disks worth of data (which you'll likely have to buy separately), these can be isolated from the online world if you so choose, or made accessible if you see fit. They allow not only sharing of key information but also devices like scanners, printers and fax machines. NAS Systems NAS systems contain one or more hard disks, often arranged into logical, redundant storage containers or RAID arrays (redundant arrays of inexpensive/independent disks). NAS devices remove the responsibility of file serving from other servers on the network. NAS provides both storage and file systems. This is often contrasted with SAN (Storage Area Network) devices, which provide only block-based storage and leaves filesystem concerns on the \"client\" side. SAN protocols include SCSI, Fibre Channel, iSCSI, ATA over Ethernet, or HyperSCSI. Flexibility & Scalability Fit for personal or small business use, network attached storage is flexible, scalable and ready for whatever in-house storage and devices you can throw at it. Reasonably priced, they even outmatch some online vendor contracts and can outlast an outage, too. Newegg has Network storage / NAS from the world\u2019s best Network storage / NAS manufacturers, including Buffalo, Cavalry, D-Link, Hammer Storage, Intel, iomega, LaCie, Linksys, Maxtor, Netgear, QNAP, Thecus, Western Digital and Synology.", "parent_text": "Hard Drives", "keyword_density": {"network": "2.6", "network attached storage": "2.8", "storage nas": "1.4", "storage": "3.5", "nas": "1.9", "network attached storage nas": "0.9"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Store/Category.aspx?Category=34&name=CPUs-Processors", "text": "CPUs / Processors", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "CPUs/Processors", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Fans-PC-Cooling/Category/ID-11", "keyword_count": {"processors": 9, "cpus processors": 2}, "description_wc": 256, "description_text": "CPU( is also known as Central Processing Unit or Processor) is the most important component of a computer. CPU/Processor is used to explain computer instructions and process software data in computer. CPU/Processor can be divided into desktop processors , mobile processors and server processors. Intel and AMD are the most famous CPU/Processor manufacturers. They have released single-core / dual-core processors / quad-core processors / six-Core Processors / eight-core processors series. The most critical component in any computer is the CPU (Central Processing Unit), where all of the \"computing\" actually occurs. It interprets and executes instructions and data contained in software programs, incoming signals from network sources, and the commands of its user. The more generic term 'processor' is often used to refer to a CPU, as well. The power and performance of the CPU is the prime determinants of a computer's overall performance. Newegg is proud to offer a wide variety of CPUs/Processors from Intel and AMD, such as Core i7 , Core i5, Core i3, Pentium, Celeron ; FX-Series, A-Series APU, Athlon, Sempron, Phenom ; Xeon E5 family, Xeon E3 family, Xeon ; Opteron series, etc. Find the CPUs/Processors you are looking for at Newegg.com, and enjoy the smoothest, most pleasurable online shopping experience around! WARNING: Products with exposed solder may contain lead, a chemical known to the State of California to cause cancer, birth defects and other reproductive harm. Please wash hands after handling internal components and motherboards and avoid inhalation of fumes if heating the solder.", "parent_text": "Fans & PC Cooling", "keyword_density": {"processors": "3.6", "cpus processors": "1.6"}, "department_id": 1},
{"level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/External-Hard-Drives/Category/ID-344", "text": "External Hard Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Hard-Drives/Category/ID-15", "parent_text": "Hard Drives", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"nr_products": 49, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Presentation-Devices/SubCategory/ID-796", "text": "Presentation Devices", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Input-Devices/Category/ID-29", "parent_text": "Input Devices", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 141, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/PC-Game-Controllers/SubCategory/ID-123", "text": "PC Game Controllers", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Game Controllers", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Input-Devices/Category/ID-29", "keyword_count": {"controllers": 5, "game": 12, "game controllers": 1}, "description_wc": 312, "description_text": "Whether you use a PC or a console, the right game controller can make all the difference when you're playing your favorite titles. It can be frustrating to navigate digital worlds with mouse clicks and keyboard commands. Some controllers are meant for general use and can be frustrating to use during certain games that require other peripheral devices. Fortunately, there are game controllers available for almost every scenario and game genre. For racing fans, pedals and steering wheels may be comfortable to use while playing. Instead of relying on buttons and triggers, gamers can control their vehicles just like their own cars. Complicated commands don't have to be entered with these driving simulators, as players can hit the gas as soon as they're ready to move. If you're a fan of aerial action or are using a flight simulation game, it may be best to use equipment similar to that found in many cockpits. The best of these peripherals are accurate recreations of the tools and gauges that pilots use while in flight. There are even gadgets that act as radar systems for on-screen action, so gamers learn to focus on more than on-screen action. PC game lovers don't have to restrict themselves to their keyboards any longer, as desktop controllers are available. Many of these devices are resemble the devices used by consoles, so players should be comfortable with the layouts. Gamers who don't want to sit too closely to their displays should consider wireless controllers that sync automatically with their systems. Even though videogame consoles typically come with a controller, a second device is necessary to play with another person. There are peripherals available for many of the major systems, like the Xbox 360, so gamers can play with their friends. Sensor controllers are also available for fans of motion-based games.", "parent_text": "Input Devices", "keyword_density": {"controllers": "1.6", "game": "3.8", "game controllers": "0.6"}, "department_id": 1},
{"level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/SSDs/Category/ID-119", "text": "SSDs", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Hard-Drives/Category/ID-15", "parent_text": "Hard Drives", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 12680, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Keyboards/SubCategory/ID-63", "text": "Keyboards", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Keyboards", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Input-Devices/Category/ID-29", "keyword_count": {"keyboards": 4}, "description_wc": 392, "description_text": "The keyboard is without a doubt one of the most important computer accessories available. The computer keyboard is an input device that sends commands and text inputs to the computer, and is the main interface that we use to communicate or control the computer in combination with the mouse. Unfortunately, not every computer's keyboard is comfortable and sturdy. Without these two characteristics, productivity may decline as working becomes a hassle and can even be painful. You may believe that your typing technique requires improvement, but more often than not faulty hardware is the root of your discomfort. Not every model has wrist supports and you can hurt your arms while you type without assistance. Ergonomic keyboards are designed to help you use your computer without any pain. These models have larger bases, letting you rest your wrists and palms while typing. Instead of uncomfortably hovering over your keyboard, your hands have the necessary support to prevent any strain and reduce the likelihood of developing physical ailments like carpal tunnel syndrome. Pads are commonly found on gaming keyboards as those are meant for more casual use. During a marathon game session, players must usually enter a great deal of key commands. With a standard keyboard, this can lead to pain or discomfort, as their hands continually move without support or rest. Some gaming models, by contrast, have features that can improve a gamer's performance as well. Wireless keyboards are also available - these ensure that users aren't tethered to their desks. If you have a large enough screen, you can use your device while sitting away from your computer. Working without wires also allows you to find a relaxed position, so you aren't confined to a single table. Buying a new keyboard can improve your typing proficiency, whether you're writing a term paper or playing a video game. The right device can raise your comfort levels while also making it easier to use your computer through key commands. Brands featured at Newegg include Microsoft, KeyTronic, Adesso, Logitech and many others. Available in multiple styles and versions you can find one to suit your unique needs rather it's multimedia, gaming, or just looking for the latest new thing. At Newegg you'll find what you need. Use this link for more information on Computer Keyboards in our Learning Center", "parent_text": "Input Devices", "keyword_density": {"keyboards": "1.0"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 227, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Microphones/SubCategory/ID-122", "text": "Microphones", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "USB Microphones", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Input-Devices/Category/ID-29", "keyword_count": {"microphones": 2, "usb": 4}, "description_wc": 297, "description_text": "Ever want to talk to somebody on the other side of the world but yelling at your computer screen just doesn't seem to work? Paying for an international call isn't necessary if you have a USB mic for your PC or laptop, making talking to anyone around the world as easy as turning on the device. These gadgets connect quickly and easily, are functional with any computer and provide unlimited high-quality audio to anyone you can connect with. These are also handy for online gaming with programs like Ventrillo, which allow for in-game communication, so long as you have the right technology on your end. Built-in microphones just don't offer the same quality as an external USB microphone, with enhanced clarity and sound customization that gives them superior performance to a base-level device. If you've ever wanted to do audio and sound work with your computer or electrical instruments, these are essential for getting studio-grade results. The more upscale models still offer the same plug-and-play connectivity, but with automatic level adjustment, analog controls and signal muting, some rival even professional-grade tools. A USB microphone of high caliber frees you from the anchor of a computer, letting you set it up with a wired or wireless connection to provide the best possible customization and function. Whether you're chatting with a friend on Skype, owning noobs in World of Warcraft or cutting a new album with your garage band, microphones that come attached to your computer just won't give you the same level of performance that a USB microphone can provide. With dozens of options for quality, clarity and control, there's no limit to how far you can take your voice using these devices.", "parent_text": "Input Devices", "keyword_density": {"microphones": "0.7", "usb": "1.3"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 1951, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Mice/SubCategory/ID-65", "text": "Mice", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Wireless Mice, Optical Mice, Laser Mice and Trackball Mice", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Input-Devices/Category/ID-29", "keyword_count": {"wireless": 4, "mice": 3}, "description_wc": 113, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Computer Mice in our Learning Center At Newegg you can choose from a massive selection of computer mice from industry leading manufacturers including wired and wireless products, as well as sleek space-saving designs for notebook computers and ergonomic mice for the utmost in user comfort and gaming performance regardless of hand-orientation. Brands featured at Newegg include Microsoft, Kensington, Logitech, Targus and others in configurations of RF wireless, Fast RF wireless, Bluetooth Wireless, and standard PS/2 and USB wired interfaces. With a mouse to fit every computer performance need Newegg has what you need. For more information, please see our Computer Mouse Buying Guide.", "parent_text": "Input Devices", "keyword_density": {"wireless": "3.5", "mice": "2.7"}, "department_id": 1},
{"nr_products": 35, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Memory-Chipset-Cooling/SubCategory/ID-572", "text": "Memory & Chipset Cooling", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Memory/Category/ID-17", "parent_text": "Memory", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 998, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Hubs/SubCategory/ID-26", "text": "Hubs", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "USB Hubs", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Input-Devices/Category/ID-29", "keyword_count": {"hubs": 1, "usb": 7}, "description_wc": 318, "description_text": "Some users do not have enough USB ports on their computers to support all of their peripheral devices. If a consumer wants to connect multiple accessories, they might have to choose between which ones have the most relevant functionality and which are expendable for the time being. This is an inconvenience for those who need their devices to work efficiently and accommodate all needs. If you have too many accessories and not enough docks, a USB hub will provide the additional support you need. A hub uses one USB port on the computer itself but provides multiple ports that link with other devices - much the way a power strip creates additional electrical outlets by working from one. After purchasing a network hub, every peripheral device can stay connected to a laptop. You can connect an external hard drive, DVD burner, printer and smartphone to a computer via a single USB connection and still have extra space for more accessories. Users can leave all their peripherals attached to the hub for more convenient connection and detachment. Instead of unplugging multiple items, consumers only have to remove a USB hub's plug. This is perfect for those who need their computers to travel, such as college students who bring their notebooks to class or workers who need their laptops in the office. There are different styles of plugs to meet the needs of every shopper. Some ports are large and have over 10 USB slots so they might be best utilized in a stationary environment, while others only feature a couple of access points for more mobile use. Other network hubs are just a series of wires so consumers don't have to carry a bulky device. Peripheral accessories help users enjoy their laptops' best features. A USB hub can provide the additional support necessary so that no one ever has to choose which device to use with which program.", "parent_text": "Input Devices", "keyword_density": {"hubs": "0.3", "usb": "2.2"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 672, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Headsets-Accessories/SubCategory/ID-707", "text": "Headsets & Accessories", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Headsets", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Input-Devices/Category/ID-29", "keyword_count": {"headsets": 4}, "description_wc": 287, "description_text": "Gamers see their hobby as serious business, so having the right tools to maximize playtime is essential. Nobody wants to mess around with desk microphones with unnecessary feedback or large computer speakers that garble in-game music and distort what other players are saying. Serious gaming requires serious headsets, and finding one that works best for you is what raises your in-game performance. Like standard pairs of headphones , headsets have a variety of styles and sizes. Some have bands that go over the top of the head, others wrap behind and still others do away with bands altogether and clip to ears to avoid stressing the temples. A wireless set may be more up a gamer's alley, as these relieve the exasperation a tethered headset can provide. The real added benefit of a headset comes from the onboard microphone, a feature that not all headsets provide but one that's worth looking for. This function gives you the ability to talk and listen without getting excessive feedback from keyboard or electronic activity, as well as reducing the amount of interference on your end so that other people in your conversation can hear you more easily. As any gamer knows, a successful raid relies partly on good communication, so it's essential that everyone in the party knows who you're dotting before someone kites the group. Headsets come in a variety of colors and styles, and picking the right one with the best additional features will depend on your preferences. Noise reducing, wireless or wired, with a slew of different wearing options and the ability to talk more easily while hammering on your keyboard, a headset is an integral part of successful online communication.", "parent_text": "Input Devices", "keyword_density": {"headsets": "1.4"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 636, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/KVM-Switches/SubCategory/ID-143", "text": "KVM Switches", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "KVM Switches", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Input-Devices/Category/ID-29", "keyword_count": {"kvm": 6, "kvm switches": 4}, "description_wc": 247, "description_text": "Suppose you have more than one computer in the same room but you do not have enough room for a second monitor. Or, you have a laptop and want to use it with your home computer's keyboard, mouse and monitor, without changing your current setup. The answer lies in a handy device called a KVM switch. KVM stands for keyboard, video, mouse. The keyboard, video, and mouse set collectively is called a \"console.\" KVM switches allow you to connect a console to more than one computer. You simply connect your console cables to the output jacks of the switch and connect the switch to the connections on your computer that the keyboard mouse and monitor would normally be plugged into. It's that simple. KVM Switches Let You Switch between Consoles To switch consoles, you just push a button on the switch and it allows you to use the other console. KVM switches save you money because you won't have to purchase separate keyboards, mice, and monitors for each computer you use. It makes it very easy when one person uses more than one computer at work, for example. They are also useful for server farms with one staff person accessing each computer periodically, one at a time. When buying KVM switches, it is important to fully understand your needs before you buy anything. Make sure the switch you choose will support your monitor refresh rates and resolution so that the signals are not degraded.", "parent_text": "Input Devices", "keyword_density": {"kvm": "2.4", "kvm switches": "3.2"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 128, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Graphics-Tablets/SubCategory/ID-296", "text": "Graphics Tablets", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Graphics Tablet", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Input-Devices/Category/ID-29", "keyword_count": {"graphics tablet": 2, "tablet": 8}, "description_wc": 319, "description_text": "Tablets have made computing easier and more convenient by combining the functionality of a laptop with the portability of an e-reader or smartphone. Some devices have been built for more specific functions, allowing consumers to buy a tablet that suits their individual needs. For artists and graphic designers, a drawing tablet might be the best option. These devices are basically digital sketchbooks. Instead of drawing a design or an image and then recreating it on a laptop, a graphics tablet comes equipped with software so users can create their artwork, save it and share the file with other devices via an internet or wired connection. There are pen tablets available for designers who aren't quite ready to make the leap to touchscreen technology. Most of these devices' screens are sensitive enough that they'll respond to the pen in natural way to create different shades, styles and lines. If you aren't comfortable with the pen that a tablet came packaged with, there are other peripherals available. You can shop around until you find the pen that feels most comfortable in your hand. There are replacement parts available for some pens, which could be useful if you're worried that you'll quickly wear out your drawing tool. Consumers who don't want to untangle wires every time they need to share a new file with another device should consider buying a wireless connection kit. A USB wireless connector enables sharing with any PC, even if the design tablet was not built with wireless sharing. Don't forget to buy a carrying case, so your device is well-protected during transport. Screens are very sensitive and will be susceptible to scratches and scuff marks if left exposed to the elements. A graphics tablet could be the perfect device for any artist who wants to work digitally but feels limited by the creation tools available on a computer.", "parent_text": "Input Devices", "keyword_density": {"graphics tablet": "1.3", "tablet": "2.5"}, "department_id": 1},
{"nr_products": 74, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Advanced-Computer-Eyewear/SubCategory/ID-774", "text": "Advanced Computer Eyewear", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Input-Devices/Category/ID-29", "parent_text": "Input Devices", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 101, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Mac-Hard-Drives/SubCategory/ID-552", "text": "Mac Hard Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "External Hard Drives for Macs", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/External-Hard-Drives/Category/ID-344", "keyword_count": {"external hard": 2, "hard": 6, "drives": 2, "external": 3}, "description_wc": 313, "description_text": "Mac users need to sync an external hard drive with their computer to use Time Machine, Apple's built-in file backup system. Shoppers can find and choose the right Mac hard drive by thinking about storage and portability needs. To figure out what size hard drive you should buy, think about how much computing you do each day and how many files you save. If you're a heavy user, consider buying a drive with terabytes (TB) of available storage. You'll be able to save an entire system to a device with that much room, so if you need a new computer, you will be able to reinstall everything as it was previously. These units are beneficial to people who work in creative industries and have libraries that are too expansive for a single Mac external hard drive. For example, a photographer who has hundreds of thousands of pictures saved on his or her desktop won't be able to back everything up with a smaller unit. Casual consumers should consider drives with a few hundred gigabytes (GB) of space. Buying a device with TBs of data storage would result in a great deal of wasted space for users who only have a couple thousand files that need to be saved. If you plan on bringing your external Mac hard drive everywhere you go, you'll want to purchase a unit that is light and damage-resistant. Some drives are smaller than most tablets, while other devices are large enough to be confused with video game consoles. If you're prone to damaging your gadgets, consider a drive with pads and shock protectors to defend against significant bumps and bruises. Time Machine is a convenient program to help ensure that every file is saved, and buying the right Mac hard drive can help Mac users make the most of the program.", "parent_text": "External Hard Drives", "keyword_density": {"external hard": "1.3", "hard": "1.9", "drives": "0.6", "external": "1.0"}, "department_id": 1},
