{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 505, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/All-Desktop-Hard-Drives/SubCategory/ID-14", "text": "All Desktop Hard Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Internal Hard Drives", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Internal-Hard-Drives/Category/ID-338", "keyword_count": {"internal hard drives": 3, "hard": 9, "drives": 4, "internal hard": 6}, "description_wc": 226, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Internal Hard Drives in our Learning Center Need more storage for your games, images, music and movies? An internal hard drive upgrade or a second drive may be what you are looking for. Internal hard drives are used as main storage in desktop PCs, workstations, and servers. Nowadays, small form factor internal hard drives are used in consumer electronic products like mp3 players and digital cameras as well. Regardless of your application, Newegg.com presents an extensive selection of internal hard drive products for you to choose from, from hard drive manufacturers like Western Digital, Seagate, HItachi, LaCie, Maxtor and others. Understanding Internal Hard Drive Specifications When selecting a hard drive, there are two main things to consider: speed and capacity. Budget permitting, always go for the fastest drive you can. Speed is measured using the RPM figure a faster rotational speed means greater performance, especially in games, but may cause greater heat and noise. The capacity, measured in GB (gigabytes), should depend on your own storage requirements. A higher capacity drive will invariably cost more than a lower capacity drive, so a balance must usually be struck between capacity and cost. In addition, the hard drive interface IDE, SATA, or SCSI determine a drives application: IDE and SATA for personal storage and SCSI for enterprise, mission critical storage.", "parent_text": "Internal Hard Drives", "keyword_density": {"internal hard drives": "4.0", "hard": "4.0", "drives": "1.8", "internal hard": "5.3"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 309, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/All-Laptop-Hard-Drives/SubCategory/ID-380", "text": "All Laptop Hard Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Laptop / Notebook Hard Drives", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Internal-Hard-Drives/Category/ID-338", "keyword_count": {"laptop notebook hard drives": 1, "hard drives": 2, "laptop": 2, "hard": 4, "drives": 4, "notebook hard": 2, "notebook": 4}, "description_wc": 135, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Laptop / Notebook Hard Drives in our Learning Center Looking for a replacement notebook hard drive or simply not satisfied with the performance of the original hard drive in your notebook computer? Newegg.com offers a large selection of notebook/laptop hard drives with storage capacities perfectly tailored to your requirements, as well as products that can contribute to higher levels of system performance for maximum enjoyment from your movies, pictures and games. Select from manufacturers such as Hitachi, Fujitsu, Seagate, Toshiba, Western Digital and Samsung with capacity limits ranging from 40GB to 320GB. Additionally, while most drives are SATA 1.5Gb/s we also carry a fair share of ATA-6 and SATA 3.0Gb/s drives too. Speed are in standard formats of 4200 RPM, 5400 RPM, and 7200 RPM.", "parent_text": "Internal Hard Drives", "keyword_density": {"laptop notebook hard drives": "3.0", "hard drives": "3.0", "laptop": "1.5", "hard": "3.0", "drives": "3.0", "notebook hard": "3.0", "notebook": "3.0"}, "department_id": 1},
