{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 9, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/CPU-Accessories/SubCategory/ID-151", "text": "CPU Accessories", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "CPU Accessories", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Store/Category.aspx?Category=34&name=CPUs-Processors", "keyword_count": {"accessories": 5, "cpu": 6, "cpu accessories": 4}, "description_wc": 252, "description_text": "You can get all the CPU accessories you need at Newegg. We sell thousands of products from hundreds of networking experts, including everything you need to maintain networking productivity. Hiccups are inevitable. Finding an affordable solution could mean the difference between fluid networking and interrupted workflow. In addition to an all-inclusive inventory of hardware, a wide selection of add-on accessories makes shopping at Newegg even easier. Inexpensive CPU Accessories Searching for a fan connector adapter? Without the right flow of air around your hardware, you could be risking performance and putting your data in jeopardy. You can find a generic connector (3-pin to 4-pin) for just a few dollars. Isn't maintaining the integrity of your information worth a few bucks? AMD backing plates are used in conjunction with a heatsink. These small yet extremely important CPU accessories are essential for smooth networking operations. Created by Swiftech, these plates are available in both bronze and chrome. Is your cooling fan not getting the job done? Perhaps you need a Coolmax sensitive fan adapter? Or better yet, a Thermaltake CPU ducting fan? These components will help increase airflow while minimizing the sound coming from your CPU. Newegg is the one-stop source for your CPU accessories. WARNING: Products with exposed solder may contain lead, a chemical known to the State of California to cause cancer, birth defects and other reproductive harm. Please wash hands after handling internal components and motherboards and avoid inhalation of fumes if heating the solder.", "parent_text": "CPUs / Processors", "keyword_density": {"cpu accessories": "3.2", "accessories": "2.0", "cpu": "2.4"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 99, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Processors-Servers/SubCategory/ID-727", "text": "Processors - Servers", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Intel and AMD CPUs / Processors", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Store/Category.aspx?Category=34&name=CPUs-Processors", "keyword_count": {"intel and amd": 1, "processors": 3, "cpus processors": 1}, "description_wc": 179, "description_text": "Use this link for more on CPUs / Processors in our Learning Center One of the most exciting components in the computer is the CPU (Central Processing Unit), which is essentially the brain of the computer. It interprets and executes instructions and data contained in software programs as well as the commands of its user. The more generic term 'processor' is often used to refer to a CPU as well. The power and performance of the CPU are the greatest determinants of a computer's overall performance. The CPU battlefield is dominated by two companies, Intel and AMD and their processors are forever pushing the performance of each other. Regardless of whether you are looking to place the CPU in a server, desktop, laptop or other mobile device Newegg has the right solution for you. We carry processors for multiple socket types and series ranging from Pentium's, Athlon's, Celeron's, Core 2's, Core Duo's, Dual Core, Quad Core, Xeon, Opteron, Phenom Sempron, Turion and more. For all your CPU / Processor needs Newegg has you covered.", "parent_text": "CPUs / Processors", "keyword_density": {"intel and amd": "1.7", "processors": "1.7", "cpus processors": "1.1"}, "department_id": 1},
{"nr_products": 571, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Card-Readers/SubCategory/ID-69", "text": "Card Readers", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Memory/Category/ID-17", "description_wc": 43, "description_text": "WARNING: Products with exposed solder may contain lead, a chemical known to the State of California to cause cancer, birth defects and other reproductive harm. Please wash hands after handling internal components and motherboards and avoid inhalation of fumes if heating the solder.", "parent_text": "Memory", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 4, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Processors-Mobile/SubCategory/ID-759", "text": "Processors - Mobile", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Intel and AMD CPUs / Processors", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Store/Category.aspx?Category=34&name=CPUs-Processors", "keyword_count": {"intel and amd": 1, "cpus": 7, "processors": 6, "amd": 5, "intel": 6, "cpus processors": 3}, "description_wc": 230, "description_text": "Use this link for more on CPUs / Processors in our Learning Center The most critical component in any computer is the CPU (Central Processing Unit), where all of the \"computing\" actually occurs. It interprets and executes instructions and data contained in software programs, incoming signals from network sources, and the commands of its user. The more generic term 'processor' is often used to refer to a CPU, as well. The power and performance of the CPU are the prime determinants of a computer's overall performance. Mobile CPUs also be called mobile processors, laptop CPUs or laptop processors. Mobile CPUs are designed to save power on portable computers. Mobile CPUs/Processors use lower voltages than desktop processors and have more \"sleep mode\" capability. Mobile CPUs/Processors can be throttled down to different power levels and/or sections of the chip can be turned off entirely when not in use. The two largest CPU / Processor manufacturers are Intel and AMD. Newegg offers the most popular mobile or laptop CPUs with the best prices. Intel Core 2 Duo T7500, Intel Core 2 Duo T9600, Intel Core 2 Duo T7700, Intel Core 2 Duo T9400, Intel Core 2 Duo T8300 are among our constant inventory. AMD Turion 64 MT32, AMD Turion 64 X2 TL-52, AMD Turion 64 MT34, and AMD Turion 64 X2 TL-56 round out the array Newegg carries.", "parent_text": "CPUs / Processors", "keyword_density": {"intel and amd": "1.3", "intel": "2.6", "processors": "2.6", "cpus": "3.1", "amd": "2.2", "cpus processors": "2.6"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 6203, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/USB-Flash-Drives/SubCategory/ID-522", "text": "USB Flash Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Flash Drives", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Memory/Category/ID-17", "keyword_count": {"flash": 5, "flash drives": 2}, "description_wc": 326, "description_text": "Not everyone wants every file they've ever created available in the cloud. It can put data at risk - not just from hackers or spammers or nosey bosses, but with some providers offering shady terms, you could lose the intellectual rights to anything uploaded. Having a portable memory drive means you don't have to sacrifice mobility for security, though, making flash drives an ideal solution for business people on the go. These are great to have when traveling abroad, too. If you should happen to need a secure link to personal data, are operating outside your network range or should lose your valuables, you can keep a flash drive handy containing ID and serial numbers for personal devices. To ensure this information isn't stolen as well, having a locked flash drive can keep anyone from viewing your files should the drive fall into the wrong hands. Tiny and portable, they easily slip into a pants or coat pocket, in a computer bag or purse, and come in a variety of shapes and sizes. External keypads add an additional level of security to portable memory, meaning a viewer must first input a numerical code to gain access to files. These in turn can be encrypted and password protected, deterring serious threats to personal security. Flash drives are also cost-effective. You can securely store a few dozen gigabytes of data for less than $30, and these devices range in storage capacity, price and overall size - equal to the amount you're willing to invest. Some even have special features like lanyards, locks, belt clips and key fobs to make them easier to carry and keep track of. Having a way to handle and maintain personal information is essential in a digital age, but not everyone wants the world to be privy to their data. For that purpose, having a flash drive to securely store files at home or on the go is a perfect solution.", "parent_text": "Memory", "keyword_density": {"flash": "1.5", "flash drives": "1.2"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 96, "level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Processors-Desktops/SubCategory/ID-343", "text": "Processors - Desktops", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Intel and AMD CPUs / Processors", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Store/Category.aspx?Category=34&name=CPUs-Processors", "keyword_count": {"intel and amd": 1, "processors": 3, "cpus processors": 1}, "description_wc": 183, "description_text": "Use this link for more on CPUs / Processors in our Learning Center One of the most exciting components in the computer is the CPU (Central Processing Unit), which is essentially the brain of the computer. It interprets and executes instructions and data contained in software programs as well as the commands of its user. The more generic term 'processor' is often used to refer to a CPU as well. The power and performance of the CPU are the greatest determinants of a computer's overall performance. The CPU battlefield is dominated by two companies, Intel and AMD and their processors are forever pushing the performance of each other. Regardless of whether you are looking to place the CPU in a server, desktop, laptop or other mobile device Newegg has the right solution for you. We carry processors for multiple socket types and series ranging from Core i7 , Core i5, Core i3, Pentium, Celeron ; FX-Series, A-Series APU, Athlon, Sempron, Phenom ; Xeon E5 family, Xeon E3 family, Xeon ; Opteron series, etc. For all your CPU / Processor needs Newegg has you covered.", "parent_text": "CPUs / Processors", "keyword_density": {"intel and amd": "1.7", "processors": "1.7", "cpus processors": "1.1"}, "department_id": 1},
