{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 1397, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Mouse-Pads-Accessories/SubCategory/ID-202", "text": "Mouse Pads & Accessories", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Mouse Pads", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Keyboards-Mice/Category/ID-234", "keyword_count": {"pads": 4, "mouse": 10, "mouse pads": 3}, "description_wc": 283, "description_text": "Not every surface is as conducive to mouse usage as you'd like. Sometimes there's no free tabletop space, or things are a bit sticky, or you want to use a mouse with a mobile device but your lap isn't the best for laser mice. Sometimes you may just want to add that little touch of self-expression to your computing space. For these reasons and more, a wide range of mouse pads are available for you to peruse. Mobile mouse pads are useful for internet cafes and other public areas where there's no guarantee you'll be able to find a spot to lay your computer. Tablet or laptop, these allow you to use a USB mouse without fear of your cursor lagging or getting lost in a browser window. They also come in a wide variety of colors and designs, and with thin, lightweight builds, they easily fit into backpacks and computer bags. Gamers know that a good gaming mouse pad is essential for in-game performance and accuracy. If your laser or roller ball loses traction for even a moment, it could spell the difference between victory and defeat. Various dimensions of mouse pads give these elite users more space to play without having to lift the mouse and reset the field. What's more, specialized gaming pads have fiber weaves and ergonomic design specifically meant to maximize accuracy in gameplay. Perfect for home or office, serious or casual use, the mouse pad makes a statement about the person who uses it. They create an oasis for a wired or USB mouse where accuracy and ease of use are guaranteed, even when you're on the go.", "parent_text": "Keyboards & Mice", "keyword_density": {"pads": "1.4", "mouse": "3.5", "mouse pads": "2.1"}, "department_id": 1},
{"nr_products": 621, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Other-Adapters-Gender-Changers/SubCategory/ID-353", "text": "Other Adapters & Gender Changers", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Keyboards-Mice/Category/ID-234", "parent_text": "Keyboards & Mice", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 125, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Mac-Memory/SubCategory/ID-551", "text": "Mac Memory", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Memory for your Mac", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Memory/Category/ID-17", "keyword_count": {"mac": 11, "memory": 3}, "description_wc": 284, "description_text": "It might have seemed back when you bought your MacBook you thought that 4GB of RAM was going to cut it. Now that you've hit your performance limit and want enhanced turnaround without the hassle of removable hard drives or USB thumb sticks, getting additional Mac RAM installed can have your system running like a pro again. Usually a Macbook Pro will give you two slots for additional memory and various other machines like the Mini and PowerMac may have explicit preferences, so optimizing this space is crucial. When shopping for upgrades, look for models that offer heat spreaders and lower tRas values. These features mean lower likelihood of overheating if you try to further modify your Mac, and even if you leave your Mac RAM as the manufacturer intended, a low tRas means faster operating speeds. Also, Macbook Pro owners should watch out for XMP-restricted RAM - this stuff will only function at 1333MHz, so you may not want to pay more for something that doesn't work the way you want it to. With the right tweaking, you can get your laptop functioning almost at the same capacity as a desktop model without spending nearly the same amount of money. For optimal output and performance make sure you check first and see what kind of memory your Mac uses. For every kind of Apple product there are corresponding limits on the amount and kinds of memory that will work for your machine, and it's important not to damage your computer in the process of upgrading. Optimal setups will run at 1600MHz but be aware that you can scale this down to get larger amounts of Mac RAM without sacrificing functionality.", "parent_text": "Memory", "keyword_density": {"mac": "3.9", "memory": "1.1"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 1951, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Mice/SubCategory/ID-65", "text": "Mice", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Wireless Mice, Optical Mice, Laser Mice and Trackball Mice", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Keyboards-Mice/Category/ID-234", "keyword_count": {"wireless": 4, "mice": 3}, "description_wc": 113, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Computer Mice in our Learning Center At Newegg you can choose from a massive selection of computer mice from industry leading manufacturers including wired and wireless products, as well as sleek space-saving designs for notebook computers and ergonomic mice for the utmost in user comfort and gaming performance regardless of hand-orientation. Brands featured at Newegg include Microsoft, Kensington, Logitech, Targus and others in configurations of RF wireless, Fast RF wireless, Bluetooth Wireless, and standard PS/2 and USB wired interfaces. With a mouse to fit every computer performance need Newegg has what you need. For more information, please see our Computer Mouse Buying Guide.", "parent_text": "Keyboards & Mice", "keyword_density": {"wireless": "3.5", "mice": "2.7"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 636, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/KVM-Switches/SubCategory/ID-143", "text": "KVM Switches", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "KVM Switches", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Keyboards-Mice/Category/ID-234", "keyword_count": {"kvm": 6, "kvm switches": 4}, "description_wc": 247, "description_text": "Suppose you have more than one computer in the same room but you do not have enough room for a second monitor. Or, you have a laptop and want to use it with your home computer's keyboard, mouse and monitor, without changing your current setup. The answer lies in a handy device called a KVM switch. KVM stands for keyboard, video, mouse. The keyboard, video, and mouse set collectively is called a \"console.\" KVM switches allow you to connect a console to more than one computer. You simply connect your console cables to the output jacks of the switch and connect the switch to the connections on your computer that the keyboard mouse and monitor would normally be plugged into. It's that simple. KVM Switches Let You Switch between Consoles To switch consoles, you just push a button on the switch and it allows you to use the other console. KVM switches save you money because you won't have to purchase separate keyboards, mice, and monitors for each computer you use. It makes it very easy when one person uses more than one computer at work, for example. They are also useful for server farms with one staff person accessing each computer periodically, one at a time. When buying KVM switches, it is important to fully understand your needs before you buy anything. Make sure the switch you choose will support your monitor refresh rates and resolution so that the signals are not degraded.", "parent_text": "Keyboards & Mice", "keyword_density": {"kvm": "2.4", "kvm switches": "3.2"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 1433, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Desktop-Memory/SubCategory/ID-147", "text": "Desktop Memory", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Desktop Memory", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Memory/Category/ID-17", "keyword_count": {"memory": 16, "desktop memory": 1}, "description_wc": 300, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Desktop Memory in our Learning Center System memory is where a computer holds the programs and data that are currently in use. The definition of the word \"memory\" has become somewhat blurred over the years because there are different types of memory that a computer uses. In general, \"memory\" refers to the system memory, or RAM, which holds instructions that the processor uses, and the data the instructions work with. System memory is directly related to the performance of your computer. In some ways, it's even more important than the processor, because without enough memory, your processor cannot work to its full potential. Newer programs require more memory than older ones, so when buying a new computer, get the most memory that you can afford. Learn about Types of System Memory There are many different types of system memory available. Researching them will help you make an informed choice when you purchase your computer. Getting the right kind of memory for your system will also affect whether you can upgrade it later on, and by how much. With the right memory, you can move it from one system to another, or continue to use the same memory even after you upgrade your motherboard. Types of memory include 168-pin SDRAM, 184-pin DDR SDRAM, 240-pin DDR2 SDRAM, and 240-pin DDR3 SDRAM. Capacity typically ranges from 128MB to 2GB with speeds covering PC 100, PC 133, PC 2100, PC 2700, PC 3200, PC 4000, PC2 3200, PC2 4200, PC2 5300, PC2 5400, PC2 6400, PC2 8000, PC2 8500, PC2 8800, PC2 8888, PC2 9136, PC2 9200, PC2 9600, PC2 10000, PC2 10400, PC3 8500, PC3 10600, PC3 10666, PC3 10700, PC3 12800, PC3 13000, PC3 14400, PC3 15000, and so on.", "parent_text": "Memory", "keyword_density": {"desktop memory": "0.7", "memory": "5.3"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 12680, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Keyboards/SubCategory/ID-63", "text": "Keyboards", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Keyboards", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Keyboards-Mice/Category/ID-234", "keyword_count": {"keyboards": 4}, "description_wc": 392, "description_text": "The keyboard is without a doubt one of the most important computer accessories available. The computer keyboard is an input device that sends commands and text inputs to the computer, and is the main interface that we use to communicate or control the computer in combination with the mouse. Unfortunately, not every computer's keyboard is comfortable and sturdy. Without these two characteristics, productivity may decline as working becomes a hassle and can even be painful. You may believe that your typing technique requires improvement, but more often than not faulty hardware is the root of your discomfort. Not every model has wrist supports and you can hurt your arms while you type without assistance. Ergonomic keyboards are designed to help you use your computer without any pain. These models have larger bases, letting you rest your wrists and palms while typing. Instead of uncomfortably hovering over your keyboard, your hands have the necessary support to prevent any strain and reduce the likelihood of developing physical ailments like carpal tunnel syndrome. Pads are commonly found on gaming keyboards as those are meant for more casual use. During a marathon game session, players must usually enter a great deal of key commands. With a standard keyboard, this can lead to pain or discomfort, as their hands continually move without support or rest. Some gaming models, by contrast, have features that can improve a gamer's performance as well. Wireless keyboards are also available - these ensure that users aren't tethered to their desks. If you have a large enough screen, you can use your device while sitting away from your computer. Working without wires also allows you to find a relaxed position, so you aren't confined to a single table. Buying a new keyboard can improve your typing proficiency, whether you're writing a term paper or playing a video game. The right device can raise your comfort levels while also making it easier to use your computer through key commands. Brands featured at Newegg include Microsoft, KeyTronic, Adesso, Logitech and many others. Available in multiple styles and versions you can find one to suit your unique needs rather it's multimedia, gaming, or just looking for the latest new thing. At Newegg you'll find what you need. Use this link for more information on Computer Keyboards in our Learning Center", "parent_text": "Keyboards & Mice", "keyword_density": {"keyboards": "1.0"}, "department_id": 1},
{"nr_products": 54, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Mouse-Keyboard-PS2-Cables/SubCategory/ID-2824", "text": "Mouse / Keyboard (PS2) Cables", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Keyboards-Mice/Category/ID-234", "parent_text": "Keyboards & Mice", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 1869, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Flash-Memory/SubCategory/ID-68", "text": "Flash Memory", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Flash Memory", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Memory/Category/ID-17", "keyword_count": {"memory": 14, "flash": 12, "flash memory": 9}, "description_wc": 323, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on Flash Memory in our Learning Center Flash memory offers non-volatile data storage and thus is capable of retaining it's data even when it's power source has been turned off. This makes it ideal for devices such as digital cameras where batteries go dead often. With being able to retain data even when power is lost you can rest assured that all your pictures will still be kept safe on the memory card. Examples of flash memory cards include Secure Digital (SD) memory cards, Compact Flash (CF) memory cards, and Sony's Memory Sticks (MS, M2, MS Duo, MS Pro, and MS Pro Duo) to name a few. Other examples of proprietary and permanent flash memory devices include memory cards for video gaming systems. The Benefits of Flash Memory Flash memory is extremely small, fast, lightweight, and makes no noise or have any moving parts, unlike hard drives. However, hard disks can hold considerably more data and its cost per megabyte is much cheaper although prices are quickly dropping as capacity grows larger for flash devices daily. Yet flash memory is quite reliable and allows you to specify which data you want to keep. USB flash drives are known as the floppy disks of the 21st century. You can see people walking around with them dangling from key chains, backpacks, and even around their necks. These are more resistant to physical abuse than the media cards used in digital cameras. They're also an improvement over optical storage like CDs and DVDs, which are easily scratched. Prices of the drives have come down so much that many companies give them to clients instead of printing reports and wasting paper and ink. In some schools, students are required to have them. At Newegg, we stock a wide variety of flash memory. Browse our site to find the lowest prices on the flash memory you want.", "parent_text": "Memory", "keyword_density": {"flash memory": "5.6", "flash": "3.7", "memory": "4.3"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 354, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Power-Strips/SubCategory/ID-350", "text": "Power Strips", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Power Strips", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Power-Protection/Category/ID-314", "keyword_count": {"strips": 4, "power strips": 3, "power": 8}, "description_wc": 312, "description_text": "Everything runs on electricity these days, it seems. Even wireless devices need to recharge from time to time, and only solar-powered technology can run without being anchored occasionally to a power source. With so many devices demanding electrical attention, there just aren't enough outlets in any given home to accommodate all of them. That's why power strips are so essential. Any computer, home entertainment system or kitchen appliance will need one or more sockets for each device incorporated in a suite of tools. Some may need a half dozen or more just to achieve basic functionality. Power strips take a single wall outlet and turn it into a hub for devices, providing 2 or 3 extra sockets for extension cord models, or upwards of 10 to 12 for high-traffic areas. Some of these are also outfitted with surge protectors and backup power alerts. These strips will automatically switch off if they detect a jump in electrical current, protecting all devices attached to it. Others will also supply a small amount of energy for a short period and issue an audible chime to alert people nearby that an event has occurred and power needs to be restored. Other safety features also include protective caps to prevent accidental electrocution from an exposed socket, which is great for households with pets or small children. These tools can also help save on your electricity bill. Instead of struggling to manually unplug and reconnect each device when you aren't using it, you can simply flip the power switch on the strip and turn everything off or back on again at once. Power strips are safe, versatile and provide necessary electricity to all the utilities in your home. Be it for recreation or practical use, they are a reliable way of multiplying the number of things you can do in any given room.", "parent_text": "Power Protection", "keyword_density": {"strips": "1.3", "power strips": "1.9", "power": "2.6"}, "department_id": 1},
{"nr_products": 708, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Surge-Suppressors/SubCategory/ID-535", "text": "Surge Suppressors", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Power-Protection/Category/ID-314", "parent_text": "Power Protection", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 636, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/KVM-Switches/SubCategory/ID-143", "text": "KVM Switches", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "KVM Switches", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Networking/Category/ID-281", "keyword_count": {"kvm": 6, "kvm switches": 4}, "description_wc": 247, "description_text": "Suppose you have more than one computer in the same room but you do not have enough room for a second monitor. Or, you have a laptop and want to use it with your home computer's keyboard, mouse and monitor, without changing your current setup. The answer lies in a handy device called a KVM switch. KVM stands for keyboard, video, mouse. The keyboard, video, and mouse set collectively is called a \"console.\" KVM switches allow you to connect a console to more than one computer. You simply connect your console cables to the output jacks of the switch and connect the switch to the connections on your computer that the keyboard mouse and monitor would normally be plugged into. It's that simple. KVM Switches Let You Switch between Consoles To switch consoles, you just push a button on the switch and it allows you to use the other console. KVM switches save you money because you won't have to purchase separate keyboards, mice, and monitors for each computer you use. It makes it very easy when one person uses more than one computer at work, for example. They are also useful for server farms with one staff person accessing each computer periodically, one at a time. When buying KVM switches, it is important to fully understand your needs before you buy anything. Make sure the switch you choose will support your monitor refresh rates and resolution so that the signals are not degraded.", "parent_text": "Networking", "keyword_density": {"kvm": "2.4", "kvm switches": "3.2"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 15, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Laptop-Networking/SubCategory/ID-34", "text": "Laptop Networking", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Laptop Wireless Cards", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Networking/Category/ID-281", "keyword_count": {"wireless": 7, "cards": 4, "laptop": 6, "wireless cards": 2, "laptop wireless cards": 1}, "description_wc": 313, "description_text": "Wi-Fi connectivity makes a laptop even more useful to its owner. Most people use their computers as gateways to the internet, so it can be frustrating if they can't go online because they can't find an ethernet cable. Consumers can buy wireless cards for laptops so their devices can connect with a signal from anywhere. These cards need to be installed to a computer's motherboard to use a wireless signal. Many of the available models come with tutorials and instruction guides, so even shoppers who aren't tech-savvy can easily install their new purchase. Laptop wireless cards act as internal receivers, allowing a computer to connect to the internet over the air without an ethernet cord. Users who are on the go need this added convenience so their devices can be fully functional anywhere there's a wireless signal. For example, college students can install a card so their laptops work in class and in the library - not just in their dorm rooms or apartments. A laptop must be within a certain proximity to a Wi-Fi router to receive the signal, as the card itself does not generate web connectivity. Fortunately, many establishments, ranging from coffee shops to public libraries, provide wireless web access, so everyone can find a place to go online. For users who want to add an ethernet connection to their notebook, there are cards with jacks for cords. Manufacturers have begun producing slim laptops that remove ethernet ports to reduce the devices' overall weight. Much like a wireless card, these units are installed internally but have an external attachment intended for a wired connection. You should make sure the wireless card you're thinking about purchasing matches your computer's hardware specifications. Access points must have driver support to function properly, so be sure to check what your system is capable of supporting.", "parent_text": "Networking", "keyword_density": {"wireless": "2.2", "cards": "1.3", "laptop": "1.9", "wireless cards": "1.3", "laptop wireless cards": "1.0"}, "department_id": 1},
