{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 433, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Intel-Motherboards/SubCategory/ID-280", "text": "Intel Motherboards", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Intel Motherboards", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Motherboards/Category/ID-20", "keyword_count": {"intel": 8, "motherboards": 4}, "description_wc": 304, "description_text": "Inspiring a better future through technology.\u2019 Intel, as a technology leader in over 40 years, brings new experiences to your home and work by delivering maximized performance and stunning visuals. Home users, causal & extreme gamers, overclockers and content creators are the audience Intel always keeps in mind when designing its innovative technologies. Intel based motherboards empower faster computing for both home and work applications. Why let your old PC hold you back from enjoying the latest 4K resolution games, 3D movies and HD content streaming? Newegg delivers a full range of motherboards with the latest Intel chipsets (X79/Z87/H87/Q87/B85/H81/H61) for Sandy Bridge, Ivy Bridge and Haswell based Intel Core i7/ i5/ i3 Processors in LGA 2011/1155/1150. You will easily find your choice of motherboards supporting multi-graphics technologies like 3-way SLI, 4-way SLI and Quad CrossFire, and the latest memory technology like DDR3 3000 here at Newegg. Understanding Motherboard Specifications Motherboard (alternatively known as mainboard, system board or logic board), the \u2018mother\u2019 of all components, is the main printed circuit board found in personal computers, workstations and other computing system. Its embedded chipset holds a key function to connect many of the crucial pc components of the system, such as CPU, Memory, Hard Drive, Graphics Card and other I/O cards. And also, it provides the connectivity for other external peripherals thru I/O connectors, like keyboard and mouse. Each chipset has its own unique design determining system performance, upgradability and connectivity. Form factor is another crucial element to determine for expandability. It\u2019s important to acknowledge Intel desktop chipsets designed for supporting only Intel Core, Pentium and Celeron processors (Please check the motherboard specifications for CPU Socket compatibility). Use this link for more information on Intel Compatible Motherboards in our Learning Center", "parent_text": "Motherboards", "keyword_density": {"intel": "2.6", "motherboards": "1.3"}, "department_id": 1},
