{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "level": 0, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Backup-Devices-Media/Category/ID-2", "text": "Backup Devices & Media", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Backup Devices & Media", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "keyword_count": {"media": 1, "backup devices": 1}, "description_wc": 136, "description_text": "Backup devices include tape drive, ZIP drive and floppy drive. Tape drive is a data storage device that reads and writes data stored on a magnetic tape. Tape drive is a typically used for archival storage of data stored on hard drives. Tape media generally has a favorable unit cost and long archival stability. ZIP drive is a medium-capacity removable disk storage system. Floppy disk is an obsolescent data storage medium that is composed of a disk of thin. Floppy disks are read and written by a floppy disk drive or FDD. WARNING: Products with exposed solder may contain lead, a chemical known to the State of California to cause cancer, birth defects and other reproductive harm. Please wash hands after handling internal components and motherboards and avoid inhalation of fumes if heating the solder.", "parent_text": "Computer Hardware", "keyword_density": {"media": "0.7", "backup devices": "1.5"}, "department_id": 1},
