{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 1397, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Mouse-Pads-Accessories/SubCategory/ID-202", "text": "Mouse Pads & Accessories", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Mouse Pads", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Accessories/Category/ID-1", "keyword_count": {"pads": 4, "mouse": 10, "mouse pads": 3}, "description_wc": 283, "description_text": "Not every surface is as conducive to mouse usage as you'd like. Sometimes there's no free tabletop space, or things are a bit sticky, or you want to use a mouse with a mobile device but your lap isn't the best for laser mice. Sometimes you may just want to add that little touch of self-expression to your computing space. For these reasons and more, a wide range of mouse pads are available for you to peruse. Mobile mouse pads are useful for internet cafes and other public areas where there's no guarantee you'll be able to find a spot to lay your computer. Tablet or laptop, these allow you to use a USB mouse without fear of your cursor lagging or getting lost in a browser window. They also come in a wide variety of colors and designs, and with thin, lightweight builds, they easily fit into backpacks and computer bags. Gamers know that a good gaming mouse pad is essential for in-game performance and accuracy. If your laser or roller ball loses traction for even a moment, it could spell the difference between victory and defeat. Various dimensions of mouse pads give these elite users more space to play without having to lift the mouse and reset the field. What's more, specialized gaming pads have fiber weaves and ergonomic design specifically meant to maximize accuracy in gameplay. Perfect for home or office, serious or casual use, the mouse pad makes a statement about the person who uses it. They create an oasis for a wired or USB mouse where accuracy and ease of use are guaranteed, even when you're on the go.", "parent_text": "Computer Accessories", "keyword_density": {"pads": "1.4", "mouse": "3.5", "mouse pads": "2.1"}, "department_id": 1},
{"level": -2, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Store/MasterComboStore.aspx?StoreID=7&name=DIY-PC-Combos", "text": "All DIY PC Combos", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/DIY-PC-SuperCombos/PromotionStore/ID-33?name=DIY-PC-SuperCombo", "parent_text": "DIY PC SuperCombo", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 9, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/CPU-Accessories/SubCategory/ID-151", "text": "CPU Accessories", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "CPU Accessories", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Accessories/Category/ID-1", "keyword_count": {"accessories": 5, "cpu": 6, "cpu accessories": 4}, "description_wc": 252, "description_text": "You can get all the CPU accessories you need at Newegg. We sell thousands of products from hundreds of networking experts, including everything you need to maintain networking productivity. Hiccups are inevitable. Finding an affordable solution could mean the difference between fluid networking and interrupted workflow. In addition to an all-inclusive inventory of hardware, a wide selection of add-on accessories makes shopping at Newegg even easier. Inexpensive CPU Accessories Searching for a fan connector adapter? Without the right flow of air around your hardware, you could be risking performance and putting your data in jeopardy. You can find a generic connector (3-pin to 4-pin) for just a few dollars. Isn't maintaining the integrity of your information worth a few bucks? AMD backing plates are used in conjunction with a heatsink. These small yet extremely important CPU accessories are essential for smooth networking operations. Created by Swiftech, these plates are available in both bronze and chrome. Is your cooling fan not getting the job done? Perhaps you need a Coolmax sensitive fan adapter? Or better yet, a Thermaltake CPU ducting fan? These components will help increase airflow while minimizing the sound coming from your CPU. Newegg is the one-stop source for your CPU accessories. WARNING: Products with exposed solder may contain lead, a chemical known to the State of California to cause cancer, birth defects and other reproductive harm. Please wash hands after handling internal components and motherboards and avoid inhalation of fumes if heating the solder.", "parent_text": "Computer Accessories", "keyword_density": {"cpu accessories": "3.2", "accessories": "2.0", "cpu": "2.4"}, "department_id": 1},
{"nr_products": 690, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/External-Enclosures/SubCategory/ID-92", "text": "External Enclosures", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Accessories/Category/ID-1", "description_wc": 124, "description_text": "External Enclosures Adding additional external storage space to your system helps protect your data and allows you to transfer it from one system to another. You can take former internal drives, put them in a new FireWire (IEEE 1394), USB, IDE, SATA/eSATA or other enclosure, and take your data with you. You can find enclosures for 1.8\" drives, 2.5\" drives, 3.5\" drives and 5.25\" drives, made from aluminum, plastic or other metal, and in a variety of colors. We offer enclosures from Crucial, OKGEAR, AcomData, EAGLE TECH, Enermax, Powmax, Addonics Technologies, Rosewill, GWC, Sabrent, AMC, ICY DOCK, Silverstone, Antec, INOI, STARTECH, IOGEAR, Syba, i-rocks, TAGAN, Kingwin, Thermaltake, Belkin, Koutech, Transcend, Vantec, Bytecc, Macally, Cooler Master, Mapower, XION, CoolMax, MASSCOOL and Zonet.", "parent_text": "Computer Accessories", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 636, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/KVM-Switches/SubCategory/ID-143", "text": "KVM Switches", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "KVM Switches", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Accessories/Category/ID-1", "keyword_count": {"kvm": 6, "kvm switches": 4}, "description_wc": 247, "description_text": "Suppose you have more than one computer in the same room but you do not have enough room for a second monitor. Or, you have a laptop and want to use it with your home computer's keyboard, mouse and monitor, without changing your current setup. The answer lies in a handy device called a KVM switch. KVM stands for keyboard, video, mouse. The keyboard, video, and mouse set collectively is called a \"console.\" KVM switches allow you to connect a console to more than one computer. You simply connect your console cables to the output jacks of the switch and connect the switch to the connections on your computer that the keyboard mouse and monitor would normally be plugged into. It's that simple. KVM Switches Let You Switch between Consoles To switch consoles, you just push a button on the switch and it allows you to use the other console. KVM switches save you money because you won't have to purchase separate keyboards, mice, and monitors for each computer you use. It makes it very easy when one person uses more than one computer at work, for example. They are also useful for server farms with one staff person accessing each computer periodically, one at a time. When buying KVM switches, it is important to fully understand your needs before you buy anything. Make sure the switch you choose will support your monitor refresh rates and resolution so that the signals are not degraded.", "parent_text": "Computer Accessories", "keyword_density": {"kvm": "2.4", "kvm switches": "3.2"}, "department_id": 1},
