{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 1568, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/HDMI-Cables/SubCategory/ID-2809", "text": "HDMI Cables", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "HDMI Cables", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Accessories/Category/ID-1", "keyword_count": {"cables": 7, "hdmi": 8, "hdmi cables": 3}, "description_wc": 368, "description_text": "The visual perks of HD video in high resolution formats such as 1080p can turn your favorite movies - even those you've seen a dozen times - into entirely new, fresh experiences. However, you need a proper HDMI cable to complete the connection between your television and cable box, game console, DVD or Blu-ray player. Luckily for you, we've got a wide range of HDMI cables in stock. These range from affordable models priced at bargain rates to high-end Monster HDMI cable as well as those made by Cables to Go and other top-tier names in the industry, all of which have been engineered with the finest precision. Take a look at our selection and choose for yourself! If you're looking for a simple, straightforward and affordable HDMI to DVI cable, you won't be disappointed with what you find in our selection. Cables for this purpose with notably low prices are available from manufacturers including Rosewill, Kaybles, Nippon Labs, Link Depot, Bytecc and many others. These will be compatible with DVD and Blu-ray players, HDTV receivers, projectors and A/V receivers - essentially, any device for which you need to provide HDMI connectivity. True audiophiles and movie buffs will not be satisfied with the quality of a standard HDMI cable, and may want to try one of the high-end cables made by Monster or Cables To Go. Though these are priced according to high-end standards, you'll certainly get nothing less than what you pay for in terms of quality. Constructed of fine materials including 24-karat gold-plated connectors, silver-coated oxygen-free (OFC) conductors and nitrogen-injected gas dielectric to ensure durability, signal strength and visual quality, these are certain to produce a crisp image and powerful sound. You can find models that occupy a middle ground between upscale quality and affordability, and if you need HDMI cables for specific purposes, such as connecting to a camcorder or an Ethernet IP enabled device, those are available as well. By choosing one of our many HDMI cables, you'll be sure to get the best visual bang for your buck while experiencing your favorite movies, TV shows and video games.", "parent_text": "Computer Accessories", "keyword_density": {"cables": "1.9", "hdmi": "2.2", "hdmi cables": "1.6"}, "department_id": 1},
{"nr_products": 19, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/IDE-Cables/SubCategory/ID-2818", "text": "IDE Cables", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/CD-DVD-Blu-Ray-Burners-Media/Category/ID-10", "parent_text": "CD / DVD / Blu-Ray Burners & Media", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 14, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/CD-DVD-Drives/SubCategory/ID-55", "text": "CD / DVD Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "CD and DVD Drives", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/CD-DVD-Blu-Ray-Burners-Media/Category/ID-10", "keyword_count": {"dvd": 5, "drives": 2, "cd": 6}, "description_wc": 294, "description_text": "A CD drive is an essential component in most computers. Users need the access port to watch DVDs, burn discs, copy music files and install software. As with most technology, the devices are sensitive and can malfunction, leading to the need for repair or replacement. For consumers that have experienced electrical failure with their CD/DVD drive, there are replacement drives available that can be easily installed into the old device's slot. This is a cost-effective alternative to hiring a technician or sending a computer to a retailer or manufacturer for repairs. The most important part of buying a new CD Rom drive is finding out if it is compatible with your system. You can check by reading your computer's hardware specifications and matching them against what a new drive requires. Ultra-slim notebooks and netbooks do not come with an internal DVD Rom drive, so users have no access to disc-based content. There are external drives available so consumers can watch DVDs or use a CD for storage. Most of these devices connect to a device via a USB cord. Some require two USB ports, so it's important for shoppers to buy one that matches the port availability of their computers. Being able to access content from CDs and DVDs is a necessity for most users. There is no need to buy a whole new system if a drive burns out, because they are detachable from a computer in most cases. Shoppers should research every piece of hardware before purchasing to avoid wasteful spending and the hassle of exchanging one piece of equipment for another. The first CD drive a consumer buys can be the last, by making sure it is compatible with their computer ahead of time.", "parent_text": "CD / DVD / Blu-Ray Burners & Media", "keyword_density": {"dvd": "1.7", "drives": "0.7", "cd": "2.0"}, "department_id": 1},
{"nr_products": 362, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/CD-DVD-Blu-Ray-Media/SubCategory/ID-71", "text": "CD / DVD / Blu-Ray Media", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/CD-DVD-Blu-Ray-Burners-Media/Category/ID-10", "parent_text": "CD / DVD / Blu-Ray Burners & Media", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"nr_products": 101, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/External-CD-DVD-Blu-Ray-Drives/SubCategory/ID-420", "text": "External CD / DVD / Blu-Ray Drives", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/CD-DVD-Blu-Ray-Burners-Media/Category/ID-10", "parent_text": "CD / DVD / Blu-Ray Burners & Media", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Cables/Category/ID-197", "text": "Cables", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Cables Overview", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Accessories/Category/ID-1", "keyword_count": {"cables": 10}, "description_wc": 278, "description_text": "Cables and cords carry current, connect components and create the center of our convenient entertainment experience when coupled with the right devices. Start by determining what you want to accomplish with your array of devices, and count on cables to provide the connectivity you need to make the dream a reality. Computer cables are essential for powering and utilizing your PC or laptop, connecting external devices and peripherals to enhance the experience. If your camera or camcorder doesn't have removable memory, USB and micro USB cables can get your media transferred from hardware to software devices. Network cables let you get online and share your uploaded images via the Internet. HDMI cables and USB cables connect your computer to your television and entertainment center. To get the best sound and balance out of your audio receiver and speaker system, audio/video cables like VGA splitters, basic RCA or component and composite variations, stereo and s-video cables all help you manipulate and connect hardware for maximized quality output. Extension cords are essential for larger spaces or for positioning your gaming and entertainment center with the most zen and flow, and not being tethered to the nearest outlet. To speed up your connections and make communication between devices easier, you might want to switch your USB cables to Firewire versions and try network Ethernet cords instead of basic models. Understanding your devices and finding faster ways to bridge them can be accomplished with competent cable connections and creative construction of your entertainment space. Extensions and upgrades can give you an enhanced experience without sacrificing connectivity, by choosing wiring that compliments your current cache of computing and media devices.", "parent_text": "Computer Accessories", "keyword_density": {"cables": "3.6"}, "department_id": 1},
