{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 31, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/CD-DVD-Burners/SubCategory/ID-5", "text": "CD / DVD Burners", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "CD/DVD Burners (RW Drives)", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/CD-DVD-Blu-Ray-Burners-Media/Category/ID-10", "keyword_count": {"dvd burners": 3, "dvd": 6, "burners": 7, "cd": 6}, "description_wc": 163, "description_text": "Use this link for more information on CD and DVD Burners in our Learning Center Newegg.com offers a large selection of CD burners, Combo and DVD burners with different functions at a range prices. We have CD and DVD burners from all the major manufacturer, like Lite-On, ASUS, Pioneer, LG, Sony, Philips, HP, Samsung and more! We carry straight CD burners, combination models for CDs and DVDs, and even HD-DVD (a discontinued format), and some Blue-Ray burners, depending on your need. Capable of writing data to the optical discs, burners offer you more amazing experience than the read-only optical drive devices, CD-ROM and DVD-ROM. Just opt for a burner that works for you! WARNING: Products with exposed solder may contain lead, a chemical known to the State of California to cause cancer, birth defects and other reproductive harm. Please wash hands after handling internal components and motherboards and avoid inhalation of fumes if heating the solder.", "parent_text": "CD / DVD / Blu-Ray Burners & Media", "keyword_density": {"dvd burners": "3.7", "dvd": "3.7", "burners": "4.3", "cd": "3.7"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 14, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Blu-Ray-Burners/SubCategory/ID-600", "text": "Blu-Ray Burners", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Blu-ray Burners/Writers", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/CD-DVD-Blu-Ray-Burners-Media/Category/ID-10", "keyword_count": {"blu ray": 9, "writers": 1}, "description_wc": 329, "description_text": "Blu-ray discs provide enormous storage space for files and data. Unfortunately for users, most PC's do not have a Blu-ray burner as standard equipment, so consumers cannot copy their image and video files onto the discs. The good news is that shoppers can find an external Blu-ray burner so all their content can be stored on Blu-ray discs and be displayed in the highest definition possible. Instead of being limited to burning DVDs, you can share your home movies and photography with friends and family in a format featuring unmatched picture quality. Blu-ray discs have greater storage capacity than other file back-up methods, like DVDs and some flash drives. It is also easier to share content through a disc than giving a close friend your camera to cycle through vacation pictures or sending videos in a multimedia message from your smartphone. Blu-ray discs provide flexibility regarding which formats it can save, so users can back-up all their content regardless of how the file was saved or which program was used to create it. Unlike an external hard drive, there is no chance for a disc to malfunction electronically unless it is scratched, and the only way to lose any data is to misplace the disc. Finding the best Blu-ray burner for you means considering your needs and what would be compatible with your PC. Not every external disc writer is supported by a computer's hardware, so it's important to figure out what your equipment can work with and what would be a wasteful purchase. Buying a burner from the same manufacturer as your computer could help avoid incompatibility issues. Some Blu-ray writers have a limited warranty, so if you're concerned about the longevity of the device or potential system incompatibility, these may be the best available options. For users who want to save and share content via Blu-ray, an external burner is a necessity.", "parent_text": "CD / DVD / Blu-Ray Burners & Media", "keyword_density": {"blu ray": "5.5", "writers": "0.3"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 33, "level": -1, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Barebone-PCs/SubCategory/ID-3", "text": "Barebone PCs", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Barebone Computers", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Barebone-Mini-Computers/Category/ID-3", "keyword_count": {"barebone": 3, "barebone computers": 1}, "description_wc": 119, "description_text": "Use this link for more on Barebone Computers in our Learning Center The barebone is a relatively new methodology in the building of the personal computer system. A barebone system provides a pre-assembled combination of several basic components that a computer system must include, and leaves room for DIYers to select the important components which may be upgraded more frequently. You'll usually get a case with power supply motherboard and cooling system, and the rest is up to you. Occasionally you'll also get a CPU or some RAM, but more often than not, those are ready for you to customize. Add CPUs, Audio or Video Cards, RAM and Hard Disks, and build the system you want!", "parent_text": "Barebone / Mini Computers", "keyword_density": {"barebone": "2.5", "barebone computers": "1.7"}, "department_id": 1},
