{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 1568, "level": -3, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/HDMI-Cables/SubCategory/ID-2809", "text": "HDMI Cables", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "HDMI Cables", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Video-Cables/Category/ID-185", "keyword_count": {"cables": 7, "hdmi": 8, "hdmi cables": 3}, "description_wc": 368, "description_text": "The visual perks of HD video in high resolution formats such as 1080p can turn your favorite movies - even those you've seen a dozen times - into entirely new, fresh experiences. However, you need a proper HDMI cable to complete the connection between your television and cable box, game console, DVD or Blu-ray player. Luckily for you, we've got a wide range of HDMI cables in stock. These range from affordable models priced at bargain rates to high-end Monster HDMI cable as well as those made by Cables to Go and other top-tier names in the industry, all of which have been engineered with the finest precision. Take a look at our selection and choose for yourself! If you're looking for a simple, straightforward and affordable HDMI to DVI cable, you won't be disappointed with what you find in our selection. Cables for this purpose with notably low prices are available from manufacturers including Rosewill, Kaybles, Nippon Labs, Link Depot, Bytecc and many others. These will be compatible with DVD and Blu-ray players, HDTV receivers, projectors and A/V receivers - essentially, any device for which you need to provide HDMI connectivity. True audiophiles and movie buffs will not be satisfied with the quality of a standard HDMI cable, and may want to try one of the high-end cables made by Monster or Cables To Go. Though these are priced according to high-end standards, you'll certainly get nothing less than what you pay for in terms of quality. Constructed of fine materials including 24-karat gold-plated connectors, silver-coated oxygen-free (OFC) conductors and nitrogen-injected gas dielectric to ensure durability, signal strength and visual quality, these are certain to produce a crisp image and powerful sound. You can find models that occupy a middle ground between upscale quality and affordability, and if you need HDMI cables for specific purposes, such as connecting to a camcorder or an Ethernet IP enabled device, those are available as well. By choosing one of our many HDMI cables, you'll be sure to get the best visual bang for your buck while experiencing your favorite movies, TV shows and video games.", "parent_text": "Computer Video Cables", "keyword_density": {"cables": "1.9", "hdmi": "2.2", "hdmi cables": "1.6"}, "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 636, "level": -3, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/KVM-Switches/SubCategory/ID-143", "text": "KVM Switches", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "KVM Switches", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Cables/Category/ID-186", "keyword_count": {"kvm": 6, "kvm switches": 4}, "description_wc": 247, "description_text": "Suppose you have more than one computer in the same room but you do not have enough room for a second monitor. Or, you have a laptop and want to use it with your home computer's keyboard, mouse and monitor, without changing your current setup. The answer lies in a handy device called a KVM switch. KVM stands for keyboard, video, mouse. The keyboard, video, and mouse set collectively is called a \"console.\" KVM switches allow you to connect a console to more than one computer. You simply connect your console cables to the output jacks of the switch and connect the switch to the connections on your computer that the keyboard mouse and monitor would normally be plugged into. It's that simple. KVM Switches Let You Switch between Consoles To switch consoles, you just push a button on the switch and it allows you to use the other console. KVM switches save you money because you won't have to purchase separate keyboards, mice, and monitors for each computer you use. It makes it very easy when one person uses more than one computer at work, for example. They are also useful for server farms with one staff person accessing each computer periodically, one at a time. When buying KVM switches, it is important to fully understand your needs before you buy anything. Make sure the switch you choose will support your monitor refresh rates and resolution so that the signals are not degraded.", "parent_text": "Computer Cables", "keyword_density": {"kvm": "2.4", "kvm switches": "3.2"}, "department_id": 1},
{"nr_products": 80, "level": -4, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Phone-Cables/SubCategory/ID-2826", "text": "Phone Cables", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_wc": 0, "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Network-Cables/Category/ID-187", "parent_text": "Network Cables", "department_text": "Computer Hardware", "department_id": 1},
{"department_text": "Computer Hardware", "nr_products": 3744, "level": -4, "url": "http://www.newegg.com/Network-Ethernet-Cables/SubCategory/ID-2825", "text": "Network Ethernet Cables", "department_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Computer-Hardware/Store", "description_title": "Network Cables", "parent_url": "http://www.newegg.com/Network-Cables/Category/ID-187", "keyword_count": {"cables": 8, "network": 2}, "description_wc": 279, "description_text": "Computer cables get your system talking, so to speak. Achieving full functionality over variable connection volumes and different distances means giving it all the bridges necessary to send and receive data, be it within a local area or over a wide network. Various connections will require different kinds of ethernet cables and other cords, so determining your system needs should always be the first step. Ethernet cable comes in different categories and can meet various needs depending on what you select. Cat5 cables as well as cat6 cables are composed of a twisted pair structure, meaning a coupled set of wires is wrapped within a protective insulation casing. This design helps cancel out electronic interference and allows data to be carried securely over large physical distances. The color of the insulation casing can tell you how many twists per meter the cable has, what kind of wiring is present, the kind of connecting head it is compatible with and what uses it can handle. Cat5 cables have largely been replaced by cat5e, or enhanced cables, and cat6 cables also come in cat6a, or augmented, capacity. All variations offer a maximum length of 100 meters, but cat5/5e offers support of up to 100 MHz while cat6 can handle up to 250 MHz and cat6a is approved at 500 MHz. The cat5 cables also are unshielded, meaning interference stands a better chance of breaking the data stream if housed in an environment with many other competing signals. Determining which cord is right for your system will require accessing your space, planning your network requirements and pricing each option to find the one that most matches your performance and communication expectations.", "parent_text": "Network Cables", "keyword_density": {"cables": "2.9", "network": "0.7"}, "department_id": 1},
